{"title_page": "R. Madhavan", "text_new": "{{short description|Indian film actor, writer and producer}}\n{{EngvarB|date=March 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name = R. Madhavan\n| image = Madhavan Saala Khadoos (cropped).jpg\n| image_size = 225px\n| caption = Madhavan in 2016\n| birth_name = Madhavan Balaji Ranganathan\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|df=y|1970|06|01}}\n| birth_place = Tamil nadu, India\n| education = \n| occupation = {{hlist|Actor|writer|producer|director}}\n| years_active = 1994\u2013present\n| nationality  = Indian\n| spouse = {{Marriage|Sarita Birje|1999}}\n| children = 1\n| partner = \n}}\n\n'''R. Madhavan''' (born 1 June 1970) is an Indian actor, writer and film producer who predominantly appears in [[Tamil language|Tamil]] and [[Hindi]] language films. He has received four [[Filmfare Awards South|Filmfare Awards]] and an award from the [[Tamil Nadu State Film Awards]] along with recognition and nominations from other organisations. He has been described as one of the few actors in India who is able to achieve pan-Indian appeal, having appeared in films from seven different languages.<ref name=\"pan-Indian\">{{cite web |year=2009 |title=R Madhavan signs up with Atul Kasbekar's Bling Entertainment |publisher=Business of Cinema |accessdate=4 February 2011 |url=http://www.businessofcinema.com/news.php?newsid=13618 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101201042753/http://businessofcinema.com/news.php?newsid=13618 |archivedate=1 December 2010 }}</ref><ref name=\"language\">{{cite news|author=Sharma, Smrity |title=Surya, Vikram need to learn Hindi: Madhavan |work=[[The Times of India]] |accessdate=4 February 2011 |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/regional/news-interviews/Surya-Vikram-need-to-learn-Hindi-Madhavan/articleshow/6913669.cms |date=13 November 2010 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101116181454/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/regional/news-interviews/Surya-Vikram-need-to-learn-Hindi-Madhavan/articleshow/6913669.cms |archivedate=16 November 2010 }}</ref>\n\nMadhavan began his acting career with television guest appearances, including a role on the [[Zee TV]] prime-time soap opera ''[[Banegi Apni Baat]]'' in 1994. After appearing in commercials and in small roles, he later gained [[Breakthrough role|recognition]] in the [[Tamil cinema|Tamil film industry]] through [[Mani Ratnam]]'s successful romance film ''[[Alaipayuthey]]'' (2000). Madhavan soon developed an image as a romantic hero with notable roles in two of 2001's highest grossing Tamil films, [[Gautham Menon]]'s directorial debut ''[[Minnale]]'' and [[Madras Talkies]]' ''[[Dumm Dumm Dumm]]''. He worked with Mani Ratnam again in the critically acclaimed 2002 film ''[[Kannathil Muthamittal]]'' playing the father of an adopted girl, whilst he achieved commercial success with his role in [[N. Linguswamy]]'s action film, ''[[Run (2002 film)|Run]]'' (2002). Madhavan was cast alongside [[Kamal Haasan]] in the 2003 drama ''[[Anbe Sivam]]'', which earned him two notable awards for Best Supporting Actor. In 2004, he gave a critically acclaimed performance as the antagonist in the multi-starrer ''[[Aayutha Ezhuthu]]'' and the film secured him his first [[Filmfare Awards South|Filmfare Award]] for the intense portrayal of a rogue.\n\nIn the mid-2000s, Madhavan also actively pursued a career in [[Bollywood|Hindi films]], by appearing in supporting roles in three highly successful productions, [[Rakeysh Omprakash Mehra]]'s ''[[Rang De Basanti]]'' (2006), Mani Ratnam's biopic ''[[Guru (2007 film)|Guru]]'' (2007) and [[Rajkumar Hirani]]'s ''[[3 Idiots]]'' (2009), which went on to become the [[List of highest-grossing Indian films|highest grossing Indian film of all time]] upon release. He simultaneously worked on Tamil films, gaining critical acclaim for his portrayal of a [[vigilante]] in his home production ''[[Evano Oruvan]]'' (2007) and for the successful bilingual horror film, ''[[Yavarum Nalam]]'' (2009). After appearing in further box office hits, ''[[Tanu Weds Manu]]'' (2011) and ''[[Vettai]]'' (2012), Madhavan took a break from acting. Returning after a three-year sabbatical in 2015, his comeback films, the romantic-comedy ''[[Tanu Weds Manu Returns]]'' (2015), the bilingual sports drama ''[[Irudhi Suttru]]'' (2016) and the crime film ''[[Vikram Vedha]]'' (2017) all won critical and commercial acclaim. His performance as a boorish boxing coach in ''Irudhi Suttru'' fetched him Best Actor awards at the [[Filmfare Award for Best Actor \u2013 Tamil|Filmfare]], [[2nd IIFA Utsavam|IIFA]] and [[South Indian International Movie Awards|SIIMA]] award ceremonies.<ref name=\"indiatimes1\">{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/winners-64th-jio-filmfare-awards-south/articleshow/59192157.cms|title=Winners: 64th Jio Filmfare Awards 2017 (South)|work=The Times of India|date=19 June 2017|access-date=21 June 2017|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6rJ496Tl8?url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/winners-64th-jio-filmfare-awards-south/articleshow/59192157.cms|archive-date=18 June 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=I have no insecurites: R Madhavan on 'Saala Khadoos', 'Tanu Weds Manu Returns' and Kangana Ranaut\n|url=http://www.firstpost.com/bollywood/i-have-no-insecurites-r-madhavan-on-saala-khadoos-tanu-weds-manu-returns-and-kangana-2312148.html |accessdate=27 June 2015 |publisher=FirstPost |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150627204437/http://www.firstpost.com/bollywood/i-have-no-insecurites-r-madhavan-on-saala-khadoos-tanu-weds-manu-returns-and-kangana-2312148.html |archivedate=27 June 2015 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title='Tanu Weds Manu Returns' Box Office Collection: Will Kangana-Madhavan Starrer Cross \u20b9150 Crore and Beat Salman's Movie Record by 6th Weekend? |url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/tanu-weds-manu-returns-box-office-collection-will-kangana-madhavan-starrer-cross-150-crore-637267 |accessdate=27 June 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150627175108/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/tanu-weds-manu-returns-box-office-collection-will-kangana-madhavan-starrer-cross-150-crore-637267 |archivedate=27 June 2015 }}</ref>\n\nIn addition to his acting career, Madhavan has worked as a writer on his films, hosted television programmes and has been a prominent celebrity endorser for brands and products.<ref name=\"oragadam\">{{cite web|year=2010 |title=Maddy's Oragadam turns out to be a hit |publisher=[[Sify]] |accessdate=4 February 2011 |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/maddys-oragadam-turns-out-to-be-a-hit-news-tamil-kkfquQbcbga.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110228045407/http://www.sify.com/movies/maddys-oragadam-turns-out-to-be-a-hit-news-tamil-kkfquQbcbga.html |archivedate=28 February 2011 }}</ref> He has also worked as a film producer, first making ''Evano Oruvan'' with Leukos Films, before setting up Tricolour Films to produce ''[[Irudhi Suttru|Saala Khadoos]]'' (2016). Madhavan is noted for his philanthropic activities and promotes various causes such as environment, health and education. He is particularly vocal about the protection of animals and was awarded PETA's Person of the Year recognition in 2011.\n\n==Early life==\nMadhavan was born on 1 June 1970 in [[Jamshedpur]], Bihar (now in [[Jharkhand]]), India, to a [[Tamil Brahmin]] family. His father Ranganathan was a management executive in [[Tata Steel]] and his mother, Saroja was a manager in the [[Bank of India]]. His younger sister, Devika, is a software engineer.<ref name=\"family\">{{cite news|author=Rangarajan, Malathi |year=2004 |title=He loves challenges |newspaper=[[The Hindu]] |accessdate=22 October 2004 |url=http://www.hindu.com/fr/2004/10/22/stories/2004102202400100.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20041112213630/http://www.hindu.com/fr/2004/10/22/stories/2004102202400100.htm |archivedate=12 November 2004 }}</ref> He had a Tamil-speaking upbringing in [[Bihar]].<ref name=\"tambrahm\">{{cite web|author=Jha, Subhash K. |year=2005 |title=He loves challenges |publisher=Nowrunning.com |accessdate=4 February 2011 |url=http://www.nowrunning.com/news/bollywood/madhavan-on-being-reel-life-bihari-real-life-father/4026/story.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121009171303/http://www.nowrunning.com/news/bollywood/madhavan-on-being-reel-life-bihari-real-life-father/4026/story.htm |archivedate= 9 October 2012 }}</ref>\n\nIn 1988, Madhavan gained a scholarship to represent India as a cultural ambassador from Rajaram College, [[Kolhapur]] and spent a year in [[Stettler, Alberta]], Canada as part of an exchange programme with [[Rotary International]]. He returned to Kolhapur and completed his education, graduating with a [[Bachelor of Science|BSc]] in [[Electronics]]. During his college years, Madhavan became actively involved in extra-curricular military training and at 22, he was recognised as amongst the leading [[National Cadet Corps (India)|NCC]] cadets in [[Maharashtra]], which allowed him to make a trip with seven others as [[National Cadet Corps (India)|NCC]] cadets to England.<ref name=\"twm2015\">{{cite web|author=Gupta, Priya K. |year=2015 |title=get along with people who get along with my wife: Maddy |work=[[The Times of India]] |accessdate=20 May 2015 |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/I-get-along-with-people-who-get-along-with-my-wife-Maddy/articleshow/47343041.cms |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150523072543/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/I-get-along-with-people-who-get-along-with-my-wife-Maddy/articleshow/47343041.cms |archivedate=23 May 2015 }}</ref> As a result of this opportunity, he received training with the [[British Army]], the [[Royal Navy]] and the [[Royal Air Force]], which he had, at a point, considered joining.<ref name=\"cadet\">{{cite web\n |author=Jain, Priyanka \n |year=2006 \n |title=Madhavan, the remote control pilot \n |publisher=[[Rediff]] \n |accessdate=8 February 2006 \n |url=http://in.rediff.com/movies/2006/feb/08mad.htm \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060222021718/http://in.rediff.com/movies/2006/feb/08mad.htm \n |archivedate=22 February 2006 \n}}</ref> However he missed the age cut-off by six months and was subsequently unable to join the programme. After he lost out on the place, he began teaching courses on public speaking and personality development skills in Kolhapur and the satisfaction he gained through teaching, prompted him to pursue a post-graduation in public speaking at [[Kishinchand Chellaram College]] in Bombay (present-day Mumbai). During the period, he also won the Indian Championship for [[Public Speaking]] and subsequently represented India at the Young Businessmen Conference in Tokyo, Japan in 1992.<ref name=\"speak\">{{cite web\n |author=Rangaswamy, Hema \n |title=City's Latest Heart Throb \n |publisher=Chennaibest.com \n |access-date=20 January 2001 \n |url=http://www.chennaibest.com/cityresources/Entertainment/movies/interviewmadhavan.asp \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20010304201747/http://www.chennaibest.com/cityresources/Entertainment/movies/interviewmadhavan.asp \n |archivedate= 4 March 2001 \n}}</ref> During his stint in Bombay, he opted to create a portfolio and submit it to a modelling agency.<ref name=\"twm2015\"/>\n\n==Acting career==\n===Early work===\nIn early 1996, Madhavan worked on a sandalwood talc advertisement directed by [[Santosh Sivan]], who later recommended him to [[Mani Ratnam]] to take part in a screen test for a role in ''[[Iruvar]]'' (1997). Madhavan was auditioned for the leading role of Tamizhselvan amongst several other more established actors, but Mani Ratnam eventually left him out of the project citing that he thought his \"eyes looked too young\" for a senior role.<ref name=\"iruvar\">{{cite web\n |author=Gliteratti \n |year=1996 \n |title=A Close Shave \n |publisher=[[Outlook India]] \n |accessdate=24 July 1996 \n |url=http://www.outlookindia.com/glitterati.aspx?41 \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101023221415/http://outlookindia.com/glitterati.aspx?41 \n |archivedate=23 October 2010 \n}}</ref><ref name=\"iruvargold\">{{cite web\n |author=Ganapati, Priya \n |year=2000 \n |title=People remember scenes, not episodes \n |publisher=[[Rediff]] \n |accessdate=8 March 2000 \n |url=http://www.rediff.com/entertai/2000/mar/08madh.htm \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120709061247/http://www.rediff.com/entertai/2000/mar/08madh.htm \n |archivedate= 9 July 2012 \n}}</ref> Prior to his film audition, Madhavan was spotted by a television executive while out walking in [[Lokhandwala]] in [[Mumbai]], and was recruited to feature in Hindi television serials, appearing as a crook in his first venture ''Yule Love Stories''. He appeared in leading roles in [[Zee TV]]'s ''[[Banegi Apni Baat]]'' and ''[[Ghar Jamai (TV series)|Ghar Jamai]]'', while he gained further popularity portraying the character of Shekhar in ''[[Saaya (Indian TV series)|Saaya]]''. He also went on to act as a ship's captain in ''[[Sea Hawks (TV series)|Sea Hawks]]'', as a convict in ''Yeh Kahan Aa Gaye Hum'' and worked as a television anchor in ''Tol Mol Ke Bol'' amongst other television appearances.<ref>{{cite web|author=site admin |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/magazine/cover-story/story/19970616-young-and-big-stars-of-television-831613-1997-06-16 |title=The rising stars |publisher=Indiatoday.in |date=16 June 1997 |accessdate=22 January 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"serials\">{{cite web\n |author=Express News Service \n |year=1998 \n |title=The man who acts Pricey. \n |work=[[The Indian Express]] \n |accessdate=11 August 1998 \n |url=http://www.indianexpress.com/res/web/pIe/ie/daily/19980811/22351284.html \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070929091446/http://www.indianexpress.com/res/web/pIe/ie/daily/19980811/22351284.html \n |archivedate=29 September 2007 \n}}</ref> His first appearance in a feature film role came through a small role in ''[[Is Raat Ki Subah Nahin]]'' (1996), where he portrayed a singer in a bar.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://in.movies.yahoo.com/news/manu-mania-r-madhavan-turns-42-183000043.html |title='Manu' Mania: R. Madhavan Turns 42! |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150611061803/https://in.movies.yahoo.com/news/manu-mania-r-madhavan-turns-42-183000043.html |archivedate=11 June 2015 }}</ref>\n\nIn 1997, Madhavan appeared in a supporting role as an Indian police officer in [[Fred Olen Ray]]'s English film, ''[[Inferno (1997 film)|Inferno]]'', which was shot in India.<ref name=\"iruvargold\"/> His first chance in [[Cinema of India|Indian cinema]] came in the form of ''[[Shanti Shanti Shanti]]'' (1998), a [[Kannada]] film, in which he appeared as a carefree youngster alongside actor [[Abbas (actor)|Abbas]]. However, the film failed to make an impact and went unnoticed at the box office.<ref name=\"sss\">{{cite web\n |author=Rajitha \n |year=2000 \n |title=Vijay meets his son on the Net! \n |publisher=[[Rediff]] \n |accessdate=26 August 2000 \n |url=http://www.rediff.com/entertai/2000/aug/26tt.htm \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20010303003735/http://www.rediff.com/entertai/2000/aug/26tt.htm \n |archivedate= 3 March 2001 \n}}</ref> During the period, Hindi film director Vinod Pandey launched Madhavan as a [[Bollywood]] hero, with a project titled ''[[Akeli (film)|Akeli]]'', however the film was shelved before the production process had been completed.<ref name=\"lakheli\">{{cite news\n |author=Karisma Upadhyay \n |title=Maddy Cool \n |work=[[The Times of India]] \n |accessdate=15 October 2001 \n |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/articleshow/1278036573.cms \n |date=15 October 2001 |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060427172423/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/articleshow/1278036573.cms \n |archivedate=27 April 2006 \n}}</ref>\n\n===1999\u20132003===\nIn 1999, leading Indian director [[Mani Ratnam]] selected Madhavan to feature in the leading role of his Tamil romantic film, ''[[Alaipayuthey]]'' (2000) and the film's subsequent critical and commercial success gave Madhavan his [[breakthrough role|breakthrough]] as an actor. Portraying the character of Karthik Varadharajan, a young husband experiencing difficulties with his marriage. Madhavan revealed that he studied the technical aspects of film-making from the director and learned the entire script of the film, irrespective of whether he was in the scene or not. He became the first debutant actor to be cast by Mani Ratnam in the lead role of a film, and revealed that when he found out that he was set to work with the director he was overcome with a \"mixture of excitement, awe, fear and expectations\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/tamil/interview.php?id=6005438&cid=2408 |title=Welcome to |publisher=Sify.com |date=20 January 2007 |accessdate=25 August 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140324200850/http://www.sify.com/movies/tamil/interview.php?id=6005438&cid=2408 |archivedate=24 March 2014 }}</ref> Featuring alongside actress [[Shalini]], Madhavan's performance was well received by critics and the film's success led to it developing \"classic\" status.<ref name=\"bebe\">{{cite news|author=Dutt, Purba |title=I'm very fond of Arya: Madhavan |work=[[The Times of India]] |accessdate=4 February 2011 |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/regional/news-interviews/Im-very-fond-of-Arya-Madhavan-/articleshow/6566336.cms |date=17 September 2010 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100920212100/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/regional/news-interviews/Im-very-fond-of-Arya-Madhavan-/articleshow/6566336.cms |archivedate=20 September 2010 }}</ref> A critic from [[The Hindu]], described that Madhavan \"sails through the litmus test with ease\", whilst another review cited that Madhavan was a \"promising debutant\" into the film industry.<ref name=\"aphindu\">{{cite web|year=2000 |title=Film Review: ''Alaipayuthey'' |work=[[The Hindu]] |accessdate=4 February 2011 |url=http://www.hinduonnet.com/2000/04/21/stories/09210225.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100901062104/http://www.hinduonnet.com/2000/04/21/stories/09210225.htm |archivedate= 1 September 2010 }}</ref><ref name=\"apindo\">{{cite web \n |author=Gopalakrishnan, Usha \n |year=2000 \n |title=Alai Payuthey \n |publisher=Indlink.com \n |accessdate=4 February 2011 \n |url=http://www.indolink.com/tamil/cinema/Reviews/articles/Alai_Payudhae_1374.html \n |url-status=dead \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120318001120/http://www.indolink.com/tamil/cinema/Reviews/articles/Alai_Payudhae_1374.html \n |archivedate=18 March 2012 \n }}</ref> After the success of his first [[Tamil film]], the producers of his previous [[Kannada]] film, ''Shanti Shanti Shanti'', dubbed the film into Tamil and released it as ''Relax'', to capitalise on Madhavan's new-found success.<ref name=\"sss\"/> Madhavan's next film, ''[[Ennavale]]'' (2000), garnered mixed reviews although Madhavan's portrayal was praised as the \"mainstay\" of the film, with claims that the film for him was a \"merely a prosaic exercise\".<ref name=\"enhindu\">{{cite news|author=Rangarajan, Malathi|year=2000|title=Film Review: Ennavale|newspaper=[[The Hindu]]|accessdate=4 February 2011|url=http://www.hindu.com/2000/12/29/stories/09290224.htm}}</ref>\n\nMadhavan's first release of 2001, [[Gautham Menon]]'s directorial debut ''[[Minnale]]'', opened to critical and commercial acclaim. Featuring a popular soundtrack by [[Harris Jayaraj]] and marketed as a [[Valentine's Day]] release, ''Minnale'' further built on the actor's image as a [[romantic hero]] and was later listed as a \"classic romantic film\" from the Tamil film industry.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/love-is-in-the-air-part-2-tamil-news-90963.html|title=Love is in the Air Part 2|accessdate=16 February 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"minhindu\">{{cite news|author=Padmanabhan, Savitha |title=Film Review: Minnale |work=[[The Hindu]] |accessdate=4 February 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/2001/02/09/stories/09090224.htm |location=Chennai, India |date=9 February 2001 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121108195114/http://www.hindu.com/2001/02/09/stories/09090224.htm |archivedate= 8 November 2012 }}</ref> He then collaborated with Mani Ratnam for the second time by appearing in the director's production venture, the romantic comedy ''[[Dumm Dumm Dumm]]'' (2001), alongside [[Jyothika]]. Appearing as an unhappy groom trying to halt his wedding, the film won positive acclaim and became a commercial success, with Madhavan establishing himself as a bankable actor in [[South India]].<ref name=\"twohits\">{{cite web|author=Shoba Warrior |year=2001 |title=Hindi films were to happen much later! |publisher=[[Rediff]] |accessdate=6 October 2001 |url=http://www.rediff.com/entertai/2001/oct/16gau.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20011016131729/http://www.rediff.com/entertai/2001/oct/16gau.htm |archivedate=16 October 2001 }}</ref> Madhavan then again appeared as a husband in a tumultuous marriage in ''[[Parthale Paravasam]]'' (2001), the hundredth venture of veteran director [[K. Balachander]]. Despite featuring amongst an ensemble cast and being highly anticipated prior to release, the film failed at the box-office, with critics citing that Madhavan looked \"rather bored\" with the proceedings.<ref name=\"paravasam\">{{cite web\n |author=Rajitha \n |year=2001 \n |title=Review:Parthale Paravasam \n |publisher=[[Rediff]] \n |accessdate=4 December 2001 \n |url=http://in.rediff.com/movies/2001/dec/04paar.htm \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20031117105747/http://in.rediff.com/movies/2001/dec/04paar.htm \n |archivedate=17 November 2003 \n}}</ref> Similarly his first lead role in a Hindi film, ''[[Rehna Hai Tere Dil Mein]]'' (2001), a remake of his ''Minnale'', was also unsuccessful at the box office, with the film and Madhavan's performance receiving mixed reviews.<ref name=\"rhtdmreview\">{{cite web\n |author=Adarsh, Taran \n |year=2001 \n |title=Rehna Hai Tere Dil Mein \n |publisher=[[Bollywood Hungama]] \n |accessdate=19 February 2011 \n |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/review/6838/index.html \n |authorlink=Taran Adarsh \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110922062043/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/review/6838/index.html \n |archivedate=22 September 2011 \n}}</ref> However, the film belatedly gained popularity through screenings on television and subsequently developed a cult following amongst young audiences.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pinkvilla.com/entertainment/discussion/bollywoods-cult-classics |title=Bollywood's Cult Classics |work=PINKVILLA |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160203022640/http://www.pinkvilla.com/entertainment/discussion/bollywoods-cult-classics |archivedate= 3 February 2016 }}</ref>\n\nIn 2002, Madhavan played the role of a novelist in Mani Ratnam's ''[[Kannathil Muthamittal]]'' alongside actresses [[P. S. Keerthana|Keerthana]], [[Simran (actress)|Simran]] and [[Nandita Das]]. In the film, he was shown as the role of the father of an adopted child, who wishes to return to her native homeland amidst the [[Sri Lankan civil war]]. The film received widespread critical acclaim and went on to win six [[National Film Awards|National Awards]] as well as over ten awards at various International Film Festivals.<ref name=\"km\">{{cite web\n |author=Rajitha \n |year=2002 \n |title=Review:Kannathil Muthamittal \n |publisher=[[Rediff]] \n |accessdate=16 February 2002 \n |url=http://in.rediff.com/movies/2002/feb/16kan.htm \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110604021138/http://in.rediff.com/movies/2002/feb/16kan.htm \n |archivedate= 4 June 2011 \n}}</ref> Madhavan gained acclaim for his portrayal with a critic citing \"he lived the role of the character he portrays\", with the film seeing him move away from the romantic hero image for the first time into a more serious, performance-orientated role. The good performance of the film internationally also helped him develop an overseas market for his films.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/mp/2002/09/23/stories/2002092301070300.htm |title=The Hindu : Mad about 'Maddy' |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20031102055404/http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/mp/2002/09/23/stories/2002092301070300.htm |archivedate= 2 November 2003 |newspaper=The Hindu |date=23 September 2002 }}</ref><ref name=\"kmreview\">{{cite web|author=Pearl, Tulika |year=2002 |title=Delicate flower caught in a storm |publisher=[[Rediff]] |accessdate=19 February 2011 |url=http://in.rediff.com/movies/2002/feb/16kan.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110604021138/http://in.rediff.com/movies/2002/feb/16kan.htm |archivedate= 4 June 2011 }}</ref> Madhavan's next large success came with ''[[Run (2002 film)|Run]]'', a film recognised for its screenplay, with Madhavan appearing in an action film for the first time in his career.<ref name=\"run\">{{cite news\n |year=2002 \n |title=Who's in the race? \n |newspaper=[[The Hindu]] \n |accessdate=25 November 2002 \n |url=http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/mp/2002/11/25/stories/2002112500090201.htm \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20031104035839/http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/mp/2002/11/25/stories/2002112500090201.htm \n |archivedate= 4 November 2003 \n}}</ref> In regard to his performance, [[The Hindu]]'s critic noted \"he manages to portray action with \u00e9lan in ''Run'' and actually looks fit and comfortable in the role\", with the film helping him make a breakthrough as an [[action hero]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/fr/2002/09/13/stories/2002091300930200.htm |title=The Hindu : Run |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080225193205/http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/fr/2002/09/13/stories/2002091300930200.htm |archivedate=25 February 2008 |newspaper=The Hindu |date=13 September 2002 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/fr/2003/01/10/stories/2003011001190300.htm |title=The Hindu : It is the package that ultimately matters |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20041117184728/http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/fr/2003/01/10/stories/2003011001190300.htm |archivedate=17 November 2004 |newspaper=The Hindu |date=10 January 2003 }}</ref> Despite another unsuccessful Hindi venture with the musical, ''[[Dil Vil Pyar Vyar]]'' (2002), the success of his previous films helped him secure the [[Tamil Nadu State Film Award for Best Actor]] for 2002, being jointly recognised for both films.<ref name=\"awardstwo\">{{cite web|year=2004 |title=Tamil Nadu announces film awards for three years |publisher=Indiaglitz.com |accessdate=19 February 2011 |url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/10733.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20041024060415/http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/10733.html |archivedate=24 October 2004 }}</ref>\n\nMadhavan was cast alongside [[Kamal Haasan]] in ''[[Anbe Sivam]]'' (2003), which told the story of an unexpected journey from [[Bhubaneswar]] to [[Chennai]] of two men who are polar opposites. Madhavan revealed his elation at working with an experienced actor like Kamal Haasan, while noting that a human drama film like ''Anbe Sivam'' was important for his career as an actor as it came after a successful [[masala (film genre)|masala]] film in ''Run''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rediff.com/entertai/2002/apr/24priyan.htm |title=Movies: No regrets, No remakes: Priyadarshan |publisher=Rediff |date=24 April 2002 |accessdate=11 June 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160325133257/http://www.rediff.com/entertai/2002/apr/24priyan.htm |archivedate=25 March 2016 }}</ref> Portraying a young frustrated filmmaker with capitalist beliefs who travels with a handicapped communist played by Kamal Haasan, Madhavan's performance was described as a \"milestone in his career\" and that \"his portrayal will remain with the viewer for long\" by a critic from [[The Hindu]].<ref name=\"sivamhin\">{{cite news\n |author=Rangarajan, Malathi \n |year=2003 \n |title=Anbe Sivam \n |newspaper=[[The Hindu]] \n |accessdate=19 February 2011 \n |url=http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/fr/2003/01/17/stories/2003011701310200.htm \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110405073533/http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/fr/2003/01/17/stories/2003011701310200.htm \n |archivedate= 5 April 2011 \n}}</ref> The film opened in January 2003 to positive reviews, but became a surprise box-office failure. Post-release, the film has garnered belated critical acclaim from critics and television audiences and is considered as one of the \"cult classics\" of Tamil cinema.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://behindwoods.com/tamil-movies/slideshow/top-20-cult-movies-of-the-millennium/anbe-sivam.html |title=Anbe Sivam \u2013 TOP 20 CULT MOVIES OF THE MILLENNIUM |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160328062759/http://behindwoods.com/tamil-movies/slideshow/top-20-cult-movies-of-the-millennium/anbe-sivam.html |archivedate=28 March 2016 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-articles/Time-to-re-release-Kamals-classics-29-08-12.html |title=Time To Re Release Kamals Classics |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160328055858/http://behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-articles/Time-to-re-release-Kamals-classics-29-08-12.html |archivedate=28 March 2016 }}</ref> Film critic [[Baradwaj Rangan]] wrote that the film \"was leagues ahead of the average Tamil and Indian film\", though felt that \"the masses were unwilling to accept the experimental nature of the film\", while talking about the film's box office failure.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://baradwajrangan.wordpress.com/2003/03/02/anbe-sivam/ |title=Anbe Sivam |work=Baradwaj Rangan |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160313135826/https://baradwajrangan.wordpress.com/2003/03/02/anbe-sivam/ |archivedate=13 March 2016 |date=2 March 2003 }}</ref><ref name=\"sivam\">{{cite web|author=P. Devarajan |year=2004 |title=The World of Movies |work=[[The Hindu]] |accessdate=11 July 2004 |url=http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/2004/07/14/stories/2004071400272000.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160328061025/http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/2004/07/14/stories/2004071400272000.htm |archivedate=28 March 2016 }}</ref> Post-filming, Kamal Haasan revealed that he was impressed with Madhavan's enthusiasm and concentration during the making of the film and thus subsequently signed him on to appear in his production venture, ''[[Nala Damayanthi (2003 film)|Nala Damayanthi]]'' (2003), where he played a [[Brahmin]] cook lost in Australia. In 2003, the actor also appeared in [[Vikraman]]'s family drama ''[[Priyamana Thozhi]]'' as a budding [[cricketer]], [[Saran (director)|Saran]]'s romantic comedy ''[[Jay Jay]]'' and made a guest appearance in [[Priyadarshan]]'s ''[[Lesa Lesa]]'' as a jailed teacher. The three films made average returns at the box office, though Madhavan's performances were appreciated by critics.<ref name=\"twoflops\">{{cite web|author=Warrior, Sohbha |year=2003 |title=Target Dhanush! |publisher=[[Rediff]] |accessdate=6 August 2003 |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2003/aug/06kadhal.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20030815035836/http://www.rediff.com/movies/2003/aug/06kadhal.htm |archivedate=15 August 2003 }}</ref><ref name=\"ndreview\">{{cite web\n |year=2003 \n |title=Nala Damayanthi \n |publisher=[[Sify]] \n |accessdate=19 February 2011 \n |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/tamil/review.php?id=13169606&ctid=5&cid=2429 \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121019153936/http://www.sify.com/movies/tamil/review.php?id=13169606&ctid=5&cid=2429 \n |archivedate=19 October 2012 \n}}</ref><ref name=\"jjreview\">{{cite news|author=Rangarajan, Malathi |year=2003 |title=Jay Jay |newspaper=[[The Hindu]] |accessdate=19 February 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/fr/2003/11/21/stories/2003112101090200.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120813043357/http://www.hindu.com/fr/2003/11/21/stories/2003112101090200.htm |archivedate=13 August 2012 }}</ref>\n\n===2004\u20132008===\nMadhavan played an imposter gangster in [[K. S. Ravikumar]]'s comedy ''[[Aethiree]]'' (2004) before being selected to feature in his fourth Mani Ratnam production, ''[[Aaytha Ezhuthu]]'' (2004), which featured him in an ensemble cast including [[Suriya]], [[Siddharth (actor)|Siddharth]], [[Meera Jasmine]], [[Esha Deol]] and [[Trisha (actress)|Trisha]]. Madhavan portrayed the character of Inba Sekhar, a hitman living in the slums of [[Chennai]], whose path crosses with the characters portrayed by Suriya and Siddharth. His role also featured him in a struggling marriage, where his wife desperately tries to claw him away from his profession. Madhavan bulked up and sported a shaven look for the first time in his career to resemble the character of a ruffian and shot for the film through the sync sound technique.<ref name=\"aayutha\">{{cite web\n |author=Indiaglitz \n |year=2004 \n |title=Chat with Surya and Madhavan on Ayudha Ezhuthu \n |publisher=Indiaglitz.com \n |accessdate=8 July 2004 \n |url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/interview/6078.html \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20041024114852/http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/interview/6078.html \n |archivedate=24 October 2004 \n}}</ref> He received widespread praise for his depiction, with Baradwaj Rangan of The Hindu claiming that Madhavan outplayed [[Abhishek Bachchan]]'s interpretation of the character in the Hindi version of the bilingual, ''[[Yuva]]''.<ref name=\"ezhuthu\">{{cite web|author=Rangan, Baradwaj |year=2004 |title=Aayutha Ezhuthu / Yuva |work=[[The Hindu]] |accessdate=24 May 2004 |url=http://www.spicevienna.org/showMovieReviews.php?m=1967 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070927213534/http://www.spicevienna.org/showMovieReviews.php?m=1967 |archivedate=27 September 2007 }}</ref> Madhavan went on to win the [[Filmfare Best Supporting Actor Award (Tamil)|Filmfare Award for the Best Tamil Supporting Actor]], whilst another critic from The Hindu cited that he \"sparkles as an anti-hero\" and that the \"character ought to find a very special place in his repertoire\".<ref name=\"aereview\">{{cite news\n |author=Rangarajan, Malathi \n |year=2004 \n |title=Aayudha Ezhuthu \n |newspaper=[[The Hindu]] \n |accessdate=19 February 2011 \n |url=http://www.hindu.com/fr/2004/05/28/stories/2004052801670300.htm \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060117100941/http://www.hindu.com/fr/2004/05/28/stories/2004052801670300.htm \n |archivedate=17 January 2006 \n}}</ref> Similarly, a critic from Indiaglitz.com stated \"Madhavan's daring decision to play a negative character, who gets beaten up black and blue at the end, putting his 'hero' image in peril, has paid off, as he walks away with top honours\", while a reviewer from Sify.com labelled him as \"terrific\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/aayitha-ezhuthu-review-tamil-pclv3nffafibh.html |title=Review : Aayitha Ezhuthu |work=Sify |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170309065210/http://www.sify.com/movies/aayitha-ezhuthu-review-tamil-pclv3nffafibh.html |archivedate= 9 March 2017 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/ayutha-ezhuthu-tamil-movie-review-7034.html |title=Ayutha Ezhuthu review. Ayutha Ezhuthu Tamil movie review, story, rating |work=IndiaGlitz |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151212182602/http://www.indiaglitz.com/ayutha-ezhuthu-tamil-movie-review-7034.html |archivedate=12 December 2015 }}</ref> In late 2004, Madhavan worked on [[Rajiv Anchal]]'s English-Malayalam crossover film ''[[Nothing But Life]]'' (2005) and completed his work in a single schedule across [[Las Vegas Valley|Las Vegas]] and [[Albuquerque]]. Portraying an orphaned youth with suicidal tendencies being treated by a Malayali psychiatrist in the USA, the film and his portrayal opened to mixed reviews.<ref name=\"top10review\">{{cite web\n |author=George, Sanu \n |year=2004 \n |title=Nothing but Life \n |publisher=Nowrunning.com \n |accessdate=19 February 2011 \n |url=http://www.nowrunning.com/movie/2234/malayalam/made-in-usa/484/review.htm \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110714203554/http://www.nowrunning.com/movie/2234/malayalam/made-in-usa/484/review.htm \n |archivedate=14 July 2011 \n}}</ref><ref name=\"innbl\">{{cite web\n |year=2005 \n |title=Made in USA \u2013 Leaves audiences confused \n |publisher=Indiaglitz.com \n |accessdate=19 February 2011 \n |url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/malayalam/review/7594.html \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110613235027/http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/malayalam/review/7594.html \n |archivedate=13 June 2011 \n}}</ref> He then appeared in another marriage drama film, ''[[Priyasakhi]]'' (2005) co-starring [[Sadha]] \u2013 with the pair playing an estranged husband and wife. The film received praise for the lead pair's performances with Madhavan being praised as \"top class\", while it also became the first [[Tamil language|Tamil]] film to be dubbed into [[Zulu language|Zulu]].<ref name=\"zulu\">{{cite news\n |author=Rajendran Govinder \n |title=Promoting South Africa for film shooting \n |work=[[The Hindu]] \n |accessdate=1 January 2006 \n |url=http://www.hindu.com/2006/01/01/stories/2006010114930200.htm \n |location=Chennai, India \n |date=1 January 2006 |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060304023046/http://www.hindu.com/2006/01/01/stories/2006010114930200.htm \n |archivedate= 4 March 2006 \n}}</ref><ref name=\"psreview\">{{cite web\n |year=2005 \n |title=Priyasakhi \n |publisher=[[Sify]] \n |accessdate=19 February 2011 \n |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/tamil/review.php?id=13901321&ctid=5&cid=2429 \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121019154027/http://www.sify.com/movies/tamil/review.php?id=13901321&ctid=5&cid=2429 \n |archivedate=19 October 2012 \n}}</ref>\n\nFrom 2005 onwards, Madhavan increased his work in Hindi films and starred and wrote the Hindi dialogues for the comedy ''[[Ramji Londonwaley]]'' (2005), a remake of his earlier film ''Nala Damayanthi''. Critics described his performance as \"a master stroke\", though the film fared averagely at the box office due to the release of other big budget films during the period.<ref name=\"rlreview\">{{cite web\n |author=Adarsh, Taran \n |year=2005 \n |title=Ramji Londonwaley \n |publisher=[[Bollywood Hungama]] \n |accessdate=19 February 2011 \n |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/review/12464/index.html \n |authorlink=Taran Adarsh \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100628191520/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/review/12464/index.html \n |archivedate=28 June 2010 \n}}</ref> He experienced box office success in Hindi films for the first time through his role in [[Rakeysh Omprakash Mehra]]'s ''[[Rang De Basanti]]'' (2006). Featuring in an ensemble cast led by [[Aamir Khan]], Madhavan essayed the guest role of [[flight lieutenant]], whose death triggers a revolutionary movement against corruption.<ref name=\"cadet\"/> The film was subsequently nominated for the [[BAFTA Award for Best Foreign Film|Best Foreign Language Film]] at the 2006 [[British Academy of Film and Television Arts|BAFTA Awards]], while it was also chosen as India's official entry for the [[Golden Globe Award]]s and the [[List of submissions to the 79th Academy Awards for Best Foreign Language Film|Academy Awards]] for the Best Foreign Language Film category. Madhavan then collaborated with Mani Ratnam for the fifth time in the biopic ''[[Guru (2007 film)|Guru]]'' (2007), co-starring [[Abhishek Bachchan]], [[Aishwarya Rai]] and [[Vidya Balan]]. His role of Shyam Saxena was inspired from the life of real-life journalist [[S. Gurumurthy]], who was a challenger to the business tycoon, [[Dhirubhai Ambani]], whose life drew allusions with Bachchan's role. The film became a blockbuster and also received critical acclaim, with a reviewer citing that Madhavan acts with \"extreme, believable sincerity\" dubbing him as \"truly a poster boy for India\", whilst another claimed he performed \"a weak role with \u00e9lan\".<ref name=\"gurureview\">{{cite web\n |author=Adarsh, Taran \n |year=2007 \n |title=Guru \n |publisher=[[Bollywood Hungama]] \n |accessdate=19 February 2011 \n |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/review/12838/index.html \n |authorlink=Taran Adarsh \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110528115018/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/review/12838/index.html \n |archivedate=28 May 2011 \n}}</ref><ref name=\"gurureviewsen\">{{cite web|author=Sen, Raja |year=2007 |title=Watch Guru for the actors |publisher=[[Rediff]] |accessdate=19 February 2011 |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2007/jan/12guru.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110123022904/http://www.rediff.com/movies/2007/jan/12guru.htm |archivedate=23 January 2011 }}</ref>\n\nHis Tamil film, ''[[Thambi (2006 film)|Thambi]]'' (2006) directed by [[Seeman (director)|Seeman]], had a delayed release but became a profitable venture in town and village centres.<ref name=\"thambirediff\">{{cite web\n |author=Shobha Warrior \n |year=2006 \n |title=I never sign a film for acceptance \n |publisher=[[Rediff]] \n |accessdate=21 November 2006 \n |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2006/nov/21madhavan.htm \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20061208202346/http://www.rediff.com/movies/2006/nov/21madhavan.htm \n |archivedate= 8 December 2006 \n}}</ref> Madhavan's portrayal of a rustic do-gooder, received positive reviews from critics though a reviewer from The Hindu claimed the actor was \"unable to shed off his classy looks\".<ref name=\"thambibad\">{{cite web\n |author=Malathi Ranganathan \n |year=2006 \n |title=The agenda is new \n |work=[[The Hindu]] \n |accessdate=24 February 2006 \n |url=http://hindujobs.com/thehindu/fr/2006/02/24/stories/2006022400240200.htm \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070926233843/http://hindujobs.com/thehindu/fr/2006/02/24/stories/2006022400240200.htm \n |archivedate=26 September 2007 \n}}</ref><ref name=\"thambigood\">{{cite web \n |author=AllIndianSite \n |year=2006 \n |title=Movie:Thambi \n |publisher=AllIndianSite \n |accessdate=22 February 2006 \n |url=http://kollywood.allindiansite.com/thambi.html \n |url-status=dead \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060409043301/http://kollywood.allindiansite.com/thambi.html \n |archivedate=9 April 2006 \n }}</ref> He then appeared in [[Sundar C]]'s comedy film ''[[Rendu]]'' (2006), where he played dual roles for the first time and in the long-delayed romantic comedy ''[[Arya (2007 film)|Aarya]]'' (2007), appearing as a medical student.<ref name=\"aryareview\">{{cite web|year=2007 |title=Arya Movie Review |publisher=Behindwoods |accessdate=19 February 2011 |url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-articles/movies-06/arya-review.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110504050217/http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-articles/movies-06/arya-review.html |archivedate= 4 May 2011 }}</ref> Madhavan wrote the dialogues, produced and featured in the lead role in [[Nishikanth Kamat]]'s ''[[Evano Oruvan]]'' (2007), playing a middle class bank employee who becomes so disgusted with the corruption he faces in his day-to-day life that he becomes a vigilante. After setting up a production studio, Leukos Films, he helped promote the film in international film festivals{{which|date=January 2020}} before the theatrical release in December 2007.<ref name=\"eoprom\">{{cite news|title=Madhavan's \"Evano Oruvan\" to be screened in America, Middle East |work=[[The Hindu]] |accessdate=19 February 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/holnus/009200710041878.htm |location=Chennai, India |date=4 October 2007 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110629024839/http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/holnus/009200710041878.htm |archivedate=29 June 2011 }}</ref><ref name=\"eopromtwo\">{{cite news|author=Malarvizhi, J. |title='Evano Oruvan' to premiere abroad |work=[[The Hindu]] |accessdate=19 February 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/2007/10/06/stories/2007100650060200.htm |location=Chennai, India |date=6 October 2007 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110109121111/http://www.hindu.com/2007/10/06/stories/2007100650060200.htm |archivedate= 9 January 2011 }}</ref> Critics called the film a \"must watch\" and a reviewer from [[The Hindu]] stated that the film was \"Madhavan's best performance to date\", while he also went on to win the [[ITFA Best Actor Award]] for his depiction.<ref name=\"eoreviews\">{{cite news|author=Kamath, Sudhish |title=Maddy vs Baddies |work=[[The Hindu]] |accessdate=15 December 2007 |url=http://www.hindu.com/mp/2007/12/15/stories/2007121550330300.htm |location=Chennai,India |date=15 December 2007 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071223093245/http://www.hindu.com/mp/2007/12/15/stories/2007121550330300.htm |archivedate=23 December 2007 }}</ref><ref name=\"eoreview2\">{{cite web|author=Srinivasan, Pavithra |year=2007 |title=Evano Oruvan, a must-watch |publisher=[[Rediff]] |accessdate=15 December 2007 |url=http://inhome.rediff.com/movies/2007/dec/07evan.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071209182848/http://inhome.rediff.com/movies/2007/dec/07evan.htm |archivedate= 9 December 2007 }}</ref> However ''Evano Oruvan'' and his subsequent release, Seeman's ''[[Vaazhthukal]]'' (2008) did not perform well at the box office, while another completed film titled ''[[Naan Aval Adhu]]'' failed to have a theatrical release.<ref name=\"vrreview2\">{{cite web|year=2007 |title=Vaazhthukkal Review |publisher=Behindwoods |accessdate=20 February 2011 |url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-reviews/reviews-1/vazhthukal-review.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110707222741/http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-reviews/reviews-1/vazhthukal-review.html |archivedate= 7 July 2011 }}</ref> Madhavan's final release of the year was the docudrama ''[[Mumbai Meri Jaan]]'', based upon the [[2006 Mumbai Bombings]]. The film, which featured him alongside [[Soha Ali Khan]], [[Irrfan Khan]] and [[Kay Kay Menon]] became critically acclaimed with Madhavan's portrayal of a man with a post-traumatic stress disorder being appreciated by reviewers.<ref name=\"mmjreview2\">{{cite web|author=Ramani, Nithya |year=2008 |title=Agony revisited |publisher=[[Rediff]] |accessdate=20 February 2011 |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2008/aug/22mumbai.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110315092123/http://www.rediff.com/movies/2008/aug/22mumbai.htm |archivedate=15 March 2011 }}</ref><ref name=\"mmjreview\">{{cite web\n |author=Adarsh, Taran \n |year=2008 \n |title=Mumbai Meri Jaan \n |publisher=[[Bollywood Hungama]] \n |accessdate=19 February 2011 \n |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/review/13809/index.html \n |authorlink=Taran Adarsh \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100920103054/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/review/13809/index.html \n |archivedate=20 September 2010 \n}}</ref>\n\n===2009\u20132014===\n[[File:Kangna Ranaut and R Madhavan promote 'Tanu Weds Manu' on Jhalak Dikhhla Jaa sets.jpg|thumb|right|upright=0.9|alt=Kangana Ranaut and R. Madhavan pose for the camera|Madhavan with co-star [[Kangana Ranaut]] at a promotional event for ''[[Tanu Weds Manu]]'', 2011]] \nMadhavan won positive acclaim for playing the lead role of an engineer experiencing eerie events in Vikram Kumar's bilingual horror film, ''[[Yavarum Nalam]]'' (2009). The film, which became a commercial and critical success, prompted a reviewer from the [[Times of India]] to suggest \"he carried the film on his shoulders\" while he was also nominated in the [[Vijay Award for Best Actor|Best Actor]] category at the [[Vijay Awards]].<ref name=\"ynreviews\">{{cite news\n |author=Bhama, Deva Ravi \n |year=2009 \n |title=Yavarum Nalam \n |work=[[The Times of India]] \n |accessdate=6 March 2009 \n |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/Tamil/Yavarum-nalam/articleshow/4234468.cms \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090310141129/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/Tamil/Yavarum-nalam/articleshow/4234468.cms \n |archivedate=10 March 2009 \n}}</ref> His following two films, the romantic comedy ''[[Guru En Aalu]]'' (2009) and the action film ''[[Sikandar (2009 film)|Sikandar]]'' (2009) in which he played a supporting role of an army officer, both fetched mixed reviews. Madhavan then portrayed one of three leading roles in [[Rajkumar Hirani]]'s [[coming of age film|coming of age]] [[comedy film|comedy]]-[[Drama (film and television)|drama film]], ''[[3 Idiots]]'' (2009), alongside [[Aamir Khan]] and [[Sharman Joshi]]. Upon release, the film received positive reviews and went on to become the highest-grossing Indian film of all time, before being overtaken in 2013.<ref name=overseas>{{cite web|title=Three Idiots Creates History in China |url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/boxnewsdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=3866&nCat= |work=30 December 2011 |publisher=BoxOfficeIndia. Com |accessdate=30 December 2011 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120107201817/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/boxnewsdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=3866&nCat= |archivedate= 7 January 2012 }}</ref> Madhavan's portrayal as a young engineer with a passion for photography earned him nominations for the [[Filmfare Award for Best Supporting Actor]] and for the [[IIFA Best Supporting Actor Award]] during 2010. Film critic [[Taran Adarsh]] from [[Bollywood Hungama]] described the actor's performance as \"incredible\", while Madhavan claimed that the film changed how he was viewed as an actor in Hindi films for the better.<ref name=\"tireview\">{{cite web|author=Adarsh, Taran |year=2009 |title=3 Idiots |publisher=[[Bollywood Hungama]] |accessdate=19 February 2011 |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/review/13910/index.html |authorlink=Taran Adarsh |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101104160008/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/review/13910/index.html |archivedate= 4 November 2010 }}</ref><ref name=\"ticahneg\">{{cite web|author=Ashraf, Syed |year=2010 |title=How 3 Idiots changed Madhavan's life |publisher=[[Rediff]] |accessdate=19 February 2011 |url=http://movies.rediff.com/slide-show/2010/jan/11/slide-show-1-madhavan-on-three-idiots.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110415133429/http://movies.rediff.com/slide-show/2010/jan/11/slide-show-1-madhavan-on-three-idiots.htm |archivedate=15 April 2011 }}</ref> He later turned down an offer of reprising the same role in the Tamil remake of the film helmed by [[S. Shankar|Shankar]]. In 2010, Madhavan appeared alongside actors [[Amitabh Bachchan]] and [[Ben Kingsley]] in ''[[Teen Patti (film)|Teen Patti]]'' (2010) as a young professor, with Adarsh again rating his performance as \"excellent\", but the film failed at the box office.<ref name=\"tpreview\">{{cite web\n |author=Adarsh, Taran \n |year=2010 \n |title=Teen Patti \n |publisher=[[Bollywood Hungama]] \n |accessdate=19 February 2011 \n |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/review/12995/index.html \n |authorlink=Taran Adarsh \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101230230731/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/review/12995/index.html \n |archivedate=30 December 2010 \n}}</ref><ref name=\"tpred\">{{cite web\n |author=Arora, Preeti \n |year=2010 \n |title=Teen Patti: Just one big bluff \n |publisher=[[Rediff]] \n |accessdate=19 February 2011 \n |url=http://movies.rediff.com/report/2010/feb/26/review-teen-patti.htm \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110430185119/http://movies.rediff.com/report/2010/feb/26/review-teen-patti.htm \n |archivedate=30 April 2011 \n}}</ref> His two guest appearances in the year also received mixed feedback with his performance in the Telugu anthology film ''[[Om Shanti]]'' (2010) being praised, whilst a role in the [[John Abraham (actor)|John Abraham]]-starrer ''[[Jhootha Hi Sahi]]'' (2010) drew him criticism.<ref name=\"jhsreview\">{{cite web\n |author=Adarsh, Taran \n |year=2010 \n |title=Jhootha Hi Sahi \n |publisher=[[Bollywood Hungama]] \n |accessdate=19 February 2011 \n |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/review/14072/index.html \n |authorlink=Taran Adarsh \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110223234544/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/review/14072/index.html \n |archivedate=23 February 2011 \n}}</ref><ref name=\"osid\">{{cite web\n |author=Jeevi \n |year=2010 \n |title=Om Shanti Film Review \n |publisher=Idlebrain.com \n |accessdate=19 February 2011 \n |url=http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/archive/mr-omshanti.html \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110713002932/http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/archive/mr-omshanti.html \n |archivedate=13 July 2011 \n}}</ref> Madhavan then collaborated again with [[Kamal Haasan]] and [[K. S. Ravikumar]] in the romantic comedy, ''[[Manmadan Ambu]]'' (2010), playing a wealthy businessman who hires a spy to follow his actress girlfriend on a European cruise tour. The film opened to positive reviews with Madhavan's performance being described by [[Rediff]].com as \"excellent\", while [[Sify]].com labelled him the \"scene stealer\".<ref name=\"mmareview\">{{cite web\n |year=2010 \n |title=Manmadan Ambu \n |publisher=[[Sify]] \n |accessdate=19 February 2011 \n |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/tamil/review.php?id=14959566&ctid=5&cid=2429 \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110121202419/http://www.sify.com/movies/tamil/review.php?id=14959566&ctid=5&cid=2429 \n |archivedate=21 January 2011 \n}}</ref><ref name=\"rediffmmaed\">{{cite web\n |author=Srinivasan, Pavithra \n |year=2010 \n |title=Kamal Haasan delivers with Manmadhan Ambu \n |publisher=[[Rediff]] \n |accessdate=19 February 2011 \n |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/review/south-review-of-manmadhan-ambu/20101223.htm \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110208035731/http://www.rediff.com/movies/review/south-review-of-manmadhan-ambu/20101223.htm \n |archivedate= 8 February 2011 \n}}</ref>\n\nHis only release in 2011 was the romantic drama film, ''[[Tanu Weds Manu]]'' alongside [[Kangana Ranaut]], which saw him play the role of a sensible doctor hoping to get an arranged marriage with a girl, who has a dramatically diverse personality to him. Prior to release, the film's promotional campaign created anticipation and upon release, the film became a large success at the box office. Madhavan's portrayal of Manoj \"Manu\" Sharma won positive acclaim, with a reviewer citing that his performance was \"real, restrained, yet forceful\" and another claiming he was \"perfectly cast\".<ref name=\"twmreview\">{{cite web\n |author=Adarsh, Taran \n |year=2011 \n |title=Tanu Weds Manu \n |publisher=[[Bollywood Hungama]] \n |accessdate=19 February 2011 \n |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/review/14135/index.html \n |authorlink=Taran Adarsh \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110228024645/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/review/14135/index.html \n |archivedate=28 February 2011 \n}}</ref><ref name=\"redifftwm\">{{cite web|author=Verma, Sukanya |year=2011 |title=Review: Tanu Weds Manu is charming |publisher=[[Rediff]] |accessdate=19 February 2011 |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/review/review-tanu-weds-manu/20110225.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110227134744/http://www.rediff.com/movies/review/review-tanu-weds-manu/20110225.htm |archivedate=27 February 2011 }}</ref> Madhavan next appeared as a police officer in [[N. Linguswamy|Linguswamy]]'s Tamil film ''[[Vettai]]'' (2012), an action entertainer featuring an ensemble cast of [[Arya (actor)|Arya]], [[Amala Paul]] and [[Sameera Reddy]]. The film opened to positive reviews in January 2012 and went on to become a commercial success, with critics praising Madhavan's decision to accept the role of a timid cop, while a critic noted that he had \"an uncanny talent for comedy\".<ref name=\"adhir\">{{cite news\n |title=Vettai: Review \n |work=[[The Times of India]] \n |accessdate=13 July 2012 \n |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/articlelist/movie-review/11496445.cms \n |date=19 October 2010 |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120120012238/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/articlelist/movie-review/11496445.cms \n |archivedate=20 January 2012 \n}}</ref><ref name=\"vettai\">{{cite news\n |author=Dutt, Purbha \n |title=Vettai's story blew me away:Madhavan \n |work=[[The Times of India]] \n |accessdate=19 February 2011 \n |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/regional/news-interviews/Vettais-story-blew-me-away-Madhavan/articleshow/6741515.cms \n |date=14 October 2010 |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101023065238/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/regional/news-interviews/Vettais-story-blew-me-away-Madhavan/articleshow/6741515.cms \n |archivedate=23 October 2010 \n}}</ref> He then featured in ''[[Jodi Breakers]]'' (2012), a Hindi romantic comedy film shot in [[Greece]] alongside [[Bipasha Basu]], though the film did not perform well commercially.<ref name=\"sff\">{{cite web | url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/channels/showbiz/bollywood/bipasha-and-madhavan-romance-greece-645 | title=Bipasha and Madhavan to romance in Greece | work=[[Deccan Chronicle]] | date=10 August 2011 | accessdate=19 February 2011 | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121011171507/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/channels/showbiz/bollywood/bipasha-and-madhavan-romance-greece-645 | archivedate=11 October 2012}}</ref> In 2012, Madhavan took a sabbatical and was based in Chicago resting his knee, which he injured during the making of ''Vettai'', causing him to suffer from [[chondromalacia patellae]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Madhavan heads to Chicago for rest! |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/madhavan-heads-to-chicago-for-rest-news-tamil-md1nloideda.html |work=Sify |accessdate=6 August 2013 |date=27 March 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131008111433/http://www.sify.com/movies/madhavan-heads-to-chicago-for-rest-news-tamil-md1nloideda.html |archivedate= 8 October 2013 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Madhavan to take a sabbatical |url=http://archive.asianage.com/bollywood/madhavan-take-sabbatical-231 |work=[[Asian Age]] |accessdate=6 August 2013 |date=13 February 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130806050025/http://archive.asianage.com/bollywood/madhavan-take-sabbatical-231 |archivedate= 6 August 2013 }}</ref> During the period, he felt he had to \"reinvent himself\" and had to work on films which would appeal to the \"new generation of audiences\", so took a decision to work on a single film at a time.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-i-became-boring-and-fat-r-madhavan-2086435 |title=I became boring and fat: R Madhavan |date=17 May 2015 |work=dna |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160313223025/http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-i-became-boring-and-fat-r-madhavan-2086435 |archivedate=13 March 2016 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/R-Madhavan-I-realised-that-I-had-become-a-terrible-actor/articleshow/46727030.cms |title=R Madhavan: I realised that I had become a terrible actor |work=The Times of India |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150401161122/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/R-Madhavan-I-realised-that-I-had-become-a-terrible-actor/articleshow/46727030.cms |archivedate= 1 April 2015 }}</ref> During a period of three years without any theatrical releases, his long-delayed Hindi film ''[[Sunglass (film)|Taak Jhaank]]'' directed by [[Rituparno Ghosh]] in 2006, premi\u00e8red at the 19th Kolkata International Film Festival in 2013, while his first Hindi film ''[[Akeli (film)|Akeli]]'', shot in 1997, was released online during the following year. During his recovery period and sabbatical in 2013, Madhavan signed on to appear in [[Simon West]]'s ''[[Night of the Living Dead: Darkest Dawn]]'', in which he appeared as a former marine personnel and shot for the project in California.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/hollywood-ho/article5179154.ece |title=Hollywood Ho! |author=Harshikaa Udasi |newspaper=The Hindu |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140317115008/http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/hollywood-ho/article5179154.ece |archivedate=17 March 2014 |date=28 September 2013 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=R Madhavan bags a Hollywood movie|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-07-28/news-interviews/40833799_1_madhavan-film-tomb-raider|work=The Times of India|accessdate=1 August 2013|date=28 July 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130801200039/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-07-28/news-interviews/40833799_1_madhavan-film-tomb-raider|archive-date=1 August 2013|url-status=live}}</ref> The [[computer animation|computer animated]] film, where Madhavan provided voice work, premi\u00e8red in San Diego during July 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jobsnhire.com/articles/26828/20150908/night-of-the-living-dead-remake-news-cg-movie-animated-retelling-1968-george-romero-classic.htm |title='Night of the Living Dead' Remake [NEWS]: A CG Movie? Animated Retelling of the 1968 George Romero Classic Disappoints Fans |publisher=Jobsnhire.com |date=8 September 2015 |accessdate=6 January 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160106163041/http://www.jobsnhire.com/articles/26828/20150908/night-of-the-living-dead-remake-news-cg-movie-animated-retelling-1968-george-romero-classic.htm |archivedate= 6 January 2016 }}</ref>\n\n===2015\u20132017===\nMadhavan's first theatrical release after his sabbatical was [[Anand L. Rai]]'s ''[[Tanu Weds Manu Returns]]'', a sequel to the 2011 film, which released in May 2015. Prior to the film's release, Madhavan stated that the \"content of the film was more important than the stars\" and acknowledged that the popularity of [[Kangana Ranaut]] would help the film gain a good opening at the box office.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/i-will-definitely-be-overshadowed-by-kangana-ranaut-in-tanu-weds-manu-returns-madhvan/story-wl0GSjk1uqJbIf08uxHn4N.html |title=I will definitely be overshadowed by Kangana Ranaut in Tanu Weds Manu Returns: Madhvan |work=hindustantimes.com/ |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160224054102/http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/i-will-definitely-be-overshadowed-by-kangana-ranaut-in-tanu-weds-manu-returns-madhvan/story-wl0GSjk1uqJbIf08uxHn4N.html |archivedate=24 February 2016 |date=15 May 2015 }}</ref> Reprising his role as Manu, Madhavan won acclaim for his restrained performance and the film went on to become a critical and commercial success.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/interview/madhavan-my-character-in-tanu-weds-manu-returns-has-a-lot-of-flaws/20150601.htm |title=Madhavan: My character in Tanu Weds Manu Returns has a lot of flaws |date=1 June 2015 |work=Rediff |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160229235833/http://www.rediff.com/movies/interview/madhavan-my-character-in-tanu-weds-manu-returns-has-a-lot-of-flaws/20150601.htm |archivedate=29 February 2016 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/madhavan-interview-maddy-returns-as-manu/article7213988.ece|title=Madhavan interview: Maddy returns as Manu|author=Archita Kashyap|newspaper=The Hindu|accessdate=16 February 2016|date=16 May 2015}}</ref> The critic from [[Bollywood Hungama]] wrote \"Madhavan excels in his role despite it being a restrained one, which was anyways the call of his character\" and added \"he is very endearing who never tries to overshadow anyone and emerges a winner\", while Sify.com stated he gives a \"subtle and restrained performance\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/moviemicro/criticreview/id/547997 |title=Tanu Weds Manu Returns |author=Bollywood Hungama |date=21 May 2015 |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160214194525/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/moviemicro/criticreview/id/547997 |archivedate=14 February 2016 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/kangana-s-dual-magic-in-tanu-weds-manu-returns-review-bollywood-pfwsrrbidbhgj.html |title=Review : Kangana's dual magic in 'Tanu Weds Manu Returns' |work=Sify |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160213143245/http://www.sify.com/movies/kangana-s-dual-magic-in-tanu-weds-manu-returns-review-bollywood-pfwsrrbidbhgj.html |archivedate=13 February 2016 }}</ref> ''Tanu Weds Manu Returns'' earned {{INRConvert|2.43|b}} worldwide at the end of its theatrical run, to become one of the [[List of highest-grossing Bollywood films|highest-grossing Bollywood films]] in 2015.<ref name=\"2.40&nbsp;billion\">{{cite web|url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/Details/art_detail/willthemegasuccessofbaahubalihitbajrangibhaijaanaseveninnorthindiaitsablockbuster|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150716171244/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/Details/art_detail/willthemegasuccessofbaahubalihitbajrangibhaijaanaseveninnorthindiaitsablockbuster|archivedate=16 July 2015|title=Will The Mega Success Of Baahubali Hit Bajrangi Bhaijaan As Even in North India Its A Blockbuster?}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/Details/art_detail/tanuwedsmanureturnsheadsfor225crworldwide|title=Tanu Weds Manu Returns Heads For 225 Cr Worldwide|accessdate=2 June 2015|publisher=Box Office India|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150626133220/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/Details/art_detail/tanuwedsmanureturnsheadsfor225crworldwide|archivedate=26 June 2015}}</ref>\n\nDuring his sabbatical, Madhavan also worked extensively on the pre-production of the bilingual sports film, ''[[Irudhi Suttru]]'' (2016) directed by [[Sudha Kongara Prasad|Sudha Kongara]]. After being impressed with Sudha's script, he helped find the project producers in Tamil and chose to produce the film in Hindi alongside [[Y NOT Studios|Sashikanth]] and [[Rajkumar Hirani]]. Madhavan also met and convinced [[mixed martial arts|mixed martial artist]] Ritika Singh to act in the film after contacting her through [[Raj Kundra]], while he was also credited for contributing as an additional screenplay writer. He also went through a body conditioning regime in Los Angeles prior to joining the film's set and learnt boxing to essay the role of a former boxer.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/features/type/view/id/9665 |title=I knew that Saala Khadoos is a film that would change my image \u2013 Madhavan \u2013 Latest Movie Features \u2013 Bollywood Hungama |author=Bollywood Hungama |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160215082742/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/features/type/view/id/9665 |archivedate=15 February 2016 }}</ref> For dubbing purposes, Madhavan wore metal braces inside his teeth, to create the effect of having a lisp that most boxers have from sporting injuries.<ref name=\"nie\">{{cite web|author=Manigandan K R |url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/tamil/Get-Ready-for-Maddys-Punch-in-Irudhi-Suttru/2016/01/05/article3211513.ece |title=Get Ready for Maddy's Punch in Irudhi Suttru |work=The New Indian Express |date=5 January 2016 |accessdate=28 January 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160204102959/http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/tamil/Get-Ready-for-Maddys-Punch-in-Irudhi-Suttru/2016/01/05/article3211513.ece |archivedate= 4 February 2016 }}</ref> Madhavan won praise for his work during the marketing campaign, having travelled throughout [[Tamil Nadu]] to promote the film, with [[The Hindu]] stating it was \"unlike other film promotions in the South\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/madhavan%E2%80%99s-aggressive-promotions-for-irudhi-suttru-news-tamil-qbgkC2aijgeae.html |title=Madhavan's aggressive promotions for 'Irudhi Suttru' |publisher=Sify.com |accessdate=28 January 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160128210200/http://www.sify.com/movies/madhavan%E2%80%99s-aggressive-promotions-for-irudhi-suttru-news-tamil-qbgkC2aijgeae.html |archivedate=28 January 2016 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-metroplus/a-gentleman-and-an-actor/article8074042.ece |title=A gentleman and an actor \u2013 Madurai |work=The Hindu |date=7 January 2016 |accessdate=28 January 2016}}</ref> For ''Irudhi Suttru'', Madhavan received widespread critical acclaim for his portrayal with Sify.com stating \"he is outstanding and carries the proverbial burden of the project on his shoulder\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/irudhi-suttru-review-tamil-qb3kkffigibjj.html |title=Review : Irudhi Suttru review |publisher=Sify.com |accessdate=20 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160224002933/http://www.sify.com/movies/irudhi-suttru-review-tamil-qb3kkffigibjj.html |archivedate=24 February 2016 }}</ref> A critic from [[The Hindu]] stated that he was \"quietly effective\", while a reviewer from Behindwoods.com wrote that Madhavan gives his \"best performance\" and is \"excellent\" at depicting his \"characterization from being subtle to being outright effervescent\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies/irudhi-suttru/irudhi-suttru-review.html |title=Irudhi Suttru (aka) Iruthi Suttru review |work=Behindwoods |publisher=Behindwoods Review Board |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160222140031/http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies/irudhi-suttru/irudhi-suttru-review.html |archivedate=22 February 2016 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/cinema-reviews/irudhi-suttru-a-heartwarming-boxing-drama/article8171346.ece |title=Irudhi Suttru: A heart-warming boxing drama |author=Baradwaj Rangan |work=The Hindu |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160131084418/http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/cinema-reviews/irudhi-suttru-a-heartwarming-boxing-drama/article8171346.ece |archivedate=31 January 2016 }}</ref> His portrayal in the Hindi version, ''Saala Khadoos'', received similar praise with critic [[Subhash K. Jha]] stating \"this is Madhavan's career-defining performance, he sinks so deep into his role both physically and emotionally, that the actor becomes one with the act\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.firstpost.com/bollywood/saala-khadoos-review-madhavan-delivers-knockout-performance-in-an-ultimately-lightweight-film-2603040.html |title=Saala Khadoos review: A decent film brought to life by Madhavan's knockout performance |work=Firstpost |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160202035646/http://www.firstpost.com/bollywood/saala-khadoos-review-madhavan-delivers-knockout-performance-in-an-ultimately-lightweight-film-2603040.html |archivedate= 2 February 2016 }}</ref>\n\nHe next featured in ''[[Vikram Vedha]]'' (2017), an action thriller film directed by duo [[Pushkar-Gayathri]] and produced by [[Y NOT Studios|Sashikanth]]. Telling the tale of an encounter cop and his pursuit of a gangster played by [[Vijay Sethupathi]], Pushkar-Gayathri scripted the film with inspiration from the [[Vikramaditya|Vikramathithan Vedhalam]] folk tale, with the characterisation of both lead roles derived from that plot.<ref>{{cite web |author=Karthik Kumar |url=http://www.thequint.com/entertainment/2016/02/15/after-boxing-coach-madhavan-to-play-an-encounter-specialist |title=After Boxing Coach, Madhavan to Play an Encounter Specialist |publisher=The Quint |date=15 February 2016 |accessdate=21 November 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161117211500/https://www.thequint.com/entertainment/2016/02/15/after-boxing-coach-madhavan-to-play-an-encounter-specialist |archive-date=17 November 2016 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/Vijay-Sethupathi-Madhavans-film-is-based-on-Vikramathithan-Vethalam/articleshow/51009766.cms |title=Vijay Sethupathi, Madhavan's film is based on Vikramathithan Vethalam |website=The Times of India |date=17 February 2016 |accessdate=21 November 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170725182631/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/Vijay-Sethupathi-Madhavans-film-is-based-on-Vikramathithan-Vethalam/articleshow/51009766.cms |archive-date=25 July 2017 |url-status=live }}</ref> For his role, Madhavan underwent arms training and met people involved with the police and defence forces.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mid-day.com/articles/madhavan-i-know-23-year-old-girls-lust-after-me/16950185 |title=Madhavan: I know 23-year-old girls lust after me |website=Mid-day.com |accessdate=21 November 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161117063256/http://www.mid-day.com/articles/madhavan-i-know-23-year-old-girls-lust-after-me/16950185 |archive-date=17 November 2016 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/kollywood/160216/madhavan-to-face-off-against-vijay-sethupathi.html |title=Madhavan to face off against Vijay Sethupathi |website=Deccan Chronicle |accessdate=21 November 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161117070252/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/kollywood/160216/madhavan-to-face-off-against-vijay-sethupathi.html |archive-date=17 November 2016 |url-status=live }}</ref> ''Vikram Vedha'' opened in July 2017 to critical acclaim and received widespread positive reports from the media and industry personnel.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/kollywood-lauds-vikram-vedha-news-tamil-rhyjNhbddffbb.html |title=Kollywood lauds 'Vikram Vedha' |publisher=Sify.com |accessdate=22 January 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180115121219/http://www.sify.com/movies/kollywood-lauds-vikram-vedha-news-tamil-rhyjNhbddffbb.html |archive-date=15 January 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> Madhavan's performance was widely appreciated by film critics, who described him as \"stylish and serious\" and \"whole-hearted\", while Sify.com's reviewer wrote it is a \"treat to watch two intense performers Madhavan and Vijay Sethupathi majestically own the screen together\".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/vikram-vedha-review-a-brilliantly-written-intense-crime-drama-review-tamil-rhvoN4jfgfbcc.html |title=Review : Vikram Vedha Review: A brilliantly written intense crime (2017) |publisher=Sify.com |date=21 July 2017 |accessdate=22 January 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180607170729/http://www.sify.com/movies/vikram-vedha-review-a-brilliantly-written-intense-crime-drama-review-tamil-rhvoN4jfgfbcc.html |archive-date=7 June 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/movie-reviews/220717/vikram-vedha-movie-review-a-simplistic-and-straightforward-affair.html |title=Vikram Vedha movie review: A simplistic and straightforward affair |work=Deccan Chronicle |accessdate=22 January 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171220021402/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/movie-reviews/220717/vikram-vedha-movie-review-a-simplistic-and-straightforward-affair.html |archive-date=20 December 2017 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movie-reviews/vikram-vedha/movie-review/59697165.cms |title=Vikram Vedha Review {3.5/5}: A playful action film with more intrigue and less intensity |work=The Times of India |date=21 July 2017 |accessdate=22 January 2018}}</ref> The film also became Madhavan's biggest commercial success in Tamil films, with trade pundits classifying the film as a \"blockbuster\".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bollywoodtrade.com/trade-news/vikram-vedha-becomes-r-madhavans-biggest-tamil-blockbuster/1703.htm |title=VIKRAM VEDHA becomes R Madhavan's biggest Tamil blockbuster! \u2013 Trade News |publisher=BollywoodTrade.com |date=17 August 2017 |accessdate=22 January 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170920191323/http://www.bollywoodtrade.com/trade-news/vikram-vedha-becomes-r-madhavans-biggest-tamil-blockbuster/1703.htm |archive-date=20 September 2017 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n===2018\u2013present===\nMadhavan next worked on a web series for Amazon titled ''[[Breathe (web series)|Breathe]]'', which was released in January 2018.<ref>{{cite web |author=Back to |url=http://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/r-madhavan-very-excited-about-vikram-vedha-its-one-of-the-best-films-of-my-career-3833305.html |title=R Madhavan: 'Very excited about Vikram Vedha, it's one of the best films of my career'- Entertainment News, Firstpost |publisher=Firstpost.com |accessdate=22 January 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180125151253/http://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/r-madhavan-very-excited-about-vikram-vedha-its-one-of-the-best-films-of-my-career-3833305.html |archive-date=25 January 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/actor-madhavan-makes-digital-debut-with-amazon-primes-breathe/article22470896.ece |title=Only 2% go to theatres, says actor Madhavan |work=The Hindu |date=20 June 2017 |accessdate=22 January 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180404192819/http://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/actor-madhavan-makes-digital-debut-with-amazon-primes-breathe/article22470896.ece |archive-date=4 April 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> Madhavan later revealed that he was initially sceptical of the web series format, but was \"totally blown away\" by the script of the series by Mayank Sharma and decided to accept to work on the project, despite his commitments for the shoot of ''Vikram Vedha''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/i-keep-meeting-people-who-think-its-the-end-of-the-road-for-me-madhavan/articleshow/62672775.cms|title=I keep meeting people who think it's the end of the road for me: Madhavan|website=The Times of India|access-date=28 January 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180128100431/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/i-keep-meeting-people-who-think-its-the-end-of-the-road-for-me-madhavan/articleshow/62672775.cms|archive-date=28 January 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/actor-madhavan-makes-digital-debut-with-amazon-primes-breathe/article22470896.ece|title=Only 2% go to theatres, says actor Madhavan|first=Vishal|last=Menon|date=19 January 2018|work=The Hindu|access-date=31 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180404192819/http://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/actor-madhavan-makes-digital-debut-with-amazon-primes-breathe/article22470896.ece|archive-date=4 April 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> For ''Breathe'', Madhavan studied his own experience as a father besides researching the complexities surrounding [[organ donation]]. In the series, he played Danny Mascarenhas, a soccer coach and the father of a young boy with cystic fibrosis, who will die in six months unless he has a lung transplant.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/arts/television/why-amazon-is-betting-on-indian-superstar-r-madhavan/article37732987/|title=Why Amazon is betting on Indian superstar R. Madhavan with its series Breathe|work=The Globe and Mail|access-date=28 January 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180128091858/https://www.theglobeandmail.com/arts/television/why-amazon-is-betting-on-indian-superstar-r-madhavan/article37732987/|archive-date=28 January 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Madhavan received positive reviews for his portrayal, with film critic [[Subhash K. Jha]] writing \"As Danny, Madhavan expresses grief, rage, frustration, guilt, repentance and self-destruction with measured excellence\" and that \"this is a showcase for an actor at the peak of his power\" and \"boy, does Madhavan embrace the opportunity\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://indianewengland.com/2018/01/review-breathe-amazon-gives-us-thriller-series-wont-let-us-breathe/|title=Review: Breathe: Amazon gives us a thriller series that won't let us breathe|date=27 January 2018|access-date=31 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190831091436/https://indianewengland.com/2018/01/review-breathe-amazon-gives-us-thriller-series-wont-let-us-breathe/|archive-date=31 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Similarly, a critic from the New Indian Express wrote \"Madhavan is in form in a potentially compelling thriller\", and a reviewer from the International Business Times wrote he \"shows a range of emotions\" in \"a smooth, beautiful way\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/web-series/madhavan-breathe-review-5039957/|title=Breathe first impression: Madhavan is in form in a potentially compelling thriller|date=26 January 2018|access-date=31 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190831091433/https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/web-series/madhavan-breathe-review-5039957/|archive-date=31 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/breathe-review-r-madhavan-amit-sadhs-brilliant-gripping-psychological-thriller-will-leave-you-758394|title=Breathe Review: R Madhavan, Amit Sadh's brilliant and gripping psychological thriller will leave you breathless|first=Chetna|last=Kapoor|date=26 January 2018|website=International Business Times, India Edition|access-date=31 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190831091432/https://www.ibtimes.co.in/breathe-review-r-madhavan-amit-sadhs-brilliant-gripping-psychological-thriller-will-leave-you-758394|archive-date=31 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nMadhavan's most recent release is ''[[Savyasachi (2018 film)|Savyasachi]]'' (2018), where he played his first full-length role in a Telugu film.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/r-madhavan-completes-schedule-of-savyasachi/articleshow/62097118.cms|title=R Madhavan completes schedule of 'Savyasachi'|website=The Times of India|access-date=28 January 2018|archive-url=https://archive.today/20180417085125/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/r-madhavan-completes-schedule-of-savyasachi/articleshow/62097118.cms|archive-date=17 April 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> He has also confirmed that he would work on ''Maara'' with debut filmmaker Dhilip Kumar, ''Silence'' by [[Kona Venkat]], and [[Rocketry: The Nambi Effect]], a biopic on rocket scientist [[Nambi Narayanan]] directed by himself.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/kollywood/150616/i-was-impressed-by-charlie-madhavan.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=18 June 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160618122932/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/kollywood/150616/i-was-impressed-by-charlie-madhavan.html |archivedate=18 June 2016 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/r-madhavan-gets-aboard-chandamama-door-ke-with-sushant-singh-rajput-4511992/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=7 February 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170207104636/http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/r-madhavan-gets-aboard-chandamama-door-ke-with-sushant-singh-rajput-4511992/ |archivedate= 7 February 2017 }}</ref>\n\n==Other projects==\n===Film and television work===\nMadhavan was first credited as a part of the technical crew for his work in ''[[Ramji Londonwaley]]'', an adaptation of his Tamil film ''[[Nala Damayanthi (2003 film)|Nala Damayanthi]]''. Apart from portraying the lead role, Madhavan worked on the film as a dialogue writer and played an active role in determining the crew of the movie.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.telegraphindia.com/1050901/asp/calcutta/story_5176144.asp |title=The Telegraph \u2013 Calcutta : Metro |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160223141522/http://www.telegraphindia.com/1050901/asp/calcutta/story_5176144.asp |archivedate=23 February 2016 }}</ref><ref name=\"rlpick\">{{cite web\n |year=2005 \n |title='Ramji Londonwale' is Madhavan's baby \n |publisher=Indiaglitz.com \n |accessdate=19 February 2011 \n |url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/malayalam/article/16537.html \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120709035222/http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/malayalam/article/16537.html \n |archivedate= 9 July 2012 \n}}</ref> In October 2007, Madhavan founded the production company, Leukos Films, and consequently bought the rights of his film, ''[[Evano Oruvan]]'', from producers [[Abbas-Mustan]] and [[K. Sera Sera]]. Securing sponsorship deals with [[HSBC]] and Santoor, Madhavan premi\u00e8red the film across North America and the Middle East before its Indian theatrical release, with the promotion method being used for the first time in Tamil cinema.<ref name=\"eoprom\"/> However, since the relative box office failure of the project, Madhavan downplayed future involvement in production ventures.<ref name=\"noprod\">{{cite news|author=Nivas, Namita |year=2009 |title=Great expectations |publisher=Screenindia.com |accessdate=20 February 2011 |url=http://www.screenindia.com/news/great-expectations/557811/ |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100401224559/http://www.screenindia.com/news/great-expectations/557811 |archivedate= 1 April 2010 }}</ref> The film, which Madhavan referred to as a \"part of his life\" during 2007, also saw him write the dialogues for the film along with [[Seeman (director)|Seeman]] by translating lines from the project's original version in the [[Marathi language|Marathi]] language.<ref name=\"eolife\">{{cite news|author=Warrier, Shobha |year=2007 |title=Evano Oruvan is a part of my life |publisher=[[Rediff]] |accessdate=20 February 2011 |url=http://specials.rediff.com/movies/2007/dec/05sl1.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101218084831/http://specials.rediff.com/movies/2007/dec/05sl1.htm |archivedate=18 December 2010 }}</ref> Madhavan then chose to become actively involved in the production of his 2016 bilingual films, ''[[Irudhi Suttru]]'' in Tamil and ''Saala Khadoos'' in Hindi, to ensure the film completed filming and had a theatrical release. Impressed by the strength of [[Sudha Kongara]]'s script for the Tamil film, Madhavan felt that the story had pan-Indian appeal and took the film's script to [[Rajkumar Hirani]], who agreed to produce and supervise work on the film's Hindi version. Madhavan co-produced the Hindi version of the film through his new production house, Tricolor Films, while leading the film's pan-Indian marketing campaign. The actor also helped finalise the film's lead actress, Ritika Singh, and was also credited as an additional screenplay writer in the films.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.khaleejtimes.com/citytimes/bollywood/raj-kumar-hirani-madhavan-confident-about-saala-khadoos |title=Raj Kumar Hirani, Madhavan confident about Saala Khadoos \u2013 Khaleej Times |author=Arti Dani |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160208082731/http://www.khaleejtimes.com/citytimes/bollywood/raj-kumar-hirani-madhavan-confident-about-saala-khadoos |archivedate= 8 February 2016 }}</ref>\n\nMadhavan has appeared as host for television programmes on [[Hindi]] channels, while he has also been a host at film award functions. During his television career in the 1990s, Madhavan first worked as a host on ''Tol Mol Ke Bol''. He was announced as the host of [[Sony Entertainment]] Television's ''[[Deal Ya No Deal]]'', the Indian version of the American game show ''[[Deal Or No Deal]]'', in October 2005. However, Madhavan quit as the lead anchor of the show in January 2006 claiming he was unhappy with the way the shoot schedules were handled by the production house. According to the actor, when he took on the show, he had made it clear that he would continue with his South Indian film assignments, and as the show was being filmed in Mumbai, he had found it hard to keep travelling throughout India from Chennai to film the ten days a month he had signed up for. Madhavan added that he was restricted by the producers to spend one day rehearsing technically, which left him with fatigue.<ref name=\"thambi\">{{cite news|author=Kamath, Sudhish |title=Madhavan returns as 'Thambi' |work=[[The Hindu]] |accessdate=25 February 2006 |url=http://www.hindu.com/2006/02/25/stories/2006022516810200.htm |location=Chennai, India |date=25 February 2006 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060227043310/http://www.hindu.com/2006/02/25/stories/2006022516810200.htm |archivedate=27 February 2006 }}</ref> [[Mandira Bedi]] subsequently replaced Madhavan as the anchor in February for Series 2 of the game show. In June 2010, Madhavan made a comeback to the game show format by accepting a contract with Imagine TV's Big Money show, signing on to host a single season, and then hosted an episode of the crime show [[Savdhaan India]] in January 2016.<ref name=\"left\">{{cite news|author=Kumar, Anuj |title=Maddie \u2013 between big and small |work=[[The Hindu]] |accessdate=21 February 2011 |url=http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article483853.ece |location=Chennai, India |date=24 June 2010 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100820055156/http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article483853.ece |archivedate=20 August 2010 }}</ref> Furthermore, he has been a guest judge in the Indian television show, [[Fame Gurukul]].<ref name=\"gurukul\">{{cite news|author=Kanwar, Rachna|year=2006|title='I have always broken the rules': Madhavan|work=[[The Times of India]]|accessdate=13 January 2006|url=http://tvguide.indiatimes.com/articleshow/1324415.cms|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20051212060507/http://tvguide.indiatimes.com/articleshow/1324415.cms|archive-date=12 December 2005|url-status=live}}</ref> In 2016, Madhavan stated that he would only take part in television commitments for money, while he does not consider his payment when signing on to appear in films.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/will-do-tv-only-for-money-r-madhavan/ |title=Will do TV only for money: R. Madhavan |date=28 January 2016 |work=The Indian Express |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160201073644/http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/will-do-tv-only-for-money-r-madhavan/ |archivedate= 1 February 2016 }}</ref> Madhavan has also hosted live events, notably the [[National Film Awards]] in 2013 with [[Huma Qureshi (actress)|Huma Qureshi]]. He was also the host of the 55th [[Filmfare Awards South]] in [[Chennai]] in 2008 and then also the Vijay Awards in 2013.<ref name=\"ffhosr\">{{cite news|author=Stephenson, Andrew |year=2007 |title=Happy Days at the 55th Filmfare South Awards |publisher=Bollyspice.com |accessdate=20 February 2011 |url=http://bollyspice.com/view.php/1411-happy-days-at-the-55th-tiger-balm-filmfare-south-awards.html |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090614085233/http://www.bollyspice.com/view.php/1411-happy-days-at-the-55th-tiger-balm-filmfare-south-awards.html |archivedate=14 June 2009 }}</ref>\n\n===Brand ambassador===\nMadhavan is amongst the leading brand ambassadors for products in India.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/metroplus/one-film-at-a-time/article1718118.ece|title=One film at a time|author=SUDHISH KAMATH|work=The Hindu|accessdate=16 February 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.livemint.com/Opinion/v6Oi5XAEwLZMbTgSPzkXgN/From-ambassadors-to-influencers.html |title=From ambassadors to influencers |author=Shuchi Bansal |work=livemint.com/ |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160129040854/http://www.livemint.com/Opinion/v6Oi5XAEwLZMbTgSPzkXgN/From-ambassadors-to-influencers.html |archivedate=29 January 2016 }}</ref> His early work involved advertisements for brands including [[Bajaj group|Bajaj]], Ponds, [[Fair and Lovely]] and [[TVS Group|TVS]], before signing a major endorsing deal with [[Pepsi]] and marketing company, IMG.<ref name=\"img\">{{cite news|year=2004 |title=IMG to manage South Indian superstar R.Madhavan |publisher=Indiantelevision.com |accessdate=20 February 2011 |url=http://www.indiantelevision.com/mam/headlines/y2k4/jan/janmam61.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110628182432/http://www.indiantelevision.com/mam/headlines/y2k4/jan/janmam61.htm |archivedate=28 June 2011 }}</ref> In 2007, Madhavan endorsed UniverCell, a multi-brand mobile phone retail chain owned by UniverCell Telecommunications India Pvt Ltd.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/todays-paper/tp-marketing/univercell-ropes-in-actor-madhavan/article1660173.ece |title=UniverCell ropes in actor Madhavan |work=Business Line |date=6 June 2007 |accessdate=13 July 2015}}</ref> Madhavan signed a contract with the mobile phone network, [[Bharti Airtel|Airtel]] for promotions in South India before being promoted as the pan-Indian ambassador for the brand a year later. His advertisements with [[Vidya Balan]] for Airtel won critical acclaim, and brought in film offers for the pair to feature together.<ref name=\"airtel\">{{cite web|year=2009 |title=Madhavan is on a dream run |publisher=[[Sify]] |accessdate=19 February 2011 |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/madhavan-is-on-a-dream-run-news-tamil-kkfsehajfje.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101119082717/http://sify.com/movies/madhavan-is-on-a-dream-run-news-tamil-kkfsehajfje.html |archivedate=19 November 2010 }}</ref> In June 2010, marketers from Arun Excello promoted a housing project in Oragadam, Chennai in a similar fashion to the release of a new film featuring Madhavan. With film-inspired posters and billboards put up around Chennai, the advertisement campaign attracted huge curiosity and the project became a success.<ref name=\"orohiy\">{{cite web|year=2010 |title=Maddy's Oragadam turns out to be a hit |publisher=[[Sify]] |accessdate=19 February 2011 |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/maddys-oragadam-turns-out-to-be-a-hit-news-tamil-kkfquQbcbga.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110228045407/http://www.sify.com/movies/maddys-oragadam-turns-out-to-be-a-hit-news-tamil-kkfquQbcbga.html |archivedate=28 February 2011 }}</ref> His long-term work with jewellery brand, [[Joyalukkas|Joy Alukkas]], led to the company creating life size wax models of him to place in their showrooms from January 2011.<ref name=\"wax\">{{cite news|title='Say cheese' with Madhavan |work=[[The Hindu]] |accessdate=21 February 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/2010/12/29/stories/2010122962750200.htm |location=Chennai, India |date=29 December 2010 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110103000014/http://www.hindu.com/2010/12/29/stories/2010122962750200.htm |archivedate= 3 January 2011 }}</ref> [[Maruti Suzuki]], for whom Madhavan is the brand ambassador, launched a special edition of the [[Suzuki Wagon R]] car calling it the Madhavan Signature Edition in September 2013.<ref name=\"maruti\">{{cite web|author=Yogi, Vikas |year=2013 |title=Maruti Suzuki Launches new Madhavan Signature Edition WagonR |work=[[Business Standard]] |accessdate=16 September 2013 |url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/news-cd/maruti-suzuki-launches-new-madhavan-signature-edition-wagonr-113091600829_1.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130920015724/http://www.business-standard.com/article/news-cd/maruti-suzuki-launches-new-madhavan-signature-edition-wagonr-113091600829_1.html |archivedate=20 September 2013 }}</ref> In 2015, online market place Snapdeal signed on [[Aamir Khan]] and Madhavan to be the company's ambassadors, with Snapdeal attempting to use Madhavan's popularity in South India to marker their services.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehansindia.com/posts/index/2015-10-16/3-Idiots-costars-%EF%BF%BD%E2%82%AC-Aamir-Khan-and-R-Madhavan-to-endorse-Snap-Deal-Big-Sale--181150 |title=3 Idiots Costars \u2013 Aamir Khan And R Madhavan To Endorse Snap Deal Big Sale |work=The Hans India |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160223123922/http://www.thehansindia.com/posts/index/2015-10-16/3-Idiots-costars-%EF%BF%BD%E2%82%AC-Aamir-Khan-and-R-Madhavan-to-endorse-Snap-Deal-Big-Sale--181150 |archivedate=23 February 2016 }}</ref>\n\n===Humanitarian causes===\nMadhavan, who is a vegetarian, promotes vegetarianism and is an active member of [[PETA]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/man-of-many-roles/article24299461.ece|title=Madhavan: man of many roles|last=S|first=Ananya|date=30 June 2018|work=The Hindu|access-date=12 August 2018|issn=0971-751X}}</ref> Since joining [[PETA]] after starring in his first film, he has appeared voluntarily in several advertisements and released an [[Interactive|E-Card]] for the brand. In July 2006, Madhavan was voted the \"cutest male vegetarian\" by an online poll conducted by the NGO, People for Ethical Treatment of Animals (PETA), while [[Kareena Kapoor]] won the female award respectively. In turn he cited that his success in the competition was due to his \"healthy vegetarian diet\".<ref name=\"vege\">{{cite news|author=Subbiah, Anandhan |year=2007 |title=Madhavan and PETA |work=[[The Times of India]] |accessdate=27 July 2007 |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/Calcutta_Times/Maddy__Kareena_cutest_vegetarians/articleshow/2240835.cms |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121025124631/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/Calcutta_Times/Maddy__Kareena_cutest_vegetarians/articleshow/2240835.cms |archivedate=25 October 2012 }}</ref> In October 2010, he wrote a letter to the CEO of [[Kentucky Fried Chicken]], on behalf of PETA, urging them to stop mistreatment of birds by the fast-food industry outlets and the killing of animals. He requested the boycott of KFC in India over animal welfare and conditions and was joined by [[Raveena Tandon]] and [[Rakhi Sawant]] in supporting the work of PETA in India.<ref name=\"kfc\">{{cite news|author=Nivas, Namita|year=2010|title=Earnest request\n|work=[[The Indian Express]]|accessdate=21 February 2011|url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/Not-even-for-his-daughter/697178/}}</ref> In addition, Madhavan was named PETA India\u2019s 2012 \"Person Of The Year\", while his son won PETA India's \"Compassionate Kid award\" in December 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://daily.bhaskar.com/article/ENT-peta-chooses-r-madhavan-as-person-of-the-year-4128229-NOR.html |title=PETA chooses R Madhavan as 'Person of the Year' |work=daily.bhaskar.com |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160224070956/http://daily.bhaskar.com/article/ENT-peta-chooses-r-madhavan-as-person-of-the-year-4128229-NOR.html |archivedate=24 February 2016 }}</ref>\n\nMadhavan has lent his support for the Chennai-based charity, The Banyan, and appeared in the charity musical [[Netru, Indru, Naalai]] directed by Mani Ratnam for the cause.<ref name=\"ninbanyan\">{{cite news\n |year=2005 \n |title=Mani Ratnam to direct Star Vijay's extravaganza \n |publisher=[[Rediff]] \n |accessdate=21 February 2011 \n |url=http://inhome.rediff.com/movies/2005/jun/15mani.htm \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110715165248/http://inhome.rediff.com/movies/2005/jun/15mani.htm \n |archivedate=15 July 2011 \n}}</ref> He appeared as a guest cook and newly launched restaurant in Chennai and cooked [[dosa]]s for auction for the charity, helping raise forty five thousand rupees.<ref name=\"cookhelp\">{{cite news\n |author=Warrier, Shobha \n |year=2006 \n |title=25,000 for a cup of coffee \n |publisher=[[Rediff]] \n |accessdate=21 February 2011 \n |url=http://inhome.rediff.com/movies/2006/jan/18look.htm \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110715165304/http://inhome.rediff.com/movies/2006/jan/18look.htm \n |archivedate=15 July 2011 \n}}</ref> He has been a part of an AIDS awareness programme initiated by [[Richard Gere]] in India and helped advertise the ''A Time for Heroes'' campaign appearing in a short film. Similarly Madhavan featured in a four-minute film produced by Agaram Foundation, ''[[Herova? Zerova?]]'', campaigning for educational awareness alongside [[Suriya]], [[Vijay (actor)|Vijay]] and [[Jyothika]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/holnus/009200805162223.htm |title=TN actors in documentary highlighting evils of child labour |date=16 May 2008 |work=[[The Hindu]] |accessdate=10 February 2010 |location=Chennai, India |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110604120118/http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/holnus/009200805162223.htm |archivedate= 4 June 2011 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://inhome.rediff.com/movies/2008/may/19sssurya.htm |title=Surya, the social activist |date=19 May 2008 |publisher=Rediff |accessdate=10 February 2010 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110715165327/http://inhome.rediff.com/movies/2008/may/19sssurya.htm |archivedate=15 July 2011 }}</ref> In 2010, along with his cast and crew from ''[[3 Idiots]]'', he helped raise Rs. 2.5&nbsp;million for the renovation of the school in [[Leh]], which was damaged by flash floods.<ref>{{Cite news|author=Somabasus, Kavitha |url=http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article613872.ece |title=Moments with Maddy |work=[[The Hindu]] |accessdate=21 February 2011 |location=Chennai, India |date=4 September 2010 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110629125355/http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article613872.ece |archivedate=29 June 2011 }}</ref> Madhavan laid bricks and tiles at the [[London Business School]] in July 2011, building a symbolic house to represent the 100,000 houses that will be built in India by 2015 as a part of Habitat for Humanity's campaign to improve substandard houses in India.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.mid-day.com/entertainment/2011/aug/040811-informer-2.htm |title=Abhishek Bachchan turns teacher |year=2011 |publisher=Mid-Day |accessdate=11 August 2011 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111109051318/http://www.mid-day.com/entertainment/2011/aug/040811-informer-2.htm |archivedate= 9 November 2011 }}</ref> During the [[2015 South Indian floods]], Madhavan worked alongside other Indian actors in coordinating the relief efforts.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/metroplus/fashion/madhavan-on-chennai-floods-the-saala-khadoos-look-and-his-style-factor/article7980456.ece|title=An actor and a style guru|author=Neeraja Murthy|work=The Hindu|accessdate=16 February 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://businessofcinema.com/bollywood_news/chennai-floods-hrithik-roshan-follows-shah-rukh-khan-donates-for-the-victims/258460 |title=Chennai Floods: Hrithik Roshan Follows Shah Rukh Khan, Donates For The Victims |work=Businessofcinema.com |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160223032151/http://businessofcinema.com/bollywood_news/chennai-floods-hrithik-roshan-follows-shah-rukh-khan-donates-for-the-victims/258460 |archivedate=23 February 2016 }}</ref> In 2016, [[Lepra]] India signed him to work as a goodwill ambassador in helping promote action against leprosy.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ians/r-madhavan-is-goodwill-ambassador-against-leprosy-116053000286_1.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=9 June 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160602081004/http://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ians/r-madhavan-is-goodwill-ambassador-against-leprosy-116053000286_1.html |archivedate= 2 June 2016 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Metro Plus |url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-metroplus/ambassador-against-leprosy/article8678575.ece |title=Ambassador against leprosy \u2013 Kochi |work=The Hindu |accessdate=22 January 2018}}</ref>\n\n==In the media==\n[[Image:Madhavanff.JPG|thumb|right|Madhavan seen with his wife, Sarita, at the [[Filmfare Awards]] ceremony in 2011]]\nMadhavan is one of the few actors in India who garners pan-Indian appeal, with his success in establishing himself in the North and the South Indian film industries, seeing him receive multiple offers as a brand ambassador.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/metroplus/the-proust-questionnaire-wish-i-had-bigger-calf-muscles-r-madhavan/article2701284.ece|title=The Proust Questionnaire \u2013 Wish I had bigger calf muscles: R. Madhavan|author=Subha J Rao|work=The Hindu|accessdate=16 February 2016}}</ref> Furthermore, it has led to producers offering him lead roles in bilingual films such as the English-Malayalam crossover film ''[[Nothing But Life]]'' and the Hindi-Tamil projects, ''[[Yavarum Nalam]]'' and ''[[Irudhi Suttru]]''. Moreover, most of his Tamil films are dubbed into Telugu, where he has created a box office market without appearing in a single straight Telugu film as a lead actor.<ref name=\"telugusuc\">{{cite web\n |year=2009 \n |title=Madhavan believes in content \n |publisher=Indiaglitz.com \n |accessdate=19 February 2011 \n |url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/telugu/article/48899.html \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120709093908/http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/telugu/article/48899.html \n |archivedate= 9 July 2012 \n}}</ref><ref name=\"teluglang\">{{cite web\n |author=Tuteja, Joginder \n |year=2010 \n |title=Maddy is against dubbing of his South films \n |publisher=Glamsham.com \n |accessdate=19 February 2011 \n |url=http://www.glamsham.com/movies/scoops/10/may/29-madhavan-is-again-dubbing-of-his-south-films-051009.asp \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110711101403/http://www.glamsham.com/movies/scoops/10/may/29-madhavan-is-again-dubbing-of-his-south-films-051009.asp \n |archivedate=11 July 2011 \n}}</ref> Madhavan holds a significant female fan following, which developed after his romantic roles in ''[[Alaipayuthey]]'' and ''[[Minnale]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/The-Madhavan-magic/articleshow/3250895.cms |title=The Madhavan magic! |work=The Times of India |date=19 July 2008 |accessdate=20 February 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-i-want-to-do-a-romantic-film-r-madhavan-1236093 |title=I want to do a romantic film: R Madhavan & Updates at Daily News & Analysis |work=Daily News and Analysis |date=4 March 2009 |accessdate=20 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160816095936/http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-i-want-to-do-a-romantic-film-r-madhavan-1236093 |archivedate=16 August 2016 }}</ref> Madhavan has also been active in keeping in contact with fans, maintaining a fan email account, a Facebook fan page and a Twitter account as well as being one of the first actors of Tamil films to turn blogger with entries in the year 2000.<ref name=\"blog\">{{cite web|author=Mahaldar, Manisha |year=2008 |title=Of 3 Idiots, blogging and more: Madhavan unplugged |publisher=[[CNN-IBN|IBN]] |accessdate=19 February 2011 |url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/of-3-idiots-blogging-and-more-madhavan-unplugged/73636-8.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120320025443/http://ibnlive.in.com/news/of-3-idiots-blogging-and-more-madhavan-unplugged/73636-8.html |archivedate=20 March 2012 }}</ref>\n\nHe has appeared at functions as a special guest, and has enjoyed particularly close links with technology company, [[Sify]], whom he signed on as his media partner for all his future releases after expressing satisfaction at the website they created for ''[[Rendu]]''.<ref name=\"sifmax\">{{cite news|title=\"Maddy\" charm enlivens Sifymax get-together |work=[[The Hindu]] |accessdate=21 February 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/2006/12/19/stories/2006121901910200.htm |location=Chennai, India |date=19 December 2006 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110629025030/http://www.hindu.com/2006/12/19/stories/2006121901910200.htm |archivedate=29 June 2011 }}</ref> Madhavan sat amongst a six-man jury for the selection of [[CNN]]-[[CNN-IBN|IBN]] Indian of the Year 2006.<ref name=\"gibn\">{{cite news\n |title=6 nominees for CNN-IBN award \n |work=[[The Hindu]] \n |accessdate=21 February 2011 \n |url=http://www.hindu.com/2007/02/01/stories/2007020118491400.htm \n |location=Chennai, India \n |date=1 February 2007 |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110629025051/http://www.hindu.com/2007/02/01/stories/2007020118491400.htm \n |archivedate=29 June 2011 \n}}</ref> He inaugurated the Chennai International Film Festival in 2007, taking the opportunity to deliver a message on preserving the environment.<ref name=\"ciff\">{{cite news|author=Kumar, Ashok |title=Film festival inaugurated |work=[[The Hindu]] |accessdate=21 February 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/2007/12/27/stories/2007122750490200.htm |location=Chennai, India |date=27 December 2007 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110629025132/http://www.hindu.com/2007/12/27/stories/2007122750490200.htm |archivedate=29 June 2011 }}</ref>\n\nA gaming company, Paradox Studios Limited, launched a new game compatible with mobile phones in July 2006, with Madhavan as the lead character. The company released two mobile game titles featuring Madhavan as their lead character.<ref name=\"game\">{{cite news|author=Devi, Sangeetha |title=Maddy to Sameera, everybody's hooked |work=[[The Hindu]] |accessdate=29 July 2006 |url=http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/mp/2006/07/29/stories/2006072902210100.htm |location=Chennai, India |date=29 July 2006 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071001010418/http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/mp/2006/07/29/stories/2006072902210100.htm |archivedate= 1 October 2007 }}</ref> The first of the two games, ''Madhavan's MIG'', featured the actor making a reprise of his [[Rang De Basanti]] pilot's role. In the other game titled ''Madhavan'', the player had to help the actor get to the premi\u00e8re of his latest movie evading the paparazzi.<ref name=\"gametwo\">{{cite news\n |author=Devi, Sangeetha \n |title=Play 'Madhavan' on your Reliance mobile \n |work=[[The Hindu]] \n |accessdate=10 July 2006 \n |url=http://www.hindu.com/2006/07/10/stories/2006071006280200.htm \n |location=Chennai, India \n |date=10 July 2006 |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071001021112/http://www.hindu.com/2006/07/10/stories/2006071006280200.htm \n |archivedate= 1 October 2007 \n}}</ref> In 2007, prominent entrepreneur [[N. R. Narayana Murthy]] requested Madhavan to be his interviewer at the India-Singapore Exposition and Madhavan went on to claim that the experience was \"unforgettable\" as Murthy was an idol to him.<ref name=\"murthy\">{{cite web|author=Warrier, Shobha |year=2007 |title=Maddy on quizzing Narayana Murthy |publisher=[[Rediff]] |accessdate=21 February 2011 |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2007/aug/24maddy.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100412093525/http://www.rediff.com/movies/2007/aug/24maddy.htm |archivedate=12 April 2010 }}</ref> Madhavan has attended conferences as a motivational speaker, talking about issues including situational awareness and confidence, with a speech delivered at [[Dr G R Damodaran College of Science|Damodaran Academy of Management]], [[Coimbatore]] going viral online.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/R-Madhavans-inspiring-speech-has-caught-everyones-attention-/articleshow/50666720.cms |title=R.Madhavan's inspiring speech has caught everyone's attention ! |work=The Times of India |date=21 January 2016 |accessdate=20 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160127041956/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/R-Madhavans-inspiring-speech-has-caught-everyones-attention-/articleshow/50666720.cms |archivedate=27 January 2016 }}</ref> Madhavan also took part and delivered speeches as a part of the annual India Conference at [[Harvard University]] during 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/r-madhavan-unforgettable-moment-while-speaking-at-harvard-university-4522656/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=15 February 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170215122059/http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/r-madhavan-unforgettable-moment-while-speaking-at-harvard-university-4522656/ |archivedate=15 February 2017 }}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nAfter completing the degree, he went on to teach communication and public speaking at workshops around India. At the [[Maharashtra]] workshop, he encountered his wife Sarita Birje for the first time in 1991, when she attended his class on the recommendation of her cousins.<ref name=\"ens\">{{cite web|author=Express News Service |year=1998 |title=The man who acts Pricey |work=[[The Indian Express]] |accessdate=11 August 1998 |url=http://www.indianexpress.com/res/web/pIe/ie/daily/19980811/22351284.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070929091446/http://www.indianexpress.com/res/web/pIe/ie/daily/19980811/22351284.html |archivedate=29 September 2007 }}</ref> Sarita was able to use the skills she had learned from Madhavan's classes to pass an interview to become an air hostess and after completing the course, the pair began dating. They married in 1999, before Madhavan entered mainstream films. The pair's marriage has been covered by the media, with Madhavan citing that advice from his mentor [[Mani Ratnam]] was useful.<ref name=\"twm2015\"/><ref name=\"marriage\">{{cite news|title=Madhavan's marriage tips |work=[[The Times of India]] |accessdate=21 February 2011 |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/news-interviews/Madhavans-relationship-tips/articleshow/7533990.cms |date=21 February 2011 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110225014828/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/news-interviews/Madhavans-relationship-tips/articleshow/7533990.cms |archivedate=25 February 2011 }}</ref> Sarita has worked as a costume designer in a few of Madhavan's films, most notably for ''[[Guru En Aalu]]'' (2009), when she worked along with [[Erum Ali]], the wife of Madhavan's co-star, [[Abbas (actor)|Abbas]], for their respective husbands.<ref name=\"designe\">{{cite web|author=Reddy, Krithika |year=2008 |title=It takes two pairs to tango |work=[[The Hindu]] |accessdate=21 February 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/mp/2008/07/26/stories/2008072651041200.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081106203148/http://www.hindu.com/mp/2008/07/26/stories/2008072651041200.htm |archivedate= 6 November 2008 }}</ref> Their son, Vedaant, was born in August 2005, which eventually led to relocating to the boat-club area in [[Chennai]] from [[Kilpauk]], where Madhavan's parents lived with him as well as his parents-in-law.<ref name=\"vedant\">{{cite web\n |author=Jha, Subhash \n |year=2005 \n |title=Madhavan has a baby boy \n |publisher=Indiaglitz.com \n |accessdate=23 August 2005 \n |url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/hindi/article/16383.html \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20051203074440/http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/hindi/article/16383.html \n |archivedate= 3 December 2005 \n}}</ref> In 2009, he relocated to [[Kandivali]], Mumbai, with his wife and son, as he pursued a career in [[Hindi]] films ahead of films in the South Indian industries.<ref>{{cite web |last= Pereira |first= Priyanka |title= Full Steam |url= http://www.indianexpress.com/news/full-steam/429097/1 |date= 28 February 2009 |work= The Indian Express |accessdate=30 August 2009}}</ref>\n\nMadhavan has maintained close links with fellow actors and has described actor [[Suriya]] as his best friend in the film industry.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/kamal-haasan-and-suriya-wish-madhavan-for-irudhi-suttru-salaa-kadoos-trailer-hollywood-news-148838.html|title=Kamal Haasan and Suriya boost up Madhavan|accessdate=16 February 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171030114616/https://www.indiaglitz.com/kamal-haasan-and-suriya-wish-madhavan-for-irudhi-suttru-salaa-kadoos-trailer-hollywood-news-148838.html|archive-date=30 October 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> The actor also is close friends with actresses [[Shilpa Shetty]] and [[Bipasha Basu]], as well as actors [[Aamir Khan]] and [[Abhishek Bachchan]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/R-Madhavan-Kangana-in-my-opinion-is-extremely-educated/articleshow/47344003.cms |title=R Madhavan: Kangana in my opinion is extremely educated |work=The Times of India |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150522015843/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/R-Madhavan-Kangana-in-my-opinion-is-extremely-educated/articleshow/47344003.cms |archivedate=22 May 2015 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/140814/entertainment-kollywood/article/%E2%80%98madhavan-very-dear-friend%E2%80%99 |title=Madhavan is a very dear friend |work=deccanchronicle.com/ |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150108073357/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/140814/entertainment-kollywood/article/%E2%80%98madhavan-very-dear-friend%E2%80%99 |archivedate= 8 January 2015 }}</ref> He is closely associated with actor [[Kamal Haasan]], after their appearance together in ''[[Anbe Sivam]]'', and has revealed that he considers the actor as his inspiration. He has also collaborated multiple times with directors Mani Ratnam, [[Rajkumar Hirani]] and [[Aanand Rai]], citing that the film makers \"understand him well\" and share a good \"comfort level\". He has also helped out actresses [[Reemma Sen]], [[Sadha]] and [[Nisha Kothari]] by signing them on for roles in his films, when they were going through a barren spell.<ref name=\"nishak\">{{cite news\n |author=Aamir \n |title=Luck by chance \n |work=[[The Hindu]] \n |accessdate=21 February 2011 \n |url=http://www.hindu.com/mp/2009/12/15/stories/2009121550500400.htm \n |location=Chennai, India \n |date=15 December 2009 |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110629025154/http://www.hindu.com/mp/2009/12/15/stories/2009121550500400.htm \n |archivedate=29 June 2011 \n}}</ref><ref name=\"reema\">{{cite web\n |author=Shankar, Settu \n |year=2007 \n |title=Reema returns to Kollywood \n |publisher=OneIndia.com \n |accessdate=1 June 2007 \n |url=http://entertainment.oneindia.in/tamil/exclusive/reema-sen-kollywood-010607.html \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070930163704/http://entertainment.oneindia.in/tamil/exclusive/reema-sen-kollywood-010607.html \n |archivedate=30 September 2007 \n}}</ref><ref name=\"sadha\">{{cite web\n |year=2007 \n |title=Sada replaces Nandana! \n |publisher=[[Sify]] \n |accessdate=27 February 2007 \n |url=http://sify.com/movies/telugu/fullstory.php?id=14395755 \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070226065542/http://sify.com/movies/telugu/fullstory.php?id=14395755 \n |archivedate=26 February 2007 \n}}</ref>\n\nMadhavan announced a sabbatical from films in late 2010 citing he would take the time off to visit London, lose weight, play golf, take treatment for his knee injury and spend time with family. Though he kept away from starting new projects, during the period he was involved in the promotional activity of two of his releases, ''[[Manmadan Ambu]]'' and ''[[Tanu Weds Manu]]''.<ref name=\"sabbatical\">{{cite web|year=2010 |title=Maddy all set for a sabbatical |publisher=[[Sify]] |accessdate=21 February 2011 |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/maddy-is-all-set-for-a-sabbatical-news-tamil-kkgu9yhdaec.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101130082411/http://sify.com/movies/maddy-is-all-set-for-a-sabbatical-news-tamil-kkgu9yhdaec.html |archivedate=30 November 2010 }}</ref> He later made a comeback, earlier than anticipated, after director [[N. Linguswamy|Linguswamy]] convinced him to work on ''[[Vettai]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-south-interview-with-madhavan/20120112.htm |title=Madhavan: Vettai has blockbuster written all over it |date=12 January 2012 |work=Rediff |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160229235933/http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-south-interview-with-madhavan/20120112.htm |archivedate=29 February 2016 }}</ref> The actor later took an extended sabbatical from 2012 onwards to work on his fitness and get into shape for his role as a retired boxer in ''[[Irudhi Suttru]]''. Madhavan is a keen golf player, having played for pleasure alongside actor [[Amitabh Bachchan]] and director [[Mani Ratnam]], while also appearing in a celebrity charity event in 2007.<ref name=\"golf\">{{cite news\n |author=Anthikad-Chibber, Mini \n |title=The Dark Knight \n |work=[[The Hindu]] \n |accessdate=21 February 2011 \n |url=http://www.hindu.com/mp/2010/02/25/stories/2010022550280400.htm \n |location=Chennai, India \n |date=25 February 2010 |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110629025202/http://www.hindu.com/mp/2010/02/25/stories/2010022550280400.htm \n |archivedate=29 June 2011 \n}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.openthemagazine.com/article/cinema/a-tamilian-in-bollywood |title=A Tamilian in Bollywood |work=OPEN Magazine |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160307194515/http://www.openthemagazine.com/article/cinema/a-tamilian-in-bollywood |archivedate= 7 March 2016 }}</ref> In 2017, he won the qualification round of the Mumbai leg of the Mercedes Trophy golf meet and subsequently qualified for the National Finals.<ref>https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/actor-madhavn-qualifies-national-finals-mercedes-trophy-golf-meet-74616</ref> He also made an appearance for Chennai Rhinos in the [[2011 Celebrity Cricket League]], playing against Karnataka Bulldozers. His experiences flying Cessna planes when he was with National Cadet Corps, also led to a passion for aero-modelling, with the actor stating it \"justified his decision\" to pursue a degree in electronics.<ref name=\"aeromodel\">{{cite news|author=Sinha, Sayoni |title=Madhavan's flight club |work=[[The Times of India]] |accessdate=21 February 2011 |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/news-interviews/Madhavans-flight-Club/articleshow/6313917.cms |date=15 August 2010 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100820014329/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/news-interviews/Madhavans-flight-Club/articleshow/6313917.cms |archivedate=20 August 2010 }}</ref>\n\n==Filmography and awards==\n{{main|R. Madhavan filmography}}\n\n===Awards and nominations===\nAmong Madhavan's film awards are four [[Filmfare Awards South|Filmfare Awards]];\n* [[Filmfare Award for Best Male Debut \u2013 South|Best South Male Debut]] for ''Alaipayuthey''\n* [[Filmfare Award for Best Supporting Actor \u2013 Tamil|Best Tamil Supporting Actor]] for ''Aaytha Ezhuthu''\n* [[Filmfare Award for Best Actor \u2013 Tamil|Best Tamil Actor]] for ''Irudhi Suttru''\n* [[Filmfare Critics Award for Best Actor \u2013 South|Critics' Best Tamil Actor]] for ''Vikram Vedha''\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{wikiquote}}\n{{commons category|Madhavan}}\n{{good article}}\n* {{IMDb name|id=0534856}}\n* [https://www.bollywoodhungama.com/celebrity/r-madhavan/ R. Madhavan] on [[Bollywood Hungama]]\n\n{{FilmfareTamilBestActor}}\n{{TamilNaduStateAwardForBestActor}}\n{{ScreenAwardBestMaleDebut}}\n{{SIIMA Award for Best Actor in a Supporting Role}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Madhavan, R}}\n[[Category:1970 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Tamil male actors]]\n[[Category:Indian game show hosts]]\n[[Category:Male actors in Kannada cinema]]\n[[Category:Indian male television actors]]\n[[Category:Indian male film actors]]\n[[Category:Indian television presenters]]\n[[Category:People from Jamshedpur]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Jharkhand]]\n[[Category:Indian male screenwriters]]\n[[Category:Film producers from Jharkhand]]\n[[Category:Male actors in Hindi cinema]]\n[[Category:Male actors in Malayalam cinema]]\n[[Category:Tamil Nadu State Film Awards winners]]\n[[Category:Filmfare Awards South winners]]\n[[Category:International Tamil Film Award winners]]\n[[Category:SIIMA Awards winners]]\n[[Category:Tamil actors]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Indian film actor, writer and producer}}\n{{EngvarB|date=March 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name = R. Madhavan\n| image = Madhavan Saala Khadoos (cropped).jpg\n| image_size = 225px\n| caption = Madhavan in 2016\n| birth_name = Madhavan Balaji Ranganathan\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|df=y|1970|06|01}}\n| birth_place = [[Jamshedpur]], Bihar (now in [[Jharkhand]]), India\n| education = \n| occupation = {{hlist|Actor|writer|producer|director}}\n| years_active = 1994\u2013present\n| nationality  = Indian\n| spouse = {{Marriage|Sarita Birje|1999}}\n| children = 1\n| partner = \n}}\n\n'''R. Madhavan''' (born 1 June 1970) is an Indian actor, writer and film producer who predominantly appears in [[Tamil language|Tamil]] and [[Hindi]] language films. He has received four [[Filmfare Awards South|Filmfare Awards]] and an award from the [[Tamil Nadu State Film Awards]] along with recognition and nominations from other organisations. He has been described as one of the few actors in India who is able to achieve pan-Indian appeal, having appeared in films from seven different languages.<ref name=\"pan-Indian\">{{cite web |year=2009 |title=R Madhavan signs up with Atul Kasbekar's Bling Entertainment |publisher=Business of Cinema |accessdate=4 February 2011 |url=http://www.businessofcinema.com/news.php?newsid=13618 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101201042753/http://businessofcinema.com/news.php?newsid=13618 |archivedate=1 December 2010 }}</ref><ref name=\"language\">{{cite news|author=Sharma, Smrity |title=Surya, Vikram need to learn Hindi: Madhavan |work=[[The Times of India]] |accessdate=4 February 2011 |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/regional/news-interviews/Surya-Vikram-need-to-learn-Hindi-Madhavan/articleshow/6913669.cms |date=13 November 2010 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101116181454/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/regional/news-interviews/Surya-Vikram-need-to-learn-Hindi-Madhavan/articleshow/6913669.cms |archivedate=16 November 2010 }}</ref>\n\nMadhavan began his acting career with television guest appearances, including a role on the [[Zee TV]] prime-time soap opera ''[[Banegi Apni Baat]]'' in 1994. After appearing in commercials and in small roles, he later gained [[Breakthrough role|recognition]] in the [[Tamil cinema|Tamil film industry]] through [[Mani Ratnam]]'s successful romance film ''[[Alaipayuthey]]'' (2000). Madhavan soon developed an image as a romantic hero with notable roles in two of 2001's highest grossing Tamil films, [[Gautham Menon]]'s directorial debut ''[[Minnale]]'' and [[Madras Talkies]]' ''[[Dumm Dumm Dumm]]''. He worked with Mani Ratnam again in the critically acclaimed 2002 film ''[[Kannathil Muthamittal]]'' playing the father of an adopted girl, whilst he achieved commercial success with his role in [[N. Linguswamy]]'s action film, ''[[Run (2002 film)|Run]]'' (2002). Madhavan was cast alongside [[Kamal Haasan]] in the 2003 drama ''[[Anbe Sivam]]'', which earned him two notable awards for Best Supporting Actor. In 2004, he gave a critically acclaimed performance as the antagonist in the multi-starrer ''[[Aayutha Ezhuthu]]'' and the film secured him his first [[Filmfare Awards South|Filmfare Award]] for the intense portrayal of a rogue.\n\nIn the mid-2000s, Madhavan also actively pursued a career in [[Bollywood|Hindi films]], by appearing in supporting roles in three highly successful productions, [[Rakeysh Omprakash Mehra]]'s ''[[Rang De Basanti]]'' (2006), Mani Ratnam's biopic ''[[Guru (2007 film)|Guru]]'' (2007) and [[Rajkumar Hirani]]'s ''[[3 Idiots]]'' (2009), which went on to become the [[List of highest-grossing Indian films|highest grossing Indian film of all time]] upon release. He simultaneously worked on Tamil films, gaining critical acclaim for his portrayal of a [[vigilante]] in his home production ''[[Evano Oruvan]]'' (2007) and for the successful bilingual horror film, ''[[Yavarum Nalam]]'' (2009). After appearing in further box office hits, ''[[Tanu Weds Manu]]'' (2011) and ''[[Vettai]]'' (2012), Madhavan took a break from acting. Returning after a three-year sabbatical in 2015, his comeback films, the romantic-comedy ''[[Tanu Weds Manu Returns]]'' (2015), the bilingual sports drama ''[[Irudhi Suttru]]'' (2016) and the crime film ''[[Vikram Vedha]]'' (2017) all won critical and commercial acclaim. His performance as a boorish boxing coach in ''Irudhi Suttru'' fetched him Best Actor awards at the [[Filmfare Award for Best Actor \u2013 Tamil|Filmfare]], [[2nd IIFA Utsavam|IIFA]] and [[South Indian International Movie Awards|SIIMA]] award ceremonies.<ref name=\"indiatimes1\">{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/winners-64th-jio-filmfare-awards-south/articleshow/59192157.cms|title=Winners: 64th Jio Filmfare Awards 2017 (South)|work=The Times of India|date=19 June 2017|access-date=21 June 2017|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6rJ496Tl8?url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/winners-64th-jio-filmfare-awards-south/articleshow/59192157.cms|archive-date=18 June 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=I have no insecurites: R Madhavan on 'Saala Khadoos', 'Tanu Weds Manu Returns' and Kangana Ranaut\n|url=http://www.firstpost.com/bollywood/i-have-no-insecurites-r-madhavan-on-saala-khadoos-tanu-weds-manu-returns-and-kangana-2312148.html |accessdate=27 June 2015 |publisher=FirstPost |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150627204437/http://www.firstpost.com/bollywood/i-have-no-insecurites-r-madhavan-on-saala-khadoos-tanu-weds-manu-returns-and-kangana-2312148.html |archivedate=27 June 2015 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title='Tanu Weds Manu Returns' Box Office Collection: Will Kangana-Madhavan Starrer Cross \u20b9150 Crore and Beat Salman's Movie Record by 6th Weekend? |url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/tanu-weds-manu-returns-box-office-collection-will-kangana-madhavan-starrer-cross-150-crore-637267 |accessdate=27 June 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150627175108/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/tanu-weds-manu-returns-box-office-collection-will-kangana-madhavan-starrer-cross-150-crore-637267 |archivedate=27 June 2015 }}</ref>\n\nIn addition to his acting career, Madhavan has worked as a writer on his films, hosted television programmes and has been a prominent celebrity endorser for brands and products.<ref name=\"oragadam\">{{cite web|year=2010 |title=Maddy's Oragadam turns out to be a hit |publisher=[[Sify]] |accessdate=4 February 2011 |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/maddys-oragadam-turns-out-to-be-a-hit-news-tamil-kkfquQbcbga.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110228045407/http://www.sify.com/movies/maddys-oragadam-turns-out-to-be-a-hit-news-tamil-kkfquQbcbga.html |archivedate=28 February 2011 }}</ref> He has also worked as a film producer, first making ''Evano Oruvan'' with Leukos Films, before setting up Tricolour Films to produce ''[[Irudhi Suttru|Saala Khadoos]]'' (2016). Madhavan is noted for his philanthropic activities and promotes various causes such as environment, health and education. He is particularly vocal about the protection of animals and was awarded PETA's Person of the Year recognition in 2011.\n\n==Early life==\nMadhavan was born on 1 June 1970 in [[Jamshedpur]], Bihar (now in [[Jharkhand]]), India, to a [[Tamil Brahmin]] family. His father Ranganathan was a management executive in [[Tata Steel]] and his mother, Saroja was a manager in the [[Bank of India]]. His younger sister, Devika, is a software engineer.<ref name=\"family\">{{cite news|author=Rangarajan, Malathi |year=2004 |title=He loves challenges |newspaper=[[The Hindu]] |accessdate=22 October 2004 |url=http://www.hindu.com/fr/2004/10/22/stories/2004102202400100.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20041112213630/http://www.hindu.com/fr/2004/10/22/stories/2004102202400100.htm |archivedate=12 November 2004 }}</ref> He had a Tamil-speaking upbringing in [[Bihar]].<ref name=\"tambrahm\">{{cite web|author=Jha, Subhash K. |year=2005 |title=He loves challenges |publisher=Nowrunning.com |accessdate=4 February 2011 |url=http://www.nowrunning.com/news/bollywood/madhavan-on-being-reel-life-bihari-real-life-father/4026/story.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121009171303/http://www.nowrunning.com/news/bollywood/madhavan-on-being-reel-life-bihari-real-life-father/4026/story.htm |archivedate= 9 October 2012 }}</ref>\n\nIn 1988, Madhavan gained a scholarship to represent India as a cultural ambassador from Rajaram College, [[Kolhapur]] and spent a year in [[Stettler, Alberta]], Canada as part of an exchange programme with [[Rotary International]]. He returned to Kolhapur and completed his education, graduating with a [[Bachelor of Science|BSc]] in [[Electronics]]. During his college years, Madhavan became actively involved in extra-curricular military training and at 22, he was recognised as amongst the leading [[National Cadet Corps (India)|NCC]] cadets in [[Maharashtra]], which allowed him to make a trip with seven others as [[National Cadet Corps (India)|NCC]] cadets to England.<ref name=\"twm2015\">{{cite web|author=Gupta, Priya K. |year=2015 |title=get along with people who get along with my wife: Maddy |work=[[The Times of India]] |accessdate=20 May 2015 |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/I-get-along-with-people-who-get-along-with-my-wife-Maddy/articleshow/47343041.cms |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150523072543/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/I-get-along-with-people-who-get-along-with-my-wife-Maddy/articleshow/47343041.cms |archivedate=23 May 2015 }}</ref> As a result of this opportunity, he received training with the [[British Army]], the [[Royal Navy]] and the [[Royal Air Force]], which he had, at a point, considered joining.<ref name=\"cadet\">{{cite web\n |author=Jain, Priyanka \n |year=2006 \n |title=Madhavan, the remote control pilot \n |publisher=[[Rediff]] \n |accessdate=8 February 2006 \n |url=http://in.rediff.com/movies/2006/feb/08mad.htm \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060222021718/http://in.rediff.com/movies/2006/feb/08mad.htm \n |archivedate=22 February 2006 \n}}</ref> However he missed the age cut-off by six months and was subsequently unable to join the programme. After he lost out on the place, he began teaching courses on public speaking and personality development skills in Kolhapur and the satisfaction he gained through teaching, prompted him to pursue a post-graduation in public speaking at [[Kishinchand Chellaram College]] in Bombay (present-day Mumbai). During the period, he also won the Indian Championship for [[Public Speaking]] and subsequently represented India at the Young Businessmen Conference in Tokyo, Japan in 1992.<ref name=\"speak\">{{cite web\n |author=Rangaswamy, Hema \n |title=City's Latest Heart Throb \n |publisher=Chennaibest.com \n |access-date=20 January 2001 \n |url=http://www.chennaibest.com/cityresources/Entertainment/movies/interviewmadhavan.asp \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20010304201747/http://www.chennaibest.com/cityresources/Entertainment/movies/interviewmadhavan.asp \n |archivedate= 4 March 2001 \n}}</ref> During his stint in Bombay, he opted to create a portfolio and submit it to a modelling agency.<ref name=\"twm2015\"/>\n\n==Acting career==\n===Early work===\nIn early 1996, Madhavan worked on a sandalwood talc advertisement directed by [[Santosh Sivan]], who later recommended him to [[Mani Ratnam]] to take part in a screen test for a role in ''[[Iruvar]]'' (1997). Madhavan was auditioned for the leading role of Tamizhselvan amongst several other more established actors, but Mani Ratnam eventually left him out of the project citing that he thought his \"eyes looked too young\" for a senior role.<ref name=\"iruvar\">{{cite web\n |author=Gliteratti \n |year=1996 \n |title=A Close Shave \n |publisher=[[Outlook India]] \n |accessdate=24 July 1996 \n |url=http://www.outlookindia.com/glitterati.aspx?41 \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101023221415/http://outlookindia.com/glitterati.aspx?41 \n |archivedate=23 October 2010 \n}}</ref><ref name=\"iruvargold\">{{cite web\n |author=Ganapati, Priya \n |year=2000 \n |title=People remember scenes, not episodes \n |publisher=[[Rediff]] \n |accessdate=8 March 2000 \n |url=http://www.rediff.com/entertai/2000/mar/08madh.htm \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120709061247/http://www.rediff.com/entertai/2000/mar/08madh.htm \n |archivedate= 9 July 2012 \n}}</ref> Prior to his film audition, Madhavan was spotted by a television executive while out walking in [[Lokhandwala]] in [[Mumbai]], and was recruited to feature in Hindi television serials, appearing as a crook in his first venture ''Yule Love Stories''. He appeared in leading roles in [[Zee TV]]'s ''[[Banegi Apni Baat]]'' and ''[[Ghar Jamai (TV series)|Ghar Jamai]]'', while he gained further popularity portraying the character of Shekhar in ''[[Saaya (Indian TV series)|Saaya]]''. He also went on to act as a ship's captain in ''[[Sea Hawks (TV series)|Sea Hawks]]'', as a convict in ''Yeh Kahan Aa Gaye Hum'' and worked as a television anchor in ''Tol Mol Ke Bol'' amongst other television appearances.<ref>{{cite web|author=site admin |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/magazine/cover-story/story/19970616-young-and-big-stars-of-television-831613-1997-06-16 |title=The rising stars |publisher=Indiatoday.in |date=16 June 1997 |accessdate=22 January 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"serials\">{{cite web\n |author=Express News Service \n |year=1998 \n |title=The man who acts Pricey. \n |work=[[The Indian Express]] \n |accessdate=11 August 1998 \n |url=http://www.indianexpress.com/res/web/pIe/ie/daily/19980811/22351284.html \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070929091446/http://www.indianexpress.com/res/web/pIe/ie/daily/19980811/22351284.html \n |archivedate=29 September 2007 \n}}</ref> His first appearance in a feature film role came through a small role in ''[[Is Raat Ki Subah Nahin]]'' (1996), where he portrayed a singer in a bar.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://in.movies.yahoo.com/news/manu-mania-r-madhavan-turns-42-183000043.html |title='Manu' Mania: R. Madhavan Turns 42! |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150611061803/https://in.movies.yahoo.com/news/manu-mania-r-madhavan-turns-42-183000043.html |archivedate=11 June 2015 }}</ref>\n\nIn 1997, Madhavan appeared in a supporting role as an Indian police officer in [[Fred Olen Ray]]'s English film, ''[[Inferno (1997 film)|Inferno]]'', which was shot in India.<ref name=\"iruvargold\"/> His first chance in [[Cinema of India|Indian cinema]] came in the form of ''[[Shanti Shanti Shanti]]'' (1998), a [[Kannada]] film, in which he appeared as a carefree youngster alongside actor [[Abbas (actor)|Abbas]]. However, the film failed to make an impact and went unnoticed at the box office.<ref name=\"sss\">{{cite web\n |author=Rajitha \n |year=2000 \n |title=Vijay meets his son on the Net! \n |publisher=[[Rediff]] \n |accessdate=26 August 2000 \n |url=http://www.rediff.com/entertai/2000/aug/26tt.htm \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20010303003735/http://www.rediff.com/entertai/2000/aug/26tt.htm \n |archivedate= 3 March 2001 \n}}</ref> During the period, Hindi film director Vinod Pandey launched Madhavan as a [[Bollywood]] hero, with a project titled ''[[Akeli (film)|Akeli]]'', however the film was shelved before the production process had been completed.<ref name=\"lakheli\">{{cite news\n |author=Karisma Upadhyay \n |title=Maddy Cool \n |work=[[The Times of India]] \n |accessdate=15 October 2001 \n |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/articleshow/1278036573.cms \n |date=15 October 2001 |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060427172423/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/articleshow/1278036573.cms \n |archivedate=27 April 2006 \n}}</ref>\n\n===1999\u20132003===\nIn 1999, leading Indian director [[Mani Ratnam]] selected Madhavan to feature in the leading role of his Tamil romantic film, ''[[Alaipayuthey]]'' (2000) and the film's subsequent critical and commercial success gave Madhavan his [[breakthrough role|breakthrough]] as an actor. Portraying the character of Karthik Varadharajan, a young husband experiencing difficulties with his marriage. Madhavan revealed that he studied the technical aspects of film-making from the director and learned the entire script of the film, irrespective of whether he was in the scene or not. He became the first debutant actor to be cast by Mani Ratnam in the lead role of a film, and revealed that when he found out that he was set to work with the director he was overcome with a \"mixture of excitement, awe, fear and expectations\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/tamil/interview.php?id=6005438&cid=2408 |title=Welcome to |publisher=Sify.com |date=20 January 2007 |accessdate=25 August 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140324200850/http://www.sify.com/movies/tamil/interview.php?id=6005438&cid=2408 |archivedate=24 March 2014 }}</ref> Featuring alongside actress [[Shalini]], Madhavan's performance was well received by critics and the film's success led to it developing \"classic\" status.<ref name=\"bebe\">{{cite news|author=Dutt, Purba |title=I'm very fond of Arya: Madhavan |work=[[The Times of India]] |accessdate=4 February 2011 |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/regional/news-interviews/Im-very-fond-of-Arya-Madhavan-/articleshow/6566336.cms |date=17 September 2010 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100920212100/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/regional/news-interviews/Im-very-fond-of-Arya-Madhavan-/articleshow/6566336.cms |archivedate=20 September 2010 }}</ref> A critic from [[The Hindu]], described that Madhavan \"sails through the litmus test with ease\", whilst another review cited that Madhavan was a \"promising debutant\" into the film industry.<ref name=\"aphindu\">{{cite web|year=2000 |title=Film Review: ''Alaipayuthey'' |work=[[The Hindu]] |accessdate=4 February 2011 |url=http://www.hinduonnet.com/2000/04/21/stories/09210225.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100901062104/http://www.hinduonnet.com/2000/04/21/stories/09210225.htm |archivedate= 1 September 2010 }}</ref><ref name=\"apindo\">{{cite web \n |author=Gopalakrishnan, Usha \n |year=2000 \n |title=Alai Payuthey \n |publisher=Indlink.com \n |accessdate=4 February 2011 \n |url=http://www.indolink.com/tamil/cinema/Reviews/articles/Alai_Payudhae_1374.html \n |url-status=dead \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120318001120/http://www.indolink.com/tamil/cinema/Reviews/articles/Alai_Payudhae_1374.html \n |archivedate=18 March 2012 \n }}</ref> After the success of his first [[Tamil film]], the producers of his previous [[Kannada]] film, ''Shanti Shanti Shanti'', dubbed the film into Tamil and released it as ''Relax'', to capitalise on Madhavan's new-found success.<ref name=\"sss\"/> Madhavan's next film, ''[[Ennavale]]'' (2000), garnered mixed reviews although Madhavan's portrayal was praised as the \"mainstay\" of the film, with claims that the film for him was a \"merely a prosaic exercise\".<ref name=\"enhindu\">{{cite news|author=Rangarajan, Malathi|year=2000|title=Film Review: Ennavale|newspaper=[[The Hindu]]|accessdate=4 February 2011|url=http://www.hindu.com/2000/12/29/stories/09290224.htm}}</ref>\n\nMadhavan's first release of 2001, [[Gautham Menon]]'s directorial debut ''[[Minnale]]'', opened to critical and commercial acclaim. Featuring a popular soundtrack by [[Harris Jayaraj]] and marketed as a [[Valentine's Day]] release, ''Minnale'' further built on the actor's image as a [[romantic hero]] and was later listed as a \"classic romantic film\" from the Tamil film industry.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/love-is-in-the-air-part-2-tamil-news-90963.html|title=Love is in the Air Part 2|accessdate=16 February 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"minhindu\">{{cite news|author=Padmanabhan, Savitha |title=Film Review: Minnale |work=[[The Hindu]] |accessdate=4 February 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/2001/02/09/stories/09090224.htm |location=Chennai, India |date=9 February 2001 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121108195114/http://www.hindu.com/2001/02/09/stories/09090224.htm |archivedate= 8 November 2012 }}</ref> He then collaborated with Mani Ratnam for the second time by appearing in the director's production venture, the romantic comedy ''[[Dumm Dumm Dumm]]'' (2001), alongside [[Jyothika]]. Appearing as an unhappy groom trying to halt his wedding, the film won positive acclaim and became a commercial success, with Madhavan establishing himself as a bankable actor in [[South India]].<ref name=\"twohits\">{{cite web|author=Shoba Warrior |year=2001 |title=Hindi films were to happen much later! |publisher=[[Rediff]] |accessdate=6 October 2001 |url=http://www.rediff.com/entertai/2001/oct/16gau.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20011016131729/http://www.rediff.com/entertai/2001/oct/16gau.htm |archivedate=16 October 2001 }}</ref> Madhavan then again appeared as a husband in a tumultuous marriage in ''[[Parthale Paravasam]]'' (2001), the hundredth venture of veteran director [[K. Balachander]]. Despite featuring amongst an ensemble cast and being highly anticipated prior to release, the film failed at the box-office, with critics citing that Madhavan looked \"rather bored\" with the proceedings.<ref name=\"paravasam\">{{cite web\n |author=Rajitha \n |year=2001 \n |title=Review:Parthale Paravasam \n |publisher=[[Rediff]] \n |accessdate=4 December 2001 \n |url=http://in.rediff.com/movies/2001/dec/04paar.htm \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20031117105747/http://in.rediff.com/movies/2001/dec/04paar.htm \n |archivedate=17 November 2003 \n}}</ref> Similarly his first lead role in a Hindi film, ''[[Rehna Hai Tere Dil Mein]]'' (2001), a remake of his ''Minnale'', was also unsuccessful at the box office, with the film and Madhavan's performance receiving mixed reviews.<ref name=\"rhtdmreview\">{{cite web\n |author=Adarsh, Taran \n |year=2001 \n |title=Rehna Hai Tere Dil Mein \n |publisher=[[Bollywood Hungama]] \n |accessdate=19 February 2011 \n |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/review/6838/index.html \n |authorlink=Taran Adarsh \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110922062043/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/review/6838/index.html \n |archivedate=22 September 2011 \n}}</ref> However, the film belatedly gained popularity through screenings on television and subsequently developed a cult following amongst young audiences.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pinkvilla.com/entertainment/discussion/bollywoods-cult-classics |title=Bollywood's Cult Classics |work=PINKVILLA |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160203022640/http://www.pinkvilla.com/entertainment/discussion/bollywoods-cult-classics |archivedate= 3 February 2016 }}</ref>\n\nIn 2002, Madhavan played the role of a novelist in Mani Ratnam's ''[[Kannathil Muthamittal]]'' alongside actresses [[P. S. Keerthana|Keerthana]], [[Simran (actress)|Simran]] and [[Nandita Das]]. In the film, he was shown as the role of the father of an adopted child, who wishes to return to her native homeland amidst the [[Sri Lankan civil war]]. The film received widespread critical acclaim and went on to win six [[National Film Awards|National Awards]] as well as over ten awards at various International Film Festivals.<ref name=\"km\">{{cite web\n |author=Rajitha \n |year=2002 \n |title=Review:Kannathil Muthamittal \n |publisher=[[Rediff]] \n |accessdate=16 February 2002 \n |url=http://in.rediff.com/movies/2002/feb/16kan.htm \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110604021138/http://in.rediff.com/movies/2002/feb/16kan.htm \n |archivedate= 4 June 2011 \n}}</ref> Madhavan gained acclaim for his portrayal with a critic citing \"he lived the role of the character he portrays\", with the film seeing him move away from the romantic hero image for the first time into a more serious, performance-orientated role. The good performance of the film internationally also helped him develop an overseas market for his films.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/mp/2002/09/23/stories/2002092301070300.htm |title=The Hindu : Mad about 'Maddy' |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20031102055404/http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/mp/2002/09/23/stories/2002092301070300.htm |archivedate= 2 November 2003 |newspaper=The Hindu |date=23 September 2002 }}</ref><ref name=\"kmreview\">{{cite web|author=Pearl, Tulika |year=2002 |title=Delicate flower caught in a storm |publisher=[[Rediff]] |accessdate=19 February 2011 |url=http://in.rediff.com/movies/2002/feb/16kan.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110604021138/http://in.rediff.com/movies/2002/feb/16kan.htm |archivedate= 4 June 2011 }}</ref> Madhavan's next large success came with ''[[Run (2002 film)|Run]]'', a film recognised for its screenplay, with Madhavan appearing in an action film for the first time in his career.<ref name=\"run\">{{cite news\n |year=2002 \n |title=Who's in the race? \n |newspaper=[[The Hindu]] \n |accessdate=25 November 2002 \n |url=http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/mp/2002/11/25/stories/2002112500090201.htm \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20031104035839/http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/mp/2002/11/25/stories/2002112500090201.htm \n |archivedate= 4 November 2003 \n}}</ref> In regard to his performance, [[The Hindu]]'s critic noted \"he manages to portray action with \u00e9lan in ''Run'' and actually looks fit and comfortable in the role\", with the film helping him make a breakthrough as an [[action hero]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/fr/2002/09/13/stories/2002091300930200.htm |title=The Hindu : Run |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080225193205/http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/fr/2002/09/13/stories/2002091300930200.htm |archivedate=25 February 2008 |newspaper=The Hindu |date=13 September 2002 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/fr/2003/01/10/stories/2003011001190300.htm |title=The Hindu : It is the package that ultimately matters |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20041117184728/http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/fr/2003/01/10/stories/2003011001190300.htm |archivedate=17 November 2004 |newspaper=The Hindu |date=10 January 2003 }}</ref> Despite another unsuccessful Hindi venture with the musical, ''[[Dil Vil Pyar Vyar]]'' (2002), the success of his previous films helped him secure the [[Tamil Nadu State Film Award for Best Actor]] for 2002, being jointly recognised for both films.<ref name=\"awardstwo\">{{cite web|year=2004 |title=Tamil Nadu announces film awards for three years |publisher=Indiaglitz.com |accessdate=19 February 2011 |url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/10733.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20041024060415/http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/10733.html |archivedate=24 October 2004 }}</ref>\n\nMadhavan was cast alongside [[Kamal Haasan]] in ''[[Anbe Sivam]]'' (2003), which told the story of an unexpected journey from [[Bhubaneswar]] to [[Chennai]] of two men who are polar opposites. Madhavan revealed his elation at working with an experienced actor like Kamal Haasan, while noting that a human drama film like ''Anbe Sivam'' was important for his career as an actor as it came after a successful [[masala (film genre)|masala]] film in ''Run''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rediff.com/entertai/2002/apr/24priyan.htm |title=Movies: No regrets, No remakes: Priyadarshan |publisher=Rediff |date=24 April 2002 |accessdate=11 June 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160325133257/http://www.rediff.com/entertai/2002/apr/24priyan.htm |archivedate=25 March 2016 }}</ref> Portraying a young frustrated filmmaker with capitalist beliefs who travels with a handicapped communist played by Kamal Haasan, Madhavan's performance was described as a \"milestone in his career\" and that \"his portrayal will remain with the viewer for long\" by a critic from [[The Hindu]].<ref name=\"sivamhin\">{{cite news\n |author=Rangarajan, Malathi \n |year=2003 \n |title=Anbe Sivam \n |newspaper=[[The Hindu]] \n |accessdate=19 February 2011 \n |url=http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/fr/2003/01/17/stories/2003011701310200.htm \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110405073533/http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/fr/2003/01/17/stories/2003011701310200.htm \n |archivedate= 5 April 2011 \n}}</ref> The film opened in January 2003 to positive reviews, but became a surprise box-office failure. Post-release, the film has garnered belated critical acclaim from critics and television audiences and is considered as one of the \"cult classics\" of Tamil cinema.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://behindwoods.com/tamil-movies/slideshow/top-20-cult-movies-of-the-millennium/anbe-sivam.html |title=Anbe Sivam \u2013 TOP 20 CULT MOVIES OF THE MILLENNIUM |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160328062759/http://behindwoods.com/tamil-movies/slideshow/top-20-cult-movies-of-the-millennium/anbe-sivam.html |archivedate=28 March 2016 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-articles/Time-to-re-release-Kamals-classics-29-08-12.html |title=Time To Re Release Kamals Classics |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160328055858/http://behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-articles/Time-to-re-release-Kamals-classics-29-08-12.html |archivedate=28 March 2016 }}</ref> Film critic [[Baradwaj Rangan]] wrote that the film \"was leagues ahead of the average Tamil and Indian film\", though felt that \"the masses were unwilling to accept the experimental nature of the film\", while talking about the film's box office failure.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://baradwajrangan.wordpress.com/2003/03/02/anbe-sivam/ |title=Anbe Sivam |work=Baradwaj Rangan |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160313135826/https://baradwajrangan.wordpress.com/2003/03/02/anbe-sivam/ |archivedate=13 March 2016 |date=2 March 2003 }}</ref><ref name=\"sivam\">{{cite web|author=P. Devarajan |year=2004 |title=The World of Movies |work=[[The Hindu]] |accessdate=11 July 2004 |url=http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/2004/07/14/stories/2004071400272000.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160328061025/http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/2004/07/14/stories/2004071400272000.htm |archivedate=28 March 2016 }}</ref> Post-filming, Kamal Haasan revealed that he was impressed with Madhavan's enthusiasm and concentration during the making of the film and thus subsequently signed him on to appear in his production venture, ''[[Nala Damayanthi (2003 film)|Nala Damayanthi]]'' (2003), where he played a [[Brahmin]] cook lost in Australia. In 2003, the actor also appeared in [[Vikraman]]'s family drama ''[[Priyamana Thozhi]]'' as a budding [[cricketer]], [[Saran (director)|Saran]]'s romantic comedy ''[[Jay Jay]]'' and made a guest appearance in [[Priyadarshan]]'s ''[[Lesa Lesa]]'' as a jailed teacher. The three films made average returns at the box office, though Madhavan's performances were appreciated by critics.<ref name=\"twoflops\">{{cite web|author=Warrior, Sohbha |year=2003 |title=Target Dhanush! |publisher=[[Rediff]] |accessdate=6 August 2003 |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2003/aug/06kadhal.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20030815035836/http://www.rediff.com/movies/2003/aug/06kadhal.htm |archivedate=15 August 2003 }}</ref><ref name=\"ndreview\">{{cite web\n |year=2003 \n |title=Nala Damayanthi \n |publisher=[[Sify]] \n |accessdate=19 February 2011 \n |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/tamil/review.php?id=13169606&ctid=5&cid=2429 \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121019153936/http://www.sify.com/movies/tamil/review.php?id=13169606&ctid=5&cid=2429 \n |archivedate=19 October 2012 \n}}</ref><ref name=\"jjreview\">{{cite news|author=Rangarajan, Malathi |year=2003 |title=Jay Jay |newspaper=[[The Hindu]] |accessdate=19 February 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/fr/2003/11/21/stories/2003112101090200.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120813043357/http://www.hindu.com/fr/2003/11/21/stories/2003112101090200.htm |archivedate=13 August 2012 }}</ref>\n\n===2004\u20132008===\nMadhavan played an imposter gangster in [[K. S. Ravikumar]]'s comedy ''[[Aethiree]]'' (2004) before being selected to feature in his fourth Mani Ratnam production, ''[[Aaytha Ezhuthu]]'' (2004), which featured him in an ensemble cast including [[Suriya]], [[Siddharth (actor)|Siddharth]], [[Meera Jasmine]], [[Esha Deol]] and [[Trisha (actress)|Trisha]]. Madhavan portrayed the character of Inba Sekhar, a hitman living in the slums of [[Chennai]], whose path crosses with the characters portrayed by Suriya and Siddharth. His role also featured him in a struggling marriage, where his wife desperately tries to claw him away from his profession. Madhavan bulked up and sported a shaven look for the first time in his career to resemble the character of a ruffian and shot for the film through the sync sound technique.<ref name=\"aayutha\">{{cite web\n |author=Indiaglitz \n |year=2004 \n |title=Chat with Surya and Madhavan on Ayudha Ezhuthu \n |publisher=Indiaglitz.com \n |accessdate=8 July 2004 \n |url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/interview/6078.html \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20041024114852/http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/interview/6078.html \n |archivedate=24 October 2004 \n}}</ref> He received widespread praise for his depiction, with Baradwaj Rangan of The Hindu claiming that Madhavan outplayed [[Abhishek Bachchan]]'s interpretation of the character in the Hindi version of the bilingual, ''[[Yuva]]''.<ref name=\"ezhuthu\">{{cite web|author=Rangan, Baradwaj |year=2004 |title=Aayutha Ezhuthu / Yuva |work=[[The Hindu]] |accessdate=24 May 2004 |url=http://www.spicevienna.org/showMovieReviews.php?m=1967 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070927213534/http://www.spicevienna.org/showMovieReviews.php?m=1967 |archivedate=27 September 2007 }}</ref> Madhavan went on to win the [[Filmfare Best Supporting Actor Award (Tamil)|Filmfare Award for the Best Tamil Supporting Actor]], whilst another critic from The Hindu cited that he \"sparkles as an anti-hero\" and that the \"character ought to find a very special place in his repertoire\".<ref name=\"aereview\">{{cite news\n |author=Rangarajan, Malathi \n |year=2004 \n |title=Aayudha Ezhuthu \n |newspaper=[[The Hindu]] \n |accessdate=19 February 2011 \n |url=http://www.hindu.com/fr/2004/05/28/stories/2004052801670300.htm \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060117100941/http://www.hindu.com/fr/2004/05/28/stories/2004052801670300.htm \n |archivedate=17 January 2006 \n}}</ref> Similarly, a critic from Indiaglitz.com stated \"Madhavan's daring decision to play a negative character, who gets beaten up black and blue at the end, putting his 'hero' image in peril, has paid off, as he walks away with top honours\", while a reviewer from Sify.com labelled him as \"terrific\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/aayitha-ezhuthu-review-tamil-pclv3nffafibh.html |title=Review : Aayitha Ezhuthu |work=Sify |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170309065210/http://www.sify.com/movies/aayitha-ezhuthu-review-tamil-pclv3nffafibh.html |archivedate= 9 March 2017 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/ayutha-ezhuthu-tamil-movie-review-7034.html |title=Ayutha Ezhuthu review. Ayutha Ezhuthu Tamil movie review, story, rating |work=IndiaGlitz |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151212182602/http://www.indiaglitz.com/ayutha-ezhuthu-tamil-movie-review-7034.html |archivedate=12 December 2015 }}</ref> In late 2004, Madhavan worked on [[Rajiv Anchal]]'s English-Malayalam crossover film ''[[Nothing But Life]]'' (2005) and completed his work in a single schedule across [[Las Vegas Valley|Las Vegas]] and [[Albuquerque]]. Portraying an orphaned youth with suicidal tendencies being treated by a Malayali psychiatrist in the USA, the film and his portrayal opened to mixed reviews.<ref name=\"top10review\">{{cite web\n |author=George, Sanu \n |year=2004 \n |title=Nothing but Life \n |publisher=Nowrunning.com \n |accessdate=19 February 2011 \n |url=http://www.nowrunning.com/movie/2234/malayalam/made-in-usa/484/review.htm \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110714203554/http://www.nowrunning.com/movie/2234/malayalam/made-in-usa/484/review.htm \n |archivedate=14 July 2011 \n}}</ref><ref name=\"innbl\">{{cite web\n |year=2005 \n |title=Made in USA \u2013 Leaves audiences confused \n |publisher=Indiaglitz.com \n |accessdate=19 February 2011 \n |url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/malayalam/review/7594.html \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110613235027/http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/malayalam/review/7594.html \n |archivedate=13 June 2011 \n}}</ref> He then appeared in another marriage drama film, ''[[Priyasakhi]]'' (2005) co-starring [[Sadha]] \u2013 with the pair playing an estranged husband and wife. The film received praise for the lead pair's performances with Madhavan being praised as \"top class\", while it also became the first [[Tamil language|Tamil]] film to be dubbed into [[Zulu language|Zulu]].<ref name=\"zulu\">{{cite news\n |author=Rajendran Govinder \n |title=Promoting South Africa for film shooting \n |work=[[The Hindu]] \n |accessdate=1 January 2006 \n |url=http://www.hindu.com/2006/01/01/stories/2006010114930200.htm \n |location=Chennai, India \n |date=1 January 2006 |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060304023046/http://www.hindu.com/2006/01/01/stories/2006010114930200.htm \n |archivedate= 4 March 2006 \n}}</ref><ref name=\"psreview\">{{cite web\n |year=2005 \n |title=Priyasakhi \n |publisher=[[Sify]] \n |accessdate=19 February 2011 \n |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/tamil/review.php?id=13901321&ctid=5&cid=2429 \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121019154027/http://www.sify.com/movies/tamil/review.php?id=13901321&ctid=5&cid=2429 \n |archivedate=19 October 2012 \n}}</ref>\n\nFrom 2005 onwards, Madhavan increased his work in Hindi films and starred and wrote the Hindi dialogues for the comedy ''[[Ramji Londonwaley]]'' (2005), a remake of his earlier film ''Nala Damayanthi''. Critics described his performance as \"a master stroke\", though the film fared averagely at the box office due to the release of other big budget films during the period.<ref name=\"rlreview\">{{cite web\n |author=Adarsh, Taran \n |year=2005 \n |title=Ramji Londonwaley \n |publisher=[[Bollywood Hungama]] \n |accessdate=19 February 2011 \n |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/review/12464/index.html \n |authorlink=Taran Adarsh \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100628191520/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/review/12464/index.html \n |archivedate=28 June 2010 \n}}</ref> He experienced box office success in Hindi films for the first time through his role in [[Rakeysh Omprakash Mehra]]'s ''[[Rang De Basanti]]'' (2006). Featuring in an ensemble cast led by [[Aamir Khan]], Madhavan essayed the guest role of [[flight lieutenant]], whose death triggers a revolutionary movement against corruption.<ref name=\"cadet\"/> The film was subsequently nominated for the [[BAFTA Award for Best Foreign Film|Best Foreign Language Film]] at the 2006 [[British Academy of Film and Television Arts|BAFTA Awards]], while it was also chosen as India's official entry for the [[Golden Globe Award]]s and the [[List of submissions to the 79th Academy Awards for Best Foreign Language Film|Academy Awards]] for the Best Foreign Language Film category. Madhavan then collaborated with Mani Ratnam for the fifth time in the biopic ''[[Guru (2007 film)|Guru]]'' (2007), co-starring [[Abhishek Bachchan]], [[Aishwarya Rai]] and [[Vidya Balan]]. His role of Shyam Saxena was inspired from the life of real-life journalist [[S. Gurumurthy]], who was a challenger to the business tycoon, [[Dhirubhai Ambani]], whose life drew allusions with Bachchan's role. The film became a blockbuster and also received critical acclaim, with a reviewer citing that Madhavan acts with \"extreme, believable sincerity\" dubbing him as \"truly a poster boy for India\", whilst another claimed he performed \"a weak role with \u00e9lan\".<ref name=\"gurureview\">{{cite web\n |author=Adarsh, Taran \n |year=2007 \n |title=Guru \n |publisher=[[Bollywood Hungama]] \n |accessdate=19 February 2011 \n |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/review/12838/index.html \n |authorlink=Taran Adarsh \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110528115018/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/review/12838/index.html \n |archivedate=28 May 2011 \n}}</ref><ref name=\"gurureviewsen\">{{cite web|author=Sen, Raja |year=2007 |title=Watch Guru for the actors |publisher=[[Rediff]] |accessdate=19 February 2011 |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2007/jan/12guru.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110123022904/http://www.rediff.com/movies/2007/jan/12guru.htm |archivedate=23 January 2011 }}</ref>\n\nHis Tamil film, ''[[Thambi (2006 film)|Thambi]]'' (2006) directed by [[Seeman (director)|Seeman]], had a delayed release but became a profitable venture in town and village centres.<ref name=\"thambirediff\">{{cite web\n |author=Shobha Warrior \n |year=2006 \n |title=I never sign a film for acceptance \n |publisher=[[Rediff]] \n |accessdate=21 November 2006 \n |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2006/nov/21madhavan.htm \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20061208202346/http://www.rediff.com/movies/2006/nov/21madhavan.htm \n |archivedate= 8 December 2006 \n}}</ref> Madhavan's portrayal of a rustic do-gooder, received positive reviews from critics though a reviewer from The Hindu claimed the actor was \"unable to shed off his classy looks\".<ref name=\"thambibad\">{{cite web\n |author=Malathi Ranganathan \n |year=2006 \n |title=The agenda is new \n |work=[[The Hindu]] \n |accessdate=24 February 2006 \n |url=http://hindujobs.com/thehindu/fr/2006/02/24/stories/2006022400240200.htm \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070926233843/http://hindujobs.com/thehindu/fr/2006/02/24/stories/2006022400240200.htm \n |archivedate=26 September 2007 \n}}</ref><ref name=\"thambigood\">{{cite web \n |author=AllIndianSite \n |year=2006 \n |title=Movie:Thambi \n |publisher=AllIndianSite \n |accessdate=22 February 2006 \n |url=http://kollywood.allindiansite.com/thambi.html \n |url-status=dead \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060409043301/http://kollywood.allindiansite.com/thambi.html \n |archivedate=9 April 2006 \n }}</ref> He then appeared in [[Sundar C]]'s comedy film ''[[Rendu]]'' (2006), where he played dual roles for the first time and in the long-delayed romantic comedy ''[[Arya (2007 film)|Aarya]]'' (2007), appearing as a medical student.<ref name=\"aryareview\">{{cite web|year=2007 |title=Arya Movie Review |publisher=Behindwoods |accessdate=19 February 2011 |url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-articles/movies-06/arya-review.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110504050217/http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-articles/movies-06/arya-review.html |archivedate= 4 May 2011 }}</ref> Madhavan wrote the dialogues, produced and featured in the lead role in [[Nishikanth Kamat]]'s ''[[Evano Oruvan]]'' (2007), playing a middle class bank employee who becomes so disgusted with the corruption he faces in his day-to-day life that he becomes a vigilante. After setting up a production studio, Leukos Films, he helped promote the film in international film festivals{{which|date=January 2020}} before the theatrical release in December 2007.<ref name=\"eoprom\">{{cite news|title=Madhavan's \"Evano Oruvan\" to be screened in America, Middle East |work=[[The Hindu]] |accessdate=19 February 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/holnus/009200710041878.htm |location=Chennai, India |date=4 October 2007 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110629024839/http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/holnus/009200710041878.htm |archivedate=29 June 2011 }}</ref><ref name=\"eopromtwo\">{{cite news|author=Malarvizhi, J. |title='Evano Oruvan' to premiere abroad |work=[[The Hindu]] |accessdate=19 February 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/2007/10/06/stories/2007100650060200.htm |location=Chennai, India |date=6 October 2007 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110109121111/http://www.hindu.com/2007/10/06/stories/2007100650060200.htm |archivedate= 9 January 2011 }}</ref> Critics called the film a \"must watch\" and a reviewer from [[The Hindu]] stated that the film was \"Madhavan's best performance to date\", while he also went on to win the [[ITFA Best Actor Award]] for his depiction.<ref name=\"eoreviews\">{{cite news|author=Kamath, Sudhish |title=Maddy vs Baddies |work=[[The Hindu]] |accessdate=15 December 2007 |url=http://www.hindu.com/mp/2007/12/15/stories/2007121550330300.htm |location=Chennai,India |date=15 December 2007 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071223093245/http://www.hindu.com/mp/2007/12/15/stories/2007121550330300.htm |archivedate=23 December 2007 }}</ref><ref name=\"eoreview2\">{{cite web|author=Srinivasan, Pavithra |year=2007 |title=Evano Oruvan, a must-watch |publisher=[[Rediff]] |accessdate=15 December 2007 |url=http://inhome.rediff.com/movies/2007/dec/07evan.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071209182848/http://inhome.rediff.com/movies/2007/dec/07evan.htm |archivedate= 9 December 2007 }}</ref> However ''Evano Oruvan'' and his subsequent release, Seeman's ''[[Vaazhthukal]]'' (2008) did not perform well at the box office, while another completed film titled ''[[Naan Aval Adhu]]'' failed to have a theatrical release.<ref name=\"vrreview2\">{{cite web|year=2007 |title=Vaazhthukkal Review |publisher=Behindwoods |accessdate=20 February 2011 |url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-reviews/reviews-1/vazhthukal-review.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110707222741/http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-reviews/reviews-1/vazhthukal-review.html |archivedate= 7 July 2011 }}</ref> Madhavan's final release of the year was the docudrama ''[[Mumbai Meri Jaan]]'', based upon the [[2006 Mumbai Bombings]]. The film, which featured him alongside [[Soha Ali Khan]], [[Irrfan Khan]] and [[Kay Kay Menon]] became critically acclaimed with Madhavan's portrayal of a man with a post-traumatic stress disorder being appreciated by reviewers.<ref name=\"mmjreview2\">{{cite web|author=Ramani, Nithya |year=2008 |title=Agony revisited |publisher=[[Rediff]] |accessdate=20 February 2011 |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2008/aug/22mumbai.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110315092123/http://www.rediff.com/movies/2008/aug/22mumbai.htm |archivedate=15 March 2011 }}</ref><ref name=\"mmjreview\">{{cite web\n |author=Adarsh, Taran \n |year=2008 \n |title=Mumbai Meri Jaan \n |publisher=[[Bollywood Hungama]] \n |accessdate=19 February 2011 \n |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/review/13809/index.html \n |authorlink=Taran Adarsh \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100920103054/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/review/13809/index.html \n |archivedate=20 September 2010 \n}}</ref>\n\n===2009\u20132014===\n[[File:Kangna Ranaut and R Madhavan promote 'Tanu Weds Manu' on Jhalak Dikhhla Jaa sets.jpg|thumb|right|upright=0.9|alt=Kangana Ranaut and R. Madhavan pose for the camera|Madhavan with co-star [[Kangana Ranaut]] at a promotional event for ''[[Tanu Weds Manu]]'', 2011]] \nMadhavan won positive acclaim for playing the lead role of an engineer experiencing eerie events in Vikram Kumar's bilingual horror film, ''[[Yavarum Nalam]]'' (2009). The film, which became a commercial and critical success, prompted a reviewer from the [[Times of India]] to suggest \"he carried the film on his shoulders\" while he was also nominated in the [[Vijay Award for Best Actor|Best Actor]] category at the [[Vijay Awards]].<ref name=\"ynreviews\">{{cite news\n |author=Bhama, Deva Ravi \n |year=2009 \n |title=Yavarum Nalam \n |work=[[The Times of India]] \n |accessdate=6 March 2009 \n |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/Tamil/Yavarum-nalam/articleshow/4234468.cms \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090310141129/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/Tamil/Yavarum-nalam/articleshow/4234468.cms \n |archivedate=10 March 2009 \n}}</ref> His following two films, the romantic comedy ''[[Guru En Aalu]]'' (2009) and the action film ''[[Sikandar (2009 film)|Sikandar]]'' (2009) in which he played a supporting role of an army officer, both fetched mixed reviews. Madhavan then portrayed one of three leading roles in [[Rajkumar Hirani]]'s [[coming of age film|coming of age]] [[comedy film|comedy]]-[[Drama (film and television)|drama film]], ''[[3 Idiots]]'' (2009), alongside [[Aamir Khan]] and [[Sharman Joshi]]. Upon release, the film received positive reviews and went on to become the highest-grossing Indian film of all time, before being overtaken in 2013.<ref name=overseas>{{cite web|title=Three Idiots Creates History in China |url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/boxnewsdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=3866&nCat= |work=30 December 2011 |publisher=BoxOfficeIndia. Com |accessdate=30 December 2011 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120107201817/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/boxnewsdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=3866&nCat= |archivedate= 7 January 2012 }}</ref> Madhavan's portrayal as a young engineer with a passion for photography earned him nominations for the [[Filmfare Award for Best Supporting Actor]] and for the [[IIFA Best Supporting Actor Award]] during 2010. Film critic [[Taran Adarsh]] from [[Bollywood Hungama]] described the actor's performance as \"incredible\", while Madhavan claimed that the film changed how he was viewed as an actor in Hindi films for the better.<ref name=\"tireview\">{{cite web|author=Adarsh, Taran |year=2009 |title=3 Idiots |publisher=[[Bollywood Hungama]] |accessdate=19 February 2011 |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/review/13910/index.html |authorlink=Taran Adarsh |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101104160008/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/review/13910/index.html |archivedate= 4 November 2010 }}</ref><ref name=\"ticahneg\">{{cite web|author=Ashraf, Syed |year=2010 |title=How 3 Idiots changed Madhavan's life |publisher=[[Rediff]] |accessdate=19 February 2011 |url=http://movies.rediff.com/slide-show/2010/jan/11/slide-show-1-madhavan-on-three-idiots.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110415133429/http://movies.rediff.com/slide-show/2010/jan/11/slide-show-1-madhavan-on-three-idiots.htm |archivedate=15 April 2011 }}</ref> He later turned down an offer of reprising the same role in the Tamil remake of the film helmed by [[S. Shankar|Shankar]]. In 2010, Madhavan appeared alongside actors [[Amitabh Bachchan]] and [[Ben Kingsley]] in ''[[Teen Patti (film)|Teen Patti]]'' (2010) as a young professor, with Adarsh again rating his performance as \"excellent\", but the film failed at the box office.<ref name=\"tpreview\">{{cite web\n |author=Adarsh, Taran \n |year=2010 \n |title=Teen Patti \n |publisher=[[Bollywood Hungama]] \n |accessdate=19 February 2011 \n |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/review/12995/index.html \n |authorlink=Taran Adarsh \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101230230731/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/review/12995/index.html \n |archivedate=30 December 2010 \n}}</ref><ref name=\"tpred\">{{cite web\n |author=Arora, Preeti \n |year=2010 \n |title=Teen Patti: Just one big bluff \n |publisher=[[Rediff]] \n |accessdate=19 February 2011 \n |url=http://movies.rediff.com/report/2010/feb/26/review-teen-patti.htm \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110430185119/http://movies.rediff.com/report/2010/feb/26/review-teen-patti.htm \n |archivedate=30 April 2011 \n}}</ref> His two guest appearances in the year also received mixed feedback with his performance in the Telugu anthology film ''[[Om Shanti]]'' (2010) being praised, whilst a role in the [[John Abraham (actor)|John Abraham]]-starrer ''[[Jhootha Hi Sahi]]'' (2010) drew him criticism.<ref name=\"jhsreview\">{{cite web\n |author=Adarsh, Taran \n |year=2010 \n |title=Jhootha Hi Sahi \n |publisher=[[Bollywood Hungama]] \n |accessdate=19 February 2011 \n |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/review/14072/index.html \n |authorlink=Taran Adarsh \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110223234544/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/review/14072/index.html \n |archivedate=23 February 2011 \n}}</ref><ref name=\"osid\">{{cite web\n |author=Jeevi \n |year=2010 \n |title=Om Shanti Film Review \n |publisher=Idlebrain.com \n |accessdate=19 February 2011 \n |url=http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/archive/mr-omshanti.html \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110713002932/http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/archive/mr-omshanti.html \n |archivedate=13 July 2011 \n}}</ref> Madhavan then collaborated again with [[Kamal Haasan]] and [[K. S. Ravikumar]] in the romantic comedy, ''[[Manmadan Ambu]]'' (2010), playing a wealthy businessman who hires a spy to follow his actress girlfriend on a European cruise tour. The film opened to positive reviews with Madhavan's performance being described by [[Rediff]].com as \"excellent\", while [[Sify]].com labelled him the \"scene stealer\".<ref name=\"mmareview\">{{cite web\n |year=2010 \n |title=Manmadan Ambu \n |publisher=[[Sify]] \n |accessdate=19 February 2011 \n |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/tamil/review.php?id=14959566&ctid=5&cid=2429 \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110121202419/http://www.sify.com/movies/tamil/review.php?id=14959566&ctid=5&cid=2429 \n |archivedate=21 January 2011 \n}}</ref><ref name=\"rediffmmaed\">{{cite web\n |author=Srinivasan, Pavithra \n |year=2010 \n |title=Kamal Haasan delivers with Manmadhan Ambu \n |publisher=[[Rediff]] \n |accessdate=19 February 2011 \n |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/review/south-review-of-manmadhan-ambu/20101223.htm \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110208035731/http://www.rediff.com/movies/review/south-review-of-manmadhan-ambu/20101223.htm \n |archivedate= 8 February 2011 \n}}</ref>\n\nHis only release in 2011 was the romantic drama film, ''[[Tanu Weds Manu]]'' alongside [[Kangana Ranaut]], which saw him play the role of a sensible doctor hoping to get an arranged marriage with a girl, who has a dramatically diverse personality to him. Prior to release, the film's promotional campaign created anticipation and upon release, the film became a large success at the box office. Madhavan's portrayal of Manoj \"Manu\" Sharma won positive acclaim, with a reviewer citing that his performance was \"real, restrained, yet forceful\" and another claiming he was \"perfectly cast\".<ref name=\"twmreview\">{{cite web\n |author=Adarsh, Taran \n |year=2011 \n |title=Tanu Weds Manu \n |publisher=[[Bollywood Hungama]] \n |accessdate=19 February 2011 \n |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/review/14135/index.html \n |authorlink=Taran Adarsh \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110228024645/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/review/14135/index.html \n |archivedate=28 February 2011 \n}}</ref><ref name=\"redifftwm\">{{cite web|author=Verma, Sukanya |year=2011 |title=Review: Tanu Weds Manu is charming |publisher=[[Rediff]] |accessdate=19 February 2011 |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/review/review-tanu-weds-manu/20110225.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110227134744/http://www.rediff.com/movies/review/review-tanu-weds-manu/20110225.htm |archivedate=27 February 2011 }}</ref> Madhavan next appeared as a police officer in [[N. Linguswamy|Linguswamy]]'s Tamil film ''[[Vettai]]'' (2012), an action entertainer featuring an ensemble cast of [[Arya (actor)|Arya]], [[Amala Paul]] and [[Sameera Reddy]]. The film opened to positive reviews in January 2012 and went on to become a commercial success, with critics praising Madhavan's decision to accept the role of a timid cop, while a critic noted that he had \"an uncanny talent for comedy\".<ref name=\"adhir\">{{cite news\n |title=Vettai: Review \n |work=[[The Times of India]] \n |accessdate=13 July 2012 \n |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/articlelist/movie-review/11496445.cms \n |date=19 October 2010 |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120120012238/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/articlelist/movie-review/11496445.cms \n |archivedate=20 January 2012 \n}}</ref><ref name=\"vettai\">{{cite news\n |author=Dutt, Purbha \n |title=Vettai's story blew me away:Madhavan \n |work=[[The Times of India]] \n |accessdate=19 February 2011 \n |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/regional/news-interviews/Vettais-story-blew-me-away-Madhavan/articleshow/6741515.cms \n |date=14 October 2010 |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101023065238/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/regional/news-interviews/Vettais-story-blew-me-away-Madhavan/articleshow/6741515.cms \n |archivedate=23 October 2010 \n}}</ref> He then featured in ''[[Jodi Breakers]]'' (2012), a Hindi romantic comedy film shot in [[Greece]] alongside [[Bipasha Basu]], though the film did not perform well commercially.<ref name=\"sff\">{{cite web | url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/channels/showbiz/bollywood/bipasha-and-madhavan-romance-greece-645 | title=Bipasha and Madhavan to romance in Greece | work=[[Deccan Chronicle]] | date=10 August 2011 | accessdate=19 February 2011 | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121011171507/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/channels/showbiz/bollywood/bipasha-and-madhavan-romance-greece-645 | archivedate=11 October 2012}}</ref> In 2012, Madhavan took a sabbatical and was based in Chicago resting his knee, which he injured during the making of ''Vettai'', causing him to suffer from [[chondromalacia patellae]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Madhavan heads to Chicago for rest! |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/madhavan-heads-to-chicago-for-rest-news-tamil-md1nloideda.html |work=Sify |accessdate=6 August 2013 |date=27 March 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131008111433/http://www.sify.com/movies/madhavan-heads-to-chicago-for-rest-news-tamil-md1nloideda.html |archivedate= 8 October 2013 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Madhavan to take a sabbatical |url=http://archive.asianage.com/bollywood/madhavan-take-sabbatical-231 |work=[[Asian Age]] |accessdate=6 August 2013 |date=13 February 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130806050025/http://archive.asianage.com/bollywood/madhavan-take-sabbatical-231 |archivedate= 6 August 2013 }}</ref> During the period, he felt he had to \"reinvent himself\" and had to work on films which would appeal to the \"new generation of audiences\", so took a decision to work on a single film at a time.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-i-became-boring-and-fat-r-madhavan-2086435 |title=I became boring and fat: R Madhavan |date=17 May 2015 |work=dna |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160313223025/http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-i-became-boring-and-fat-r-madhavan-2086435 |archivedate=13 March 2016 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/R-Madhavan-I-realised-that-I-had-become-a-terrible-actor/articleshow/46727030.cms |title=R Madhavan: I realised that I had become a terrible actor |work=The Times of India |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150401161122/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/R-Madhavan-I-realised-that-I-had-become-a-terrible-actor/articleshow/46727030.cms |archivedate= 1 April 2015 }}</ref> During a period of three years without any theatrical releases, his long-delayed Hindi film ''[[Sunglass (film)|Taak Jhaank]]'' directed by [[Rituparno Ghosh]] in 2006, premi\u00e8red at the 19th Kolkata International Film Festival in 2013, while his first Hindi film ''[[Akeli (film)|Akeli]]'', shot in 1997, was released online during the following year. During his recovery period and sabbatical in 2013, Madhavan signed on to appear in [[Simon West]]'s ''[[Night of the Living Dead: Darkest Dawn]]'', in which he appeared as a former marine personnel and shot for the project in California.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/hollywood-ho/article5179154.ece |title=Hollywood Ho! |author=Harshikaa Udasi |newspaper=The Hindu |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140317115008/http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/hollywood-ho/article5179154.ece |archivedate=17 March 2014 |date=28 September 2013 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=R Madhavan bags a Hollywood movie|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-07-28/news-interviews/40833799_1_madhavan-film-tomb-raider|work=The Times of India|accessdate=1 August 2013|date=28 July 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130801200039/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-07-28/news-interviews/40833799_1_madhavan-film-tomb-raider|archive-date=1 August 2013|url-status=live}}</ref> The [[computer animation|computer animated]] film, where Madhavan provided voice work, premi\u00e8red in San Diego during July 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jobsnhire.com/articles/26828/20150908/night-of-the-living-dead-remake-news-cg-movie-animated-retelling-1968-george-romero-classic.htm |title='Night of the Living Dead' Remake [NEWS]: A CG Movie? Animated Retelling of the 1968 George Romero Classic Disappoints Fans |publisher=Jobsnhire.com |date=8 September 2015 |accessdate=6 January 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160106163041/http://www.jobsnhire.com/articles/26828/20150908/night-of-the-living-dead-remake-news-cg-movie-animated-retelling-1968-george-romero-classic.htm |archivedate= 6 January 2016 }}</ref>\n\n===2015\u20132017===\nMadhavan's first theatrical release after his sabbatical was [[Anand L. Rai]]'s ''[[Tanu Weds Manu Returns]]'', a sequel to the 2011 film, which released in May 2015. Prior to the film's release, Madhavan stated that the \"content of the film was more important than the stars\" and acknowledged that the popularity of [[Kangana Ranaut]] would help the film gain a good opening at the box office.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/i-will-definitely-be-overshadowed-by-kangana-ranaut-in-tanu-weds-manu-returns-madhvan/story-wl0GSjk1uqJbIf08uxHn4N.html |title=I will definitely be overshadowed by Kangana Ranaut in Tanu Weds Manu Returns: Madhvan |work=hindustantimes.com/ |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160224054102/http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/i-will-definitely-be-overshadowed-by-kangana-ranaut-in-tanu-weds-manu-returns-madhvan/story-wl0GSjk1uqJbIf08uxHn4N.html |archivedate=24 February 2016 |date=15 May 2015 }}</ref> Reprising his role as Manu, Madhavan won acclaim for his restrained performance and the film went on to become a critical and commercial success.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/interview/madhavan-my-character-in-tanu-weds-manu-returns-has-a-lot-of-flaws/20150601.htm |title=Madhavan: My character in Tanu Weds Manu Returns has a lot of flaws |date=1 June 2015 |work=Rediff |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160229235833/http://www.rediff.com/movies/interview/madhavan-my-character-in-tanu-weds-manu-returns-has-a-lot-of-flaws/20150601.htm |archivedate=29 February 2016 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/madhavan-interview-maddy-returns-as-manu/article7213988.ece|title=Madhavan interview: Maddy returns as Manu|author=Archita Kashyap|newspaper=The Hindu|accessdate=16 February 2016|date=16 May 2015}}</ref> The critic from [[Bollywood Hungama]] wrote \"Madhavan excels in his role despite it being a restrained one, which was anyways the call of his character\" and added \"he is very endearing who never tries to overshadow anyone and emerges a winner\", while Sify.com stated he gives a \"subtle and restrained performance\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/moviemicro/criticreview/id/547997 |title=Tanu Weds Manu Returns |author=Bollywood Hungama |date=21 May 2015 |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160214194525/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/moviemicro/criticreview/id/547997 |archivedate=14 February 2016 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/kangana-s-dual-magic-in-tanu-weds-manu-returns-review-bollywood-pfwsrrbidbhgj.html |title=Review : Kangana's dual magic in 'Tanu Weds Manu Returns' |work=Sify |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160213143245/http://www.sify.com/movies/kangana-s-dual-magic-in-tanu-weds-manu-returns-review-bollywood-pfwsrrbidbhgj.html |archivedate=13 February 2016 }}</ref> ''Tanu Weds Manu Returns'' earned {{INRConvert|2.43|b}} worldwide at the end of its theatrical run, to become one of the [[List of highest-grossing Bollywood films|highest-grossing Bollywood films]] in 2015.<ref name=\"2.40&nbsp;billion\">{{cite web|url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/Details/art_detail/willthemegasuccessofbaahubalihitbajrangibhaijaanaseveninnorthindiaitsablockbuster|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150716171244/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/Details/art_detail/willthemegasuccessofbaahubalihitbajrangibhaijaanaseveninnorthindiaitsablockbuster|archivedate=16 July 2015|title=Will The Mega Success Of Baahubali Hit Bajrangi Bhaijaan As Even in North India Its A Blockbuster?}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/Details/art_detail/tanuwedsmanureturnsheadsfor225crworldwide|title=Tanu Weds Manu Returns Heads For 225 Cr Worldwide|accessdate=2 June 2015|publisher=Box Office India|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150626133220/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/Details/art_detail/tanuwedsmanureturnsheadsfor225crworldwide|archivedate=26 June 2015}}</ref>\n\nDuring his sabbatical, Madhavan also worked extensively on the pre-production of the bilingual sports film, ''[[Irudhi Suttru]]'' (2016) directed by [[Sudha Kongara Prasad|Sudha Kongara]]. After being impressed with Sudha's script, he helped find the project producers in Tamil and chose to produce the film in Hindi alongside [[Y NOT Studios|Sashikanth]] and [[Rajkumar Hirani]]. Madhavan also met and convinced [[mixed martial arts|mixed martial artist]] Ritika Singh to act in the film after contacting her through [[Raj Kundra]], while he was also credited for contributing as an additional screenplay writer. He also went through a body conditioning regime in Los Angeles prior to joining the film's set and learnt boxing to essay the role of a former boxer.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/features/type/view/id/9665 |title=I knew that Saala Khadoos is a film that would change my image \u2013 Madhavan \u2013 Latest Movie Features \u2013 Bollywood Hungama |author=Bollywood Hungama |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160215082742/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/features/type/view/id/9665 |archivedate=15 February 2016 }}</ref> For dubbing purposes, Madhavan wore metal braces inside his teeth, to create the effect of having a lisp that most boxers have from sporting injuries.<ref name=\"nie\">{{cite web|author=Manigandan K R |url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/tamil/Get-Ready-for-Maddys-Punch-in-Irudhi-Suttru/2016/01/05/article3211513.ece |title=Get Ready for Maddy's Punch in Irudhi Suttru |work=The New Indian Express |date=5 January 2016 |accessdate=28 January 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160204102959/http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/tamil/Get-Ready-for-Maddys-Punch-in-Irudhi-Suttru/2016/01/05/article3211513.ece |archivedate= 4 February 2016 }}</ref> Madhavan won praise for his work during the marketing campaign, having travelled throughout [[Tamil Nadu]] to promote the film, with [[The Hindu]] stating it was \"unlike other film promotions in the South\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/madhavan%E2%80%99s-aggressive-promotions-for-irudhi-suttru-news-tamil-qbgkC2aijgeae.html |title=Madhavan's aggressive promotions for 'Irudhi Suttru' |publisher=Sify.com |accessdate=28 January 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160128210200/http://www.sify.com/movies/madhavan%E2%80%99s-aggressive-promotions-for-irudhi-suttru-news-tamil-qbgkC2aijgeae.html |archivedate=28 January 2016 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-metroplus/a-gentleman-and-an-actor/article8074042.ece |title=A gentleman and an actor \u2013 Madurai |work=The Hindu |date=7 January 2016 |accessdate=28 January 2016}}</ref> For ''Irudhi Suttru'', Madhavan received widespread critical acclaim for his portrayal with Sify.com stating \"he is outstanding and carries the proverbial burden of the project on his shoulder\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/irudhi-suttru-review-tamil-qb3kkffigibjj.html |title=Review : Irudhi Suttru review |publisher=Sify.com |accessdate=20 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160224002933/http://www.sify.com/movies/irudhi-suttru-review-tamil-qb3kkffigibjj.html |archivedate=24 February 2016 }}</ref> A critic from [[The Hindu]] stated that he was \"quietly effective\", while a reviewer from Behindwoods.com wrote that Madhavan gives his \"best performance\" and is \"excellent\" at depicting his \"characterization from being subtle to being outright effervescent\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies/irudhi-suttru/irudhi-suttru-review.html |title=Irudhi Suttru (aka) Iruthi Suttru review |work=Behindwoods |publisher=Behindwoods Review Board |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160222140031/http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies/irudhi-suttru/irudhi-suttru-review.html |archivedate=22 February 2016 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/cinema-reviews/irudhi-suttru-a-heartwarming-boxing-drama/article8171346.ece |title=Irudhi Suttru: A heart-warming boxing drama |author=Baradwaj Rangan |work=The Hindu |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160131084418/http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/cinema-reviews/irudhi-suttru-a-heartwarming-boxing-drama/article8171346.ece |archivedate=31 January 2016 }}</ref> His portrayal in the Hindi version, ''Saala Khadoos'', received similar praise with critic [[Subhash K. Jha]] stating \"this is Madhavan's career-defining performance, he sinks so deep into his role both physically and emotionally, that the actor becomes one with the act\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.firstpost.com/bollywood/saala-khadoos-review-madhavan-delivers-knockout-performance-in-an-ultimately-lightweight-film-2603040.html |title=Saala Khadoos review: A decent film brought to life by Madhavan's knockout performance |work=Firstpost |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160202035646/http://www.firstpost.com/bollywood/saala-khadoos-review-madhavan-delivers-knockout-performance-in-an-ultimately-lightweight-film-2603040.html |archivedate= 2 February 2016 }}</ref>\n\nHe next featured in ''[[Vikram Vedha]]'' (2017), an action thriller film directed by duo [[Pushkar-Gayathri]] and produced by [[Y NOT Studios|Sashikanth]]. Telling the tale of an encounter cop and his pursuit of a gangster played by [[Vijay Sethupathi]], Pushkar-Gayathri scripted the film with inspiration from the [[Vikramaditya|Vikramathithan Vedhalam]] folk tale, with the characterisation of both lead roles derived from that plot.<ref>{{cite web |author=Karthik Kumar |url=http://www.thequint.com/entertainment/2016/02/15/after-boxing-coach-madhavan-to-play-an-encounter-specialist |title=After Boxing Coach, Madhavan to Play an Encounter Specialist |publisher=The Quint |date=15 February 2016 |accessdate=21 November 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161117211500/https://www.thequint.com/entertainment/2016/02/15/after-boxing-coach-madhavan-to-play-an-encounter-specialist |archive-date=17 November 2016 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/Vijay-Sethupathi-Madhavans-film-is-based-on-Vikramathithan-Vethalam/articleshow/51009766.cms |title=Vijay Sethupathi, Madhavan's film is based on Vikramathithan Vethalam |website=The Times of India |date=17 February 2016 |accessdate=21 November 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170725182631/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/Vijay-Sethupathi-Madhavans-film-is-based-on-Vikramathithan-Vethalam/articleshow/51009766.cms |archive-date=25 July 2017 |url-status=live }}</ref> For his role, Madhavan underwent arms training and met people involved with the police and defence forces.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mid-day.com/articles/madhavan-i-know-23-year-old-girls-lust-after-me/16950185 |title=Madhavan: I know 23-year-old girls lust after me |website=Mid-day.com |accessdate=21 November 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161117063256/http://www.mid-day.com/articles/madhavan-i-know-23-year-old-girls-lust-after-me/16950185 |archive-date=17 November 2016 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/kollywood/160216/madhavan-to-face-off-against-vijay-sethupathi.html |title=Madhavan to face off against Vijay Sethupathi |website=Deccan Chronicle |accessdate=21 November 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161117070252/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/kollywood/160216/madhavan-to-face-off-against-vijay-sethupathi.html |archive-date=17 November 2016 |url-status=live }}</ref> ''Vikram Vedha'' opened in July 2017 to critical acclaim and received widespread positive reports from the media and industry personnel.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/kollywood-lauds-vikram-vedha-news-tamil-rhyjNhbddffbb.html |title=Kollywood lauds 'Vikram Vedha' |publisher=Sify.com |accessdate=22 January 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180115121219/http://www.sify.com/movies/kollywood-lauds-vikram-vedha-news-tamil-rhyjNhbddffbb.html |archive-date=15 January 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> Madhavan's performance was widely appreciated by film critics, who described him as \"stylish and serious\" and \"whole-hearted\", while Sify.com's reviewer wrote it is a \"treat to watch two intense performers Madhavan and Vijay Sethupathi majestically own the screen together\".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/vikram-vedha-review-a-brilliantly-written-intense-crime-drama-review-tamil-rhvoN4jfgfbcc.html |title=Review : Vikram Vedha Review: A brilliantly written intense crime (2017) |publisher=Sify.com |date=21 July 2017 |accessdate=22 January 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180607170729/http://www.sify.com/movies/vikram-vedha-review-a-brilliantly-written-intense-crime-drama-review-tamil-rhvoN4jfgfbcc.html |archive-date=7 June 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/movie-reviews/220717/vikram-vedha-movie-review-a-simplistic-and-straightforward-affair.html |title=Vikram Vedha movie review: A simplistic and straightforward affair |work=Deccan Chronicle |accessdate=22 January 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171220021402/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/movie-reviews/220717/vikram-vedha-movie-review-a-simplistic-and-straightforward-affair.html |archive-date=20 December 2017 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movie-reviews/vikram-vedha/movie-review/59697165.cms |title=Vikram Vedha Review {3.5/5}: A playful action film with more intrigue and less intensity |work=The Times of India |date=21 July 2017 |accessdate=22 January 2018}}</ref> The film also became Madhavan's biggest commercial success in Tamil films, with trade pundits classifying the film as a \"blockbuster\".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bollywoodtrade.com/trade-news/vikram-vedha-becomes-r-madhavans-biggest-tamil-blockbuster/1703.htm |title=VIKRAM VEDHA becomes R Madhavan's biggest Tamil blockbuster! \u2013 Trade News |publisher=BollywoodTrade.com |date=17 August 2017 |accessdate=22 January 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170920191323/http://www.bollywoodtrade.com/trade-news/vikram-vedha-becomes-r-madhavans-biggest-tamil-blockbuster/1703.htm |archive-date=20 September 2017 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n===2018\u2013present===\nMadhavan next worked on a web series for Amazon titled ''[[Breathe (web series)|Breathe]]'', which was released in January 2018.<ref>{{cite web |author=Back to |url=http://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/r-madhavan-very-excited-about-vikram-vedha-its-one-of-the-best-films-of-my-career-3833305.html |title=R Madhavan: 'Very excited about Vikram Vedha, it's one of the best films of my career'- Entertainment News, Firstpost |publisher=Firstpost.com |accessdate=22 January 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180125151253/http://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/r-madhavan-very-excited-about-vikram-vedha-its-one-of-the-best-films-of-my-career-3833305.html |archive-date=25 January 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/actor-madhavan-makes-digital-debut-with-amazon-primes-breathe/article22470896.ece |title=Only 2% go to theatres, says actor Madhavan |work=The Hindu |date=20 June 2017 |accessdate=22 January 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180404192819/http://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/actor-madhavan-makes-digital-debut-with-amazon-primes-breathe/article22470896.ece |archive-date=4 April 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> Madhavan later revealed that he was initially sceptical of the web series format, but was \"totally blown away\" by the script of the series by Mayank Sharma and decided to accept to work on the project, despite his commitments for the shoot of ''Vikram Vedha''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/i-keep-meeting-people-who-think-its-the-end-of-the-road-for-me-madhavan/articleshow/62672775.cms|title=I keep meeting people who think it's the end of the road for me: Madhavan|website=The Times of India|access-date=28 January 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180128100431/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/i-keep-meeting-people-who-think-its-the-end-of-the-road-for-me-madhavan/articleshow/62672775.cms|archive-date=28 January 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/actor-madhavan-makes-digital-debut-with-amazon-primes-breathe/article22470896.ece|title=Only 2% go to theatres, says actor Madhavan|first=Vishal|last=Menon|date=19 January 2018|work=The Hindu|access-date=31 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180404192819/http://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/actor-madhavan-makes-digital-debut-with-amazon-primes-breathe/article22470896.ece|archive-date=4 April 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> For ''Breathe'', Madhavan studied his own experience as a father besides researching the complexities surrounding [[organ donation]]. In the series, he played Danny Mascarenhas, a soccer coach and the father of a young boy with cystic fibrosis, who will die in six months unless he has a lung transplant.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/arts/television/why-amazon-is-betting-on-indian-superstar-r-madhavan/article37732987/|title=Why Amazon is betting on Indian superstar R. Madhavan with its series Breathe|work=The Globe and Mail|access-date=28 January 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180128091858/https://www.theglobeandmail.com/arts/television/why-amazon-is-betting-on-indian-superstar-r-madhavan/article37732987/|archive-date=28 January 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Madhavan received positive reviews for his portrayal, with film critic [[Subhash K. Jha]] writing \"As Danny, Madhavan expresses grief, rage, frustration, guilt, repentance and self-destruction with measured excellence\" and that \"this is a showcase for an actor at the peak of his power\" and \"boy, does Madhavan embrace the opportunity\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://indianewengland.com/2018/01/review-breathe-amazon-gives-us-thriller-series-wont-let-us-breathe/|title=Review: Breathe: Amazon gives us a thriller series that won't let us breathe|date=27 January 2018|access-date=31 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190831091436/https://indianewengland.com/2018/01/review-breathe-amazon-gives-us-thriller-series-wont-let-us-breathe/|archive-date=31 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Similarly, a critic from the New Indian Express wrote \"Madhavan is in form in a potentially compelling thriller\", and a reviewer from the International Business Times wrote he \"shows a range of emotions\" in \"a smooth, beautiful way\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/web-series/madhavan-breathe-review-5039957/|title=Breathe first impression: Madhavan is in form in a potentially compelling thriller|date=26 January 2018|access-date=31 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190831091433/https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/web-series/madhavan-breathe-review-5039957/|archive-date=31 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/breathe-review-r-madhavan-amit-sadhs-brilliant-gripping-psychological-thriller-will-leave-you-758394|title=Breathe Review: R Madhavan, Amit Sadh's brilliant and gripping psychological thriller will leave you breathless|first=Chetna|last=Kapoor|date=26 January 2018|website=International Business Times, India Edition|access-date=31 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190831091432/https://www.ibtimes.co.in/breathe-review-r-madhavan-amit-sadhs-brilliant-gripping-psychological-thriller-will-leave-you-758394|archive-date=31 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nMadhavan's most recent release is ''[[Savyasachi (2018 film)|Savyasachi]]'' (2018), where he played his first full-length role in a Telugu film.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/r-madhavan-completes-schedule-of-savyasachi/articleshow/62097118.cms|title=R Madhavan completes schedule of 'Savyasachi'|website=The Times of India|access-date=28 January 2018|archive-url=https://archive.today/20180417085125/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/r-madhavan-completes-schedule-of-savyasachi/articleshow/62097118.cms|archive-date=17 April 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> He has also confirmed that he would work on ''Maara'' with debut filmmaker Dhilip Kumar, ''Silence'' by [[Kona Venkat]], and [[Rocketry: The Nambi Effect]], a biopic on rocket scientist [[Nambi Narayanan]] directed by himself.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/kollywood/150616/i-was-impressed-by-charlie-madhavan.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=18 June 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160618122932/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/kollywood/150616/i-was-impressed-by-charlie-madhavan.html |archivedate=18 June 2016 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/r-madhavan-gets-aboard-chandamama-door-ke-with-sushant-singh-rajput-4511992/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=7 February 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170207104636/http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/r-madhavan-gets-aboard-chandamama-door-ke-with-sushant-singh-rajput-4511992/ |archivedate= 7 February 2017 }}</ref>\n\n==Other projects==\n===Film and television work===\nMadhavan was first credited as a part of the technical crew for his work in ''[[Ramji Londonwaley]]'', an adaptation of his Tamil film ''[[Nala Damayanthi (2003 film)|Nala Damayanthi]]''. Apart from portraying the lead role, Madhavan worked on the film as a dialogue writer and played an active role in determining the crew of the movie.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.telegraphindia.com/1050901/asp/calcutta/story_5176144.asp |title=The Telegraph \u2013 Calcutta : Metro |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160223141522/http://www.telegraphindia.com/1050901/asp/calcutta/story_5176144.asp |archivedate=23 February 2016 }}</ref><ref name=\"rlpick\">{{cite web\n |year=2005 \n |title='Ramji Londonwale' is Madhavan's baby \n |publisher=Indiaglitz.com \n |accessdate=19 February 2011 \n |url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/malayalam/article/16537.html \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120709035222/http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/malayalam/article/16537.html \n |archivedate= 9 July 2012 \n}}</ref> In October 2007, Madhavan founded the production company, Leukos Films, and consequently bought the rights of his film, ''[[Evano Oruvan]]'', from producers [[Abbas-Mustan]] and [[K. Sera Sera]]. Securing sponsorship deals with [[HSBC]] and Santoor, Madhavan premi\u00e8red the film across North America and the Middle East before its Indian theatrical release, with the promotion method being used for the first time in Tamil cinema.<ref name=\"eoprom\"/> However, since the relative box office failure of the project, Madhavan downplayed future involvement in production ventures.<ref name=\"noprod\">{{cite news|author=Nivas, Namita |year=2009 |title=Great expectations |publisher=Screenindia.com |accessdate=20 February 2011 |url=http://www.screenindia.com/news/great-expectations/557811/ |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100401224559/http://www.screenindia.com/news/great-expectations/557811 |archivedate= 1 April 2010 }}</ref> The film, which Madhavan referred to as a \"part of his life\" during 2007, also saw him write the dialogues for the film along with [[Seeman (director)|Seeman]] by translating lines from the project's original version in the [[Marathi language|Marathi]] language.<ref name=\"eolife\">{{cite news|author=Warrier, Shobha |year=2007 |title=Evano Oruvan is a part of my life |publisher=[[Rediff]] |accessdate=20 February 2011 |url=http://specials.rediff.com/movies/2007/dec/05sl1.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101218084831/http://specials.rediff.com/movies/2007/dec/05sl1.htm |archivedate=18 December 2010 }}</ref> Madhavan then chose to become actively involved in the production of his 2016 bilingual films, ''[[Irudhi Suttru]]'' in Tamil and ''Saala Khadoos'' in Hindi, to ensure the film completed filming and had a theatrical release. Impressed by the strength of [[Sudha Kongara]]'s script for the Tamil film, Madhavan felt that the story had pan-Indian appeal and took the film's script to [[Rajkumar Hirani]], who agreed to produce and supervise work on the film's Hindi version. Madhavan co-produced the Hindi version of the film through his new production house, Tricolor Films, while leading the film's pan-Indian marketing campaign. The actor also helped finalise the film's lead actress, Ritika Singh, and was also credited as an additional screenplay writer in the films.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.khaleejtimes.com/citytimes/bollywood/raj-kumar-hirani-madhavan-confident-about-saala-khadoos |title=Raj Kumar Hirani, Madhavan confident about Saala Khadoos \u2013 Khaleej Times |author=Arti Dani |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160208082731/http://www.khaleejtimes.com/citytimes/bollywood/raj-kumar-hirani-madhavan-confident-about-saala-khadoos |archivedate= 8 February 2016 }}</ref>\n\nMadhavan has appeared as host for television programmes on [[Hindi]] channels, while he has also been a host at film award functions. During his television career in the 1990s, Madhavan first worked as a host on ''Tol Mol Ke Bol''. He was announced as the host of [[Sony Entertainment]] Television's ''[[Deal Ya No Deal]]'', the Indian version of the American game show ''[[Deal Or No Deal]]'', in October 2005. However, Madhavan quit as the lead anchor of the show in January 2006 claiming he was unhappy with the way the shoot schedules were handled by the production house. According to the actor, when he took on the show, he had made it clear that he would continue with his South Indian film assignments, and as the show was being filmed in Mumbai, he had found it hard to keep travelling throughout India from Chennai to film the ten days a month he had signed up for. Madhavan added that he was restricted by the producers to spend one day rehearsing technically, which left him with fatigue.<ref name=\"thambi\">{{cite news|author=Kamath, Sudhish |title=Madhavan returns as 'Thambi' |work=[[The Hindu]] |accessdate=25 February 2006 |url=http://www.hindu.com/2006/02/25/stories/2006022516810200.htm |location=Chennai, India |date=25 February 2006 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060227043310/http://www.hindu.com/2006/02/25/stories/2006022516810200.htm |archivedate=27 February 2006 }}</ref> [[Mandira Bedi]] subsequently replaced Madhavan as the anchor in February for Series 2 of the game show. In June 2010, Madhavan made a comeback to the game show format by accepting a contract with Imagine TV's Big Money show, signing on to host a single season, and then hosted an episode of the crime show [[Savdhaan India]] in January 2016.<ref name=\"left\">{{cite news|author=Kumar, Anuj |title=Maddie \u2013 between big and small |work=[[The Hindu]] |accessdate=21 February 2011 |url=http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article483853.ece |location=Chennai, India |date=24 June 2010 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100820055156/http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article483853.ece |archivedate=20 August 2010 }}</ref> Furthermore, he has been a guest judge in the Indian television show, [[Fame Gurukul]].<ref name=\"gurukul\">{{cite news|author=Kanwar, Rachna|year=2006|title='I have always broken the rules': Madhavan|work=[[The Times of India]]|accessdate=13 January 2006|url=http://tvguide.indiatimes.com/articleshow/1324415.cms|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20051212060507/http://tvguide.indiatimes.com/articleshow/1324415.cms|archive-date=12 December 2005|url-status=live}}</ref> In 2016, Madhavan stated that he would only take part in television commitments for money, while he does not consider his payment when signing on to appear in films.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/will-do-tv-only-for-money-r-madhavan/ |title=Will do TV only for money: R. Madhavan |date=28 January 2016 |work=The Indian Express |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160201073644/http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/will-do-tv-only-for-money-r-madhavan/ |archivedate= 1 February 2016 }}</ref> Madhavan has also hosted live events, notably the [[National Film Awards]] in 2013 with [[Huma Qureshi (actress)|Huma Qureshi]]. He was also the host of the 55th [[Filmfare Awards South]] in [[Chennai]] in 2008 and then also the Vijay Awards in 2013.<ref name=\"ffhosr\">{{cite news|author=Stephenson, Andrew |year=2007 |title=Happy Days at the 55th Filmfare South Awards |publisher=Bollyspice.com |accessdate=20 February 2011 |url=http://bollyspice.com/view.php/1411-happy-days-at-the-55th-tiger-balm-filmfare-south-awards.html |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090614085233/http://www.bollyspice.com/view.php/1411-happy-days-at-the-55th-tiger-balm-filmfare-south-awards.html |archivedate=14 June 2009 }}</ref>\n\n===Brand ambassador===\nMadhavan is amongst the leading brand ambassadors for products in India.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/metroplus/one-film-at-a-time/article1718118.ece|title=One film at a time|author=SUDHISH KAMATH|work=The Hindu|accessdate=16 February 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.livemint.com/Opinion/v6Oi5XAEwLZMbTgSPzkXgN/From-ambassadors-to-influencers.html |title=From ambassadors to influencers |author=Shuchi Bansal |work=livemint.com/ |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160129040854/http://www.livemint.com/Opinion/v6Oi5XAEwLZMbTgSPzkXgN/From-ambassadors-to-influencers.html |archivedate=29 January 2016 }}</ref> His early work involved advertisements for brands including [[Bajaj group|Bajaj]], Ponds, [[Fair and Lovely]] and [[TVS Group|TVS]], before signing a major endorsing deal with [[Pepsi]] and marketing company, IMG.<ref name=\"img\">{{cite news|year=2004 |title=IMG to manage South Indian superstar R.Madhavan |publisher=Indiantelevision.com |accessdate=20 February 2011 |url=http://www.indiantelevision.com/mam/headlines/y2k4/jan/janmam61.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110628182432/http://www.indiantelevision.com/mam/headlines/y2k4/jan/janmam61.htm |archivedate=28 June 2011 }}</ref> In 2007, Madhavan endorsed UniverCell, a multi-brand mobile phone retail chain owned by UniverCell Telecommunications India Pvt Ltd.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/todays-paper/tp-marketing/univercell-ropes-in-actor-madhavan/article1660173.ece |title=UniverCell ropes in actor Madhavan |work=Business Line |date=6 June 2007 |accessdate=13 July 2015}}</ref> Madhavan signed a contract with the mobile phone network, [[Bharti Airtel|Airtel]] for promotions in South India before being promoted as the pan-Indian ambassador for the brand a year later. His advertisements with [[Vidya Balan]] for Airtel won critical acclaim, and brought in film offers for the pair to feature together.<ref name=\"airtel\">{{cite web|year=2009 |title=Madhavan is on a dream run |publisher=[[Sify]] |accessdate=19 February 2011 |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/madhavan-is-on-a-dream-run-news-tamil-kkfsehajfje.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101119082717/http://sify.com/movies/madhavan-is-on-a-dream-run-news-tamil-kkfsehajfje.html |archivedate=19 November 2010 }}</ref> In June 2010, marketers from Arun Excello promoted a housing project in Oragadam, Chennai in a similar fashion to the release of a new film featuring Madhavan. With film-inspired posters and billboards put up around Chennai, the advertisement campaign attracted huge curiosity and the project became a success.<ref name=\"orohiy\">{{cite web|year=2010 |title=Maddy's Oragadam turns out to be a hit |publisher=[[Sify]] |accessdate=19 February 2011 |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/maddys-oragadam-turns-out-to-be-a-hit-news-tamil-kkfquQbcbga.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110228045407/http://www.sify.com/movies/maddys-oragadam-turns-out-to-be-a-hit-news-tamil-kkfquQbcbga.html |archivedate=28 February 2011 }}</ref> His long-term work with jewellery brand, [[Joyalukkas|Joy Alukkas]], led to the company creating life size wax models of him to place in their showrooms from January 2011.<ref name=\"wax\">{{cite news|title='Say cheese' with Madhavan |work=[[The Hindu]] |accessdate=21 February 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/2010/12/29/stories/2010122962750200.htm |location=Chennai, India |date=29 December 2010 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110103000014/http://www.hindu.com/2010/12/29/stories/2010122962750200.htm |archivedate= 3 January 2011 }}</ref> [[Maruti Suzuki]], for whom Madhavan is the brand ambassador, launched a special edition of the [[Suzuki Wagon R]] car calling it the Madhavan Signature Edition in September 2013.<ref name=\"maruti\">{{cite web|author=Yogi, Vikas |year=2013 |title=Maruti Suzuki Launches new Madhavan Signature Edition WagonR |work=[[Business Standard]] |accessdate=16 September 2013 |url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/news-cd/maruti-suzuki-launches-new-madhavan-signature-edition-wagonr-113091600829_1.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130920015724/http://www.business-standard.com/article/news-cd/maruti-suzuki-launches-new-madhavan-signature-edition-wagonr-113091600829_1.html |archivedate=20 September 2013 }}</ref> In 2015, online market place Snapdeal signed on [[Aamir Khan]] and Madhavan to be the company's ambassadors, with Snapdeal attempting to use Madhavan's popularity in South India to marker their services.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehansindia.com/posts/index/2015-10-16/3-Idiots-costars-%EF%BF%BD%E2%82%AC-Aamir-Khan-and-R-Madhavan-to-endorse-Snap-Deal-Big-Sale--181150 |title=3 Idiots Costars \u2013 Aamir Khan And R Madhavan To Endorse Snap Deal Big Sale |work=The Hans India |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160223123922/http://www.thehansindia.com/posts/index/2015-10-16/3-Idiots-costars-%EF%BF%BD%E2%82%AC-Aamir-Khan-and-R-Madhavan-to-endorse-Snap-Deal-Big-Sale--181150 |archivedate=23 February 2016 }}</ref>\n\n===Humanitarian causes===\nMadhavan, who is a vegetarian, promotes vegetarianism and is an active member of [[PETA]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/man-of-many-roles/article24299461.ece|title=Madhavan: man of many roles|last=S|first=Ananya|date=30 June 2018|work=The Hindu|access-date=12 August 2018|issn=0971-751X}}</ref> Since joining [[PETA]] after starring in his first film, he has appeared voluntarily in several advertisements and released an [[Interactive|E-Card]] for the brand. In July 2006, Madhavan was voted the \"cutest male vegetarian\" by an online poll conducted by the NGO, People for Ethical Treatment of Animals (PETA), while [[Kareena Kapoor]] won the female award respectively. In turn he cited that his success in the competition was due to his \"healthy vegetarian diet\".<ref name=\"vege\">{{cite news|author=Subbiah, Anandhan |year=2007 |title=Madhavan and PETA |work=[[The Times of India]] |accessdate=27 July 2007 |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/Calcutta_Times/Maddy__Kareena_cutest_vegetarians/articleshow/2240835.cms |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121025124631/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/Calcutta_Times/Maddy__Kareena_cutest_vegetarians/articleshow/2240835.cms |archivedate=25 October 2012 }}</ref> In October 2010, he wrote a letter to the CEO of [[Kentucky Fried Chicken]], on behalf of PETA, urging them to stop mistreatment of birds by the fast-food industry outlets and the killing of animals. He requested the boycott of KFC in India over animal welfare and conditions and was joined by [[Raveena Tandon]] and [[Rakhi Sawant]] in supporting the work of PETA in India.<ref name=\"kfc\">{{cite news|author=Nivas, Namita|year=2010|title=Earnest request\n|work=[[The Indian Express]]|accessdate=21 February 2011|url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/Not-even-for-his-daughter/697178/}}</ref> In addition, Madhavan was named PETA India\u2019s 2012 \"Person Of The Year\", while his son won PETA India's \"Compassionate Kid award\" in December 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://daily.bhaskar.com/article/ENT-peta-chooses-r-madhavan-as-person-of-the-year-4128229-NOR.html |title=PETA chooses R Madhavan as 'Person of the Year' |work=daily.bhaskar.com |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160224070956/http://daily.bhaskar.com/article/ENT-peta-chooses-r-madhavan-as-person-of-the-year-4128229-NOR.html |archivedate=24 February 2016 }}</ref>\n\nMadhavan has lent his support for the Chennai-based charity, The Banyan, and appeared in the charity musical [[Netru, Indru, Naalai]] directed by Mani Ratnam for the cause.<ref name=\"ninbanyan\">{{cite news\n |year=2005 \n |title=Mani Ratnam to direct Star Vijay's extravaganza \n |publisher=[[Rediff]] \n |accessdate=21 February 2011 \n |url=http://inhome.rediff.com/movies/2005/jun/15mani.htm \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110715165248/http://inhome.rediff.com/movies/2005/jun/15mani.htm \n |archivedate=15 July 2011 \n}}</ref> He appeared as a guest cook and newly launched restaurant in Chennai and cooked [[dosa]]s for auction for the charity, helping raise forty five thousand rupees.<ref name=\"cookhelp\">{{cite news\n |author=Warrier, Shobha \n |year=2006 \n |title=25,000 for a cup of coffee \n |publisher=[[Rediff]] \n |accessdate=21 February 2011 \n |url=http://inhome.rediff.com/movies/2006/jan/18look.htm \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110715165304/http://inhome.rediff.com/movies/2006/jan/18look.htm \n |archivedate=15 July 2011 \n}}</ref> He has been a part of an AIDS awareness programme initiated by [[Richard Gere]] in India and helped advertise the ''A Time for Heroes'' campaign appearing in a short film. Similarly Madhavan featured in a four-minute film produced by Agaram Foundation, ''[[Herova? Zerova?]]'', campaigning for educational awareness alongside [[Suriya]], [[Vijay (actor)|Vijay]] and [[Jyothika]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/holnus/009200805162223.htm |title=TN actors in documentary highlighting evils of child labour |date=16 May 2008 |work=[[The Hindu]] |accessdate=10 February 2010 |location=Chennai, India |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110604120118/http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/holnus/009200805162223.htm |archivedate= 4 June 2011 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://inhome.rediff.com/movies/2008/may/19sssurya.htm |title=Surya, the social activist |date=19 May 2008 |publisher=Rediff |accessdate=10 February 2010 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110715165327/http://inhome.rediff.com/movies/2008/may/19sssurya.htm |archivedate=15 July 2011 }}</ref> In 2010, along with his cast and crew from ''[[3 Idiots]]'', he helped raise Rs. 2.5&nbsp;million for the renovation of the school in [[Leh]], which was damaged by flash floods.<ref>{{Cite news|author=Somabasus, Kavitha |url=http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article613872.ece |title=Moments with Maddy |work=[[The Hindu]] |accessdate=21 February 2011 |location=Chennai, India |date=4 September 2010 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110629125355/http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article613872.ece |archivedate=29 June 2011 }}</ref> Madhavan laid bricks and tiles at the [[London Business School]] in July 2011, building a symbolic house to represent the 100,000 houses that will be built in India by 2015 as a part of Habitat for Humanity's campaign to improve substandard houses in India.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.mid-day.com/entertainment/2011/aug/040811-informer-2.htm |title=Abhishek Bachchan turns teacher |year=2011 |publisher=Mid-Day |accessdate=11 August 2011 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111109051318/http://www.mid-day.com/entertainment/2011/aug/040811-informer-2.htm |archivedate= 9 November 2011 }}</ref> During the [[2015 South Indian floods]], Madhavan worked alongside other Indian actors in coordinating the relief efforts.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/metroplus/fashion/madhavan-on-chennai-floods-the-saala-khadoos-look-and-his-style-factor/article7980456.ece|title=An actor and a style guru|author=Neeraja Murthy|work=The Hindu|accessdate=16 February 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://businessofcinema.com/bollywood_news/chennai-floods-hrithik-roshan-follows-shah-rukh-khan-donates-for-the-victims/258460 |title=Chennai Floods: Hrithik Roshan Follows Shah Rukh Khan, Donates For The Victims |work=Businessofcinema.com |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160223032151/http://businessofcinema.com/bollywood_news/chennai-floods-hrithik-roshan-follows-shah-rukh-khan-donates-for-the-victims/258460 |archivedate=23 February 2016 }}</ref> In 2016, [[Lepra]] India signed him to work as a goodwill ambassador in helping promote action against leprosy.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ians/r-madhavan-is-goodwill-ambassador-against-leprosy-116053000286_1.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=9 June 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160602081004/http://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ians/r-madhavan-is-goodwill-ambassador-against-leprosy-116053000286_1.html |archivedate= 2 June 2016 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Metro Plus |url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-metroplus/ambassador-against-leprosy/article8678575.ece |title=Ambassador against leprosy \u2013 Kochi |work=The Hindu |accessdate=22 January 2018}}</ref>\n\n==In the media==\n[[Image:Madhavanff.JPG|thumb|right|Madhavan seen with his wife, Sarita, at the [[Filmfare Awards]] ceremony in 2011]]\nMadhavan is one of the few actors in India who garners pan-Indian appeal, with his success in establishing himself in the North and the South Indian film industries, seeing him receive multiple offers as a brand ambassador.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/metroplus/the-proust-questionnaire-wish-i-had-bigger-calf-muscles-r-madhavan/article2701284.ece|title=The Proust Questionnaire \u2013 Wish I had bigger calf muscles: R. Madhavan|author=Subha J Rao|work=The Hindu|accessdate=16 February 2016}}</ref> Furthermore, it has led to producers offering him lead roles in bilingual films such as the English-Malayalam crossover film ''[[Nothing But Life]]'' and the Hindi-Tamil projects, ''[[Yavarum Nalam]]'' and ''[[Irudhi Suttru]]''. Moreover, most of his Tamil films are dubbed into Telugu, where he has created a box office market without appearing in a single straight Telugu film as a lead actor.<ref name=\"telugusuc\">{{cite web\n |year=2009 \n |title=Madhavan believes in content \n |publisher=Indiaglitz.com \n |accessdate=19 February 2011 \n |url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/telugu/article/48899.html \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120709093908/http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/telugu/article/48899.html \n |archivedate= 9 July 2012 \n}}</ref><ref name=\"teluglang\">{{cite web\n |author=Tuteja, Joginder \n |year=2010 \n |title=Maddy is against dubbing of his South films \n |publisher=Glamsham.com \n |accessdate=19 February 2011 \n |url=http://www.glamsham.com/movies/scoops/10/may/29-madhavan-is-again-dubbing-of-his-south-films-051009.asp \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110711101403/http://www.glamsham.com/movies/scoops/10/may/29-madhavan-is-again-dubbing-of-his-south-films-051009.asp \n |archivedate=11 July 2011 \n}}</ref> Madhavan holds a significant female fan following, which developed after his romantic roles in ''[[Alaipayuthey]]'' and ''[[Minnale]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/The-Madhavan-magic/articleshow/3250895.cms |title=The Madhavan magic! |work=The Times of India |date=19 July 2008 |accessdate=20 February 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-i-want-to-do-a-romantic-film-r-madhavan-1236093 |title=I want to do a romantic film: R Madhavan & Updates at Daily News & Analysis |work=Daily News and Analysis |date=4 March 2009 |accessdate=20 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160816095936/http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-i-want-to-do-a-romantic-film-r-madhavan-1236093 |archivedate=16 August 2016 }}</ref> Madhavan has also been active in keeping in contact with fans, maintaining a fan email account, a Facebook fan page and a Twitter account as well as being one of the first actors of Tamil films to turn blogger with entries in the year 2000.<ref name=\"blog\">{{cite web|author=Mahaldar, Manisha |year=2008 |title=Of 3 Idiots, blogging and more: Madhavan unplugged |publisher=[[CNN-IBN|IBN]] |accessdate=19 February 2011 |url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/of-3-idiots-blogging-and-more-madhavan-unplugged/73636-8.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120320025443/http://ibnlive.in.com/news/of-3-idiots-blogging-and-more-madhavan-unplugged/73636-8.html |archivedate=20 March 2012 }}</ref>\n\nHe has appeared at functions as a special guest, and has enjoyed particularly close links with technology company, [[Sify]], whom he signed on as his media partner for all his future releases after expressing satisfaction at the website they created for ''[[Rendu]]''.<ref name=\"sifmax\">{{cite news|title=\"Maddy\" charm enlivens Sifymax get-together |work=[[The Hindu]] |accessdate=21 February 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/2006/12/19/stories/2006121901910200.htm |location=Chennai, India |date=19 December 2006 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110629025030/http://www.hindu.com/2006/12/19/stories/2006121901910200.htm |archivedate=29 June 2011 }}</ref> Madhavan sat amongst a six-man jury for the selection of [[CNN]]-[[CNN-IBN|IBN]] Indian of the Year 2006.<ref name=\"gibn\">{{cite news\n |title=6 nominees for CNN-IBN award \n |work=[[The Hindu]] \n |accessdate=21 February 2011 \n |url=http://www.hindu.com/2007/02/01/stories/2007020118491400.htm \n |location=Chennai, India \n |date=1 February 2007 |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110629025051/http://www.hindu.com/2007/02/01/stories/2007020118491400.htm \n |archivedate=29 June 2011 \n}}</ref> He inaugurated the Chennai International Film Festival in 2007, taking the opportunity to deliver a message on preserving the environment.<ref name=\"ciff\">{{cite news|author=Kumar, Ashok |title=Film festival inaugurated |work=[[The Hindu]] |accessdate=21 February 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/2007/12/27/stories/2007122750490200.htm |location=Chennai, India |date=27 December 2007 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110629025132/http://www.hindu.com/2007/12/27/stories/2007122750490200.htm |archivedate=29 June 2011 }}</ref>\n\nA gaming company, Paradox Studios Limited, launched a new game compatible with mobile phones in July 2006, with Madhavan as the lead character. The company released two mobile game titles featuring Madhavan as their lead character.<ref name=\"game\">{{cite news|author=Devi, Sangeetha |title=Maddy to Sameera, everybody's hooked |work=[[The Hindu]] |accessdate=29 July 2006 |url=http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/mp/2006/07/29/stories/2006072902210100.htm |location=Chennai, India |date=29 July 2006 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071001010418/http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/mp/2006/07/29/stories/2006072902210100.htm |archivedate= 1 October 2007 }}</ref> The first of the two games, ''Madhavan's MIG'', featured the actor making a reprise of his [[Rang De Basanti]] pilot's role. In the other game titled ''Madhavan'', the player had to help the actor get to the premi\u00e8re of his latest movie evading the paparazzi.<ref name=\"gametwo\">{{cite news\n |author=Devi, Sangeetha \n |title=Play 'Madhavan' on your Reliance mobile \n |work=[[The Hindu]] \n |accessdate=10 July 2006 \n |url=http://www.hindu.com/2006/07/10/stories/2006071006280200.htm \n |location=Chennai, India \n |date=10 July 2006 |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071001021112/http://www.hindu.com/2006/07/10/stories/2006071006280200.htm \n |archivedate= 1 October 2007 \n}}</ref> In 2007, prominent entrepreneur [[N. R. Narayana Murthy]] requested Madhavan to be his interviewer at the India-Singapore Exposition and Madhavan went on to claim that the experience was \"unforgettable\" as Murthy was an idol to him.<ref name=\"murthy\">{{cite web|author=Warrier, Shobha |year=2007 |title=Maddy on quizzing Narayana Murthy |publisher=[[Rediff]] |accessdate=21 February 2011 |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2007/aug/24maddy.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100412093525/http://www.rediff.com/movies/2007/aug/24maddy.htm |archivedate=12 April 2010 }}</ref> Madhavan has attended conferences as a motivational speaker, talking about issues including situational awareness and confidence, with a speech delivered at [[Dr G R Damodaran College of Science|Damodaran Academy of Management]], [[Coimbatore]] going viral online.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/R-Madhavans-inspiring-speech-has-caught-everyones-attention-/articleshow/50666720.cms |title=R.Madhavan's inspiring speech has caught everyone's attention ! |work=The Times of India |date=21 January 2016 |accessdate=20 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160127041956/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/R-Madhavans-inspiring-speech-has-caught-everyones-attention-/articleshow/50666720.cms |archivedate=27 January 2016 }}</ref> Madhavan also took part and delivered speeches as a part of the annual India Conference at [[Harvard University]] during 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/r-madhavan-unforgettable-moment-while-speaking-at-harvard-university-4522656/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=15 February 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170215122059/http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/r-madhavan-unforgettable-moment-while-speaking-at-harvard-university-4522656/ |archivedate=15 February 2017 }}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nAfter completing the degree, he went on to teach communication and public speaking at workshops around India. At the [[Maharashtra]] workshop, he encountered his wife Sarita Birje for the first time in 1991, when she attended his class on the recommendation of her cousins.<ref name=\"ens\">{{cite web|author=Express News Service |year=1998 |title=The man who acts Pricey |work=[[The Indian Express]] |accessdate=11 August 1998 |url=http://www.indianexpress.com/res/web/pIe/ie/daily/19980811/22351284.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070929091446/http://www.indianexpress.com/res/web/pIe/ie/daily/19980811/22351284.html |archivedate=29 September 2007 }}</ref> Sarita was able to use the skills she had learned from Madhavan's classes to pass an interview to become an air hostess and after completing the course, the pair began dating. They married in 1999, before Madhavan entered mainstream films. The pair's marriage has been covered by the media, with Madhavan citing that advice from his mentor [[Mani Ratnam]] was useful.<ref name=\"twm2015\"/><ref name=\"marriage\">{{cite news|title=Madhavan's marriage tips |work=[[The Times of India]] |accessdate=21 February 2011 |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/news-interviews/Madhavans-relationship-tips/articleshow/7533990.cms |date=21 February 2011 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110225014828/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/news-interviews/Madhavans-relationship-tips/articleshow/7533990.cms |archivedate=25 February 2011 }}</ref> Sarita has worked as a costume designer in a few of Madhavan's films, most notably for ''[[Guru En Aalu]]'' (2009), when she worked along with [[Erum Ali]], the wife of Madhavan's co-star, [[Abbas (actor)|Abbas]], for their respective husbands.<ref name=\"designe\">{{cite web|author=Reddy, Krithika |year=2008 |title=It takes two pairs to tango |work=[[The Hindu]] |accessdate=21 February 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/mp/2008/07/26/stories/2008072651041200.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081106203148/http://www.hindu.com/mp/2008/07/26/stories/2008072651041200.htm |archivedate= 6 November 2008 }}</ref> Their son, Vedaant, was born in August 2005, which eventually led to relocating to the boat-club area in [[Chennai]] from [[Kilpauk]], where Madhavan's parents lived with him as well as his parents-in-law.<ref name=\"vedant\">{{cite web\n |author=Jha, Subhash \n |year=2005 \n |title=Madhavan has a baby boy \n |publisher=Indiaglitz.com \n |accessdate=23 August 2005 \n |url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/hindi/article/16383.html \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20051203074440/http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/hindi/article/16383.html \n |archivedate= 3 December 2005 \n}}</ref> In 2009, he relocated to [[Kandivali]], Mumbai, with his wife and son, as he pursued a career in [[Hindi]] films ahead of films in the South Indian industries.<ref>{{cite web |last= Pereira |first= Priyanka |title= Full Steam |url= http://www.indianexpress.com/news/full-steam/429097/1 |date= 28 February 2009 |work= The Indian Express |accessdate=30 August 2009}}</ref>\n\nMadhavan has maintained close links with fellow actors and has described actor [[Suriya]] as his best friend in the film industry.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/kamal-haasan-and-suriya-wish-madhavan-for-irudhi-suttru-salaa-kadoos-trailer-hollywood-news-148838.html|title=Kamal Haasan and Suriya boost up Madhavan|accessdate=16 February 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171030114616/https://www.indiaglitz.com/kamal-haasan-and-suriya-wish-madhavan-for-irudhi-suttru-salaa-kadoos-trailer-hollywood-news-148838.html|archive-date=30 October 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> The actor also is close friends with actresses [[Shilpa Shetty]] and [[Bipasha Basu]], as well as actors [[Aamir Khan]] and [[Abhishek Bachchan]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/R-Madhavan-Kangana-in-my-opinion-is-extremely-educated/articleshow/47344003.cms |title=R Madhavan: Kangana in my opinion is extremely educated |work=The Times of India |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150522015843/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/R-Madhavan-Kangana-in-my-opinion-is-extremely-educated/articleshow/47344003.cms |archivedate=22 May 2015 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/140814/entertainment-kollywood/article/%E2%80%98madhavan-very-dear-friend%E2%80%99 |title=Madhavan is a very dear friend |work=deccanchronicle.com/ |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150108073357/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/140814/entertainment-kollywood/article/%E2%80%98madhavan-very-dear-friend%E2%80%99 |archivedate= 8 January 2015 }}</ref> He is closely associated with actor [[Kamal Haasan]], after their appearance together in ''[[Anbe Sivam]]'', and has revealed that he considers the actor as his inspiration. He has also collaborated multiple times with directors Mani Ratnam, [[Rajkumar Hirani]] and [[Aanand Rai]], citing that the film makers \"understand him well\" and share a good \"comfort level\". He has also helped out actresses [[Reemma Sen]], [[Sadha]] and [[Nisha Kothari]] by signing them on for roles in his films, when they were going through a barren spell.<ref name=\"nishak\">{{cite news\n |author=Aamir \n |title=Luck by chance \n |work=[[The Hindu]] \n |accessdate=21 February 2011 \n |url=http://www.hindu.com/mp/2009/12/15/stories/2009121550500400.htm \n |location=Chennai, India \n |date=15 December 2009 |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110629025154/http://www.hindu.com/mp/2009/12/15/stories/2009121550500400.htm \n |archivedate=29 June 2011 \n}}</ref><ref name=\"reema\">{{cite web\n |author=Shankar, Settu \n |year=2007 \n |title=Reema returns to Kollywood \n |publisher=OneIndia.com \n |accessdate=1 June 2007 \n |url=http://entertainment.oneindia.in/tamil/exclusive/reema-sen-kollywood-010607.html \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070930163704/http://entertainment.oneindia.in/tamil/exclusive/reema-sen-kollywood-010607.html \n |archivedate=30 September 2007 \n}}</ref><ref name=\"sadha\">{{cite web\n |year=2007 \n |title=Sada replaces Nandana! \n |publisher=[[Sify]] \n |accessdate=27 February 2007 \n |url=http://sify.com/movies/telugu/fullstory.php?id=14395755 \n |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070226065542/http://sify.com/movies/telugu/fullstory.php?id=14395755 \n |archivedate=26 February 2007 \n}}</ref>\n\nMadhavan announced a sabbatical from films in late 2010 citing he would take the time off to visit London, lose weight, play golf, take treatment for his knee injury and spend time with family. Though he kept away from starting new projects, during the period he was involved in the promotional activity of two of his releases, ''[[Manmadan Ambu]]'' and ''[[Tanu Weds Manu]]''.<ref name=\"sabbatical\">{{cite web|year=2010 |title=Maddy all set for a sabbatical |publisher=[[Sify]] |accessdate=21 February 2011 |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/maddy-is-all-set-for-a-sabbatical-news-tamil-kkgu9yhdaec.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101130082411/http://sify.com/movies/maddy-is-all-set-for-a-sabbatical-news-tamil-kkgu9yhdaec.html |archivedate=30 November 2010 }}</ref> He later made a comeback, earlier than anticipated, after director [[N. Linguswamy|Linguswamy]] convinced him to work on ''[[Vettai]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-south-interview-with-madhavan/20120112.htm |title=Madhavan: Vettai has blockbuster written all over it |date=12 January 2012 |work=Rediff |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160229235933/http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-south-interview-with-madhavan/20120112.htm |archivedate=29 February 2016 }}</ref> The actor later took an extended sabbatical from 2012 onwards to work on his fitness and get into shape for his role as a retired boxer in ''[[Irudhi Suttru]]''. Madhavan is a keen golf player, having played for pleasure alongside actor [[Amitabh Bachchan]] and director [[Mani Ratnam]], while also appearing in a celebrity charity event in 2007.<ref name=\"golf\">{{cite news\n |author=Anthikad-Chibber, Mini \n |title=The Dark Knight \n |work=[[The Hindu]] \n |accessdate=21 February 2011 \n |url=http://www.hindu.com/mp/2010/02/25/stories/2010022550280400.htm \n |location=Chennai, India \n |date=25 February 2010 |url-status=live \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110629025202/http://www.hindu.com/mp/2010/02/25/stories/2010022550280400.htm \n |archivedate=29 June 2011 \n}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.openthemagazine.com/article/cinema/a-tamilian-in-bollywood |title=A Tamilian in Bollywood |work=OPEN Magazine |accessdate=16 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160307194515/http://www.openthemagazine.com/article/cinema/a-tamilian-in-bollywood |archivedate= 7 March 2016 }}</ref> In 2017, he won the qualification round of the Mumbai leg of the Mercedes Trophy golf meet and subsequently qualified for the National Finals.<ref>https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/actor-madhavn-qualifies-national-finals-mercedes-trophy-golf-meet-74616</ref> He also made an appearance for Chennai Rhinos in the [[2011 Celebrity Cricket League]], playing against Karnataka Bulldozers. His experiences flying Cessna planes when he was with National Cadet Corps, also led to a passion for aero-modelling, with the actor stating it \"justified his decision\" to pursue a degree in electronics.<ref name=\"aeromodel\">{{cite news|author=Sinha, Sayoni |title=Madhavan's flight club |work=[[The Times of India]] |accessdate=21 February 2011 |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/news-interviews/Madhavans-flight-Club/articleshow/6313917.cms |date=15 August 2010 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100820014329/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/news-interviews/Madhavans-flight-Club/articleshow/6313917.cms |archivedate=20 August 2010 }}</ref>\n\n==Filmography and awards==\n{{main|R. Madhavan filmography}}\n\n===Awards and nominations===\nAmong Madhavan's film awards are four [[Filmfare Awards South|Filmfare Awards]];\n* [[Filmfare Award for Best Male Debut \u2013 South|Best South Male Debut]] for ''Alaipayuthey''\n* [[Filmfare Award for Best Supporting Actor \u2013 Tamil|Best Tamil Supporting Actor]] for ''Aaytha Ezhuthu''\n* [[Filmfare Award for Best Actor \u2013 Tamil|Best Tamil Actor]] for ''Irudhi Suttru''\n* [[Filmfare Critics Award for Best Actor \u2013 South|Critics' Best Tamil Actor]] for ''Vikram Vedha''\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{wikiquote}}\n{{commons category|Madhavan}}\n{{good article}}\n* {{IMDb name|id=0534856}}\n* [https://www.bollywoodhungama.com/celebrity/r-madhavan/ R. Madhavan] on [[Bollywood Hungama]]\n\n{{FilmfareTamilBestActor}}\n{{TamilNaduStateAwardForBestActor}}\n{{ScreenAwardBestMaleDebut}}\n{{SIIMA Award for Best Actor in a Supporting Role}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Madhavan, R}}\n[[Category:1970 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Tamil male actors]]\n[[Category:Indian game show hosts]]\n[[Category:Male actors in Kannada cinema]]\n[[Category:Indian male television actors]]\n[[Category:Indian male film actors]]\n[[Category:Indian television presenters]]\n[[Category:People from Jamshedpur]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Jharkhand]]\n[[Category:Indian male screenwriters]]\n[[Category:Film producers from Jharkhand]]\n[[Category:Male actors in Hindi cinema]]\n[[Category:Male actors in Malayalam cinema]]\n[[Category:Tamil Nadu State Film Awards winners]]\n[[Category:Filmfare Awards South winners]]\n[[Category:International Tamil Film Award winners]]\n[[Category:SIIMA Awards winners]]\n[[Category:Tamil actors]]\n", "name_user": "117.103.86.34", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/R._Madhavan"}
